title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda. Combine butter, sugars, pudding, and vanilla in large mixing bowl. Beat until smooth and creamy. Beat in eggs, gradually adding flour mixture. Then stir in chips & nuts.

title: play dough
directions: Mix salt, flour and cream of tartar in large pan.
Add water, oil and coloring.
Stir until well blended.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture gets rubbery.
Turn dough onto flat surface and knead.
Keep in airtight containers.

title: boarding house orange tea
directions: Combine 1 cup water, cloves and cinnamon.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Add honey, 1 cup water and orange juice, bringing to boiling.
Remove from heat and add tea bags.
Let steep, covered, for 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags and spices.
Pour into cups and serve at once with floaters of quartered orange slices.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: cheddar cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter and blend in flour.
Gradually add milk and cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Blend in cheese, salt and seasonings.
Yields 1 quart.

title: graham cracker log
directions: Combine marshmallows, dates and walnuts; mix thoroughly with 1 3/4 cups cracker crumbs.
Add unwhipped cream; mix well.
Shape into roll; coat in remaining crumbs.
Wrap well in waxed paper; refrigerate for at least 6 hours.
Slice; serve with whipped cream.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken with onion, salt and pepper.
Debone chicken. Mix soups and broth.
Layer chicken and soup mixture and vegetables.
Mix together flour, buttermilk and butter.
Pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter; add flour and a little of the quart of water, enough to get it mixed.
Then add broccoli, 1 quart milk and rest of 1 quart water.
Stir until it begins to thicken, then add rest of milk, water and chicken soup.
Let simmer for awhile.
Stir frequently to keep from sticking.
When serving, add a little grated cheese to each serving.

title: e. z. quiche
directions: Tear crusts from bread; line in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer cheese, ham and broccoli, then bread centers.
Mix eggs, milk and onion, then pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: gourmet beans
directions: Cook the onion and tomato in butter. Add to remaining ingredients.
Heat in oven for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: pralines
directions: In a saucepan mix milk and sugar together and bring to a boil. On low flame cook until a drop forms a ball in water.
Remove from fire and add pecans, vanilla and butter.
Beat until slightly thick.
Drop spoonful on wax paper.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding with 3 c milk. Mix cool whip in pudding, set aside. Butter bottom and sides of a 9 x 13 glass pan. Lay whole graham crackers on bottom of pan. Pour 1/2 of pudding mixture over graham crackers. Add another layer of crackers, then pour the remaining pudding over the crackers. Next, put one more layer of crackers on top of the pudding.

title: oklahoma guacamole dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: honey appetizer wings
directions: Cut off and discard chicken wing tips.
Cut each wing into 2 parts and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place wings in slow cooker and pour sauce over.
Cook all day on low setting.
Or, preheat oven to 375°, place wings in shallow casserole, pour sauce over and bake until chicken is well done and sauce is caramelized about 1 hour.

title: cranberry nut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 inch baking pan.
Beat eggs in a medium mixing bowl until thick.
Gradually add sugar, beating until thoroughly blended.
Stir in flour and melted butter, blend well.
Add cranberries and walnuts, mixing gently just until combined.
Spread evenly in pan.
Bake for 40-45 minutes or until golden brown and a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.
Cool and cut into bars.
Makes 16 servings.

title: orange ball
directions: Crush vanilla wafers to fine crumbs.
Add next 4 ingredients and mix well.
With hand, form into balls; chill until firm.
Roll balls into coconut.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: oatmeal peek-a-boos
directions: Sift together in bowl flour, baking soda and salt.
Add shortening, sugar, egg, vanilla and water.
Beat until smooth. Blend in oats.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Roll out on lightly floured board to 1/8-inch thickness.
Using a floured, 2 1/2-inch round cookie cutter, cut cookie rounds.
Then use a smaller cutter or sharp knife to cut design in center of half the cookies.
Be sure to remove centers.
Place whole plain cookie mounds on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: no-sweat hiker's pie
directions: Spoon soft ice cream into the pie shell.
Sprinkle peanut butter chips over ice cream.
Put Cool Whip over peanut butter chips.
Sprinkle trail mix over whipped topping.
Freeze and serve!

title: cheesy chicken bake
directions: Mix chicken soup with white wine.
Top each piece of chicken with 1 piece of Swiss cheese; cover with soup/wine mixture.
Cover with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cheese frosted cauliflower
directions: Wash cauliflower.
Remove leaves and cut out base (be sure it is even at the bottom so it will sit evenly in serving dish). Cook, covered, in boiling salted water 12 to 15 minutes or until tender; drain well.
Place in shallow baking pan or ovenproof dish. Combine mayonnaise and mustard.
Spread over cauliflower.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika and garish as desired.
This sauce can also be used over broccoli, sliced carrots or other veggies.
If low fat mayonnaise is used, it won't melt as much as is not as tasty.

title: egg nog pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in egg nog.
Add sugar and nutmeg.
Heat in double boiler.
Refrigerate until slightly jelled.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into 9-inch graham cracker crust and decorate with shaved chocolate.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together all ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 13
x
2-inch
pan and bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini-parmesan
directions: Cut zucchini into discs and dip in melted butter.
In gallon size Baggie, combine cheese, crumbs, salt and pepper.
After dipping squash in butter, drop into Baggie and toss to cover. Place squash on baking sheet lined with foil. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until browned and tender.

title: garden pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain and rinse with
cold water.
Cut tomatoes into chunks.
In a large bowl, combine
all
ingredients; toss to coat and chill before serving. Makes 10 cups.

title: congri
directions: If dry beans, soak overnight and cook until soft the next day. Saute ingredients.
Add beans, tomato sauce, etc.
Mix well and add water to make 2 or more cups of liquid.
Bring to a boil; add rice. When rice surfaces, turn off heat.
Cover until done, 1/2 hour. Depending on your stove, you may need to put it on simmer.
Mine cooks with the heat only.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Shape into balls.
Put into flat pan and cover with sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: beef or pork tamales
directions: Cream the lard until it is very soft.

Add the flour, little by little, and continue beating either by hand or with a mixer. Add broth as needed, the salt, baking powder and cumin. Keep the dough soft but not too wet. Put the corn husks to soak in hot water and rinse them well.

title: festive cherry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatins in boiling water; stir in orange juice. Chill until mixture is the consistency of an unbeaten egg white. Fold in remaining ingredients; spoon into a lightly oiled 5-cup mold.
Chill until set.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix in large bowl:
sugar, Bisquick, egg and orange juice. Fold in nuts and cranberries.
Bake in greased baking pans at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 small loaves or 1 angel food pan. Can be made in coffee tins or soup cans for holiday gifts.

title: quick easy meal
directions: Combine all ingredients in a skillet large enough to be able to stir.
Saute until potatoes are done turning as needed.
Serve with bread and butter.

title: pumpkin or squash pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, milk, syrup, eggs, sugars, cinnamon, salt, ginger and cloves in top of double boiler and cook over hot water until thick.
Cool; add brandy and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and freeze.
Let set at room temperature for 30 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cherokee corn
directions: Mix all ingredients, except save 1 cup cheese to top casserole. Pour in greased casserole dish. Top with saved cheese. Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: frozen raspberry salad
directions: Combine marshmallows and orange juice.
Microwave for 1 minute and 30 seconds on High, stirring until marshmallows are melted. Let cool.
Add cream cheese and mayonnaise to cooled mixture; beat until smooth.
Whip cream; stir in whipped cream, raspberries and pecans.
Pour into lightly oiled 7 1/2 x 3 x 2-inch loaf pan; freeze overnight.

title: crab casserole
directions: Toss crab with wine.
Marinate for 30 minutes. Combine cream, mustard, salt and thyme. Toss crab, celery and eggs with mixture. Place in buttered casserole dish. Sprinkle with almonds and cheese.
Pour butter over it.
Bake.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Make a well in the center. Combine egg, zucchini, honey, oil and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into well of dry ingredients.
Stir until moist.
Stir in walnuts. Spoon into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Yields 1 to 1 1/2 dozen.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Place butter in a small saucepan and bring to a boil. Remove from heat; stir in sour cream and sugar. Cool mixture to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl. Stir in sour cream mixture and eggs. Combine flour and salt. Gradually add to yeast mixture, mixing well. Cover dough and refrigerate overnight. Punch down dough and divide into 4 equal parts. Roll each into a 10-inch circle on a floured surface; brush with butter. Cut into 12 wedges. Roll up each wedge, beginning at wide end. Place on greased baking sheet. Cover and let rise in warm place, free of draft, until double, about 1 hour. Bake at 375° for 10 or 12 minutes. Yield: 4 dozen.

title: overnight chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl, except the bread crumbs and refrigerate overnight.
Stir next morning and put mixture into a 9 x 13-inch casserole or baking dish of same volume.
Sprinkle the top with bread crumbs, if desired.
Cover casserole with foil and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and continue to bake another 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 8, depending on appetites.

title: paper cup frozen salads
directions: Stir together first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; stir in food color, nuts and cherries. Place cups in muffin pan; spoon fruit mixture evenly into cups. Cover; freeze 8 hours. Remove from freezer. Let stand 15 minutes before serving. Makes 1 dozen cups.

title: meringue kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until almost stiff.
Add sugar while beating egg whites until stiff.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Mix together the chicken, pineapple, celery, mandarin oranges, black olives, green peppers and onions.
In separate bowl combine mustard and mayo and then mix this blend with first mixture. Chill several hours.
Serve with green grapes on the side.
A lovely luncheon plate.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Store in airtight container. When ready to drink, place as much as you desire in a mug and fill with hot water.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Prepare and bake cake mix as directed on package.
When cake is still warm, but not hot, poke holes in cake about 1 inch apart (use handle of wooden spoon).
Pour sweetened condensed milk over cake, then pour butterscotch caramel fudge over cake.
Refrigerate until completely cooled, about 1 hour.
Top with whipped topping and crushed candy bars.
Keep refrigerated.
Yields 15 to 25 servings.

title: herb coated baked drumsticks(fun and easy)
directions: Blend yogurt, garlic, oil, maple syrup and mustard.
Add chicken; turn to coat.
Let marinate in refrigerator for 1 hour. Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine bread crumbs and herbs.
Dip drumsticks into crumb mixture, turning to coat them thickly. Place on baking sheet and bake for 35 to 45 minutes.
Contains 288 calories per serving.

title: blueberry stack cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl add margarine, eggs, milk, vanilla and cake mix blending well.
Bake in six thin layers.
Set aside to cool.
For filling, cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Add whipped topping.
Layer cake, cream cheese mixture and pie filling until all cake layers are used.
Refrigerate.

title: snowball dessert
directions: Drain pineapple and cherries; reserve juice.
Mix first 6 ingredients together; toss lightly, pudding mix and juice from pineapple and cherries being sure the juice is 1 cup.
Press fruit down into pudding mixture and chill in covered tightly dish. Refrigerate a couple of hours or overnight.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix above ingredients.
This will be thick.
Pour in 9 x 13 inch or 10 x 15 inch pan.
Bake until cake tests done.

title: easy casserole
directions: Layer each ingredient in a greased casserole.
Bake, covered, until potatoes are done.

title: impossible coconut pie(makes its own crust)
directions: Beat eggs well and add above ingredients.
Pour into well greased pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oven fried crispy chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Wash chicken and pat dry.
Melt shortening and butter in baking pan.
Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Coat chicken with flour mixture.
Place chicken, skin side down, in melted shortening.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes; turn chicken over and bake 30 minutes longer until pieces are tender.

title: ham and potato breakfast casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except paprika in large bowl.
Pour into ungreased rectangular baking dish, 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, until a knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: ham it ups
directions: Unroll dough into 4 rectangles and seal.
Place ham on rectangles and top with ham, mustard and cheese.
Start at shortest side and roll.
Press edges to seal.
Coat rolls with sesame seed.
Cut each roll into 5 slices.
Place cut side on pan. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: cheesy mexican pasta
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add rest of ingredients and beat well.
Drop dough from spoon on greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: venison sausage balls(microwave)
directions: Roll sausage in small balls and place on the outer edge of bacon rack or round plate with paper towels under and over sausage.
Microwave for 45 seconds for each sausage ball.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly and roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased pans and bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: frozen lemonade squares
directions: Mix graham crumbs and margarine; press on bottom of 9-inch square pan.
Blend frozen yogurt and lemonade concentrate in large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. Spread on crust.
Freeze 4 hours or until firm.
Cut into squares. Garnish with cool whip if desired.
Makes 9 servings.

title: pasta sauce(different and delicious)
directions: Mix the tomato soup and water (stir to get all tomato soup cup oil.
When transparent, but not brown, combine with tomato mixture.
Heat to a simmer.
Add cheese that has been cut into small bits.
Stir until melted.
Small shell pasta is nice with this, some prefer spaghetti.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream butter with sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Put soda in sour milk and add to mixture.
Add vanilla, flour and salt.
Stir just until all ingredients are moistened.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into 1 large loaf pan or 2 small ones.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool slightly and remove from pan.

title: pecan surprise bar
directions: Reserve 2/3 cup cake mix.
Combine remaining cake mix with oleo and 1 egg.
Mix until crumbly.
Press into well-greased 11 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine reserved 2/3 cake mix with remaining 3 eggs, brown sugar, syrup and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour over baked crust.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until filling is set.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: wieners in sauce
directions: Combine last two ingredients to make paste.
Combine all other ingredients; mix with paste.
Make slices longwise in wieners. Arrange in large shallow pan and pour sauce over it.
Cook on medium heat until sauce is thick and cooked through wieners. Makes enough for 1 pound of wieners.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Cut cake into 1 inch cubes. Mix half of Cool Whip with cake. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix remaining half of Cool Whip, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; spread on top of cake mixture. Fold strawberries in glaze and spoon on top.
Chill.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 450° until brown in an oblong pan.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients until crumbly, then add enough ice water to hold the mixture together. Start with about 5 tablespoons.
May have to add more. This will make a 9 or 10-inch two-crust pie.

title: dorothy's ham barbecues
directions: Boil together for 3/4 hour.
Add chipped ham.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Break up lettuce and cover bottom of 12 x 9-inch pan.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain.
Crumble bacon over lettuce.
Thinly slice onion and layer over bacon.
Break or slice cauliflower into bite-size pieces and place over onion.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar; drizzle over cauliflower.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Toss and serve.

title: leg of lamb
directions: Debone lamb and tie.
Bake 3 hours at 350°, basting often with Worcestershire sauce.
Serve with mint jelly.

title: amaretto cake
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add cake mix, pudding (dry), Amaretto, flavorings, water and oil.
Beat for 10 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot and pear pie
directions: Prepare pie crust according to package directions for two crust pie, using a 9-inch pan.
Heat oven to 425°.

title: trail mix
directions: Combine all ingredients. Store in tightly covered bowl.

title: dilled sour cream and cucumbers
directions: Mix cucumbers with vinegar, parsley, sugar, seasonings, green onions and sour cream.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours. Garnish with tomato wedges.

title: peanut butter meltaways
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into balls or form into long rolls for slicing.

title: brandy slush
directions: Bring to boil water and sugar and remove.
Add tea bags for about 5 minutes and then remove from mixture.
Add frozen lemonade and frozen orange juice.
Add brandy or favorite fruit liqueur and maraschino cherries and the juice.
Pour into tray and freeze. (Takes about 24 hours to get slushy.)
Serve half and half with ginger ale.

title: son-of-a-gun-stew
directions: Dredge beef in seasoned flour until well coated. In Dutch oven, brown beef in bacon fat. Cover with water and simmer, covered, for 1 hour. Add carrots; simmer 30 minutes longer. Add cabbage and cook 15 minutes. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Top stew with cornmeal dumpling if desired.

title: double chocolate muffins
directions: In
large
bowl, combine flour, cocoa, sugar and baking powder.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onion and pepper in large bowl; set aside.
Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and celery salt.
Pour over vegetables and put in refrigerator overnight.
Great for picnics.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Add other ingredients. Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine Parmesan cheese and seasonings and set aside.
Layer 1/3 of the potatoes in casserole and top with half of the seasoning.
Repeat process ending with potatoes.
Combine whipping cream and water.
Pour over potatoes.
Top with cheddar cheese. Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 1-1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake 30 min. more.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat and drain off fat.
Add all ingredients except cheese.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add cheese.
Simmer another hour.
Let set overnight, if possible.

title: italian beef sandwiches
directions: Start 24 hours before you want to eat. Put roast in crock-pot. Sprinkle with packages of dry salad dressing mix. Pour pepperoncinis, juice and all over roast. Start on high for 2 hours, then turn to low. Before serving, pull apart and put on sub rolls or buns.

title: fresh sun-dried tomato sauce
directions: Combine the fresh tomatoes, sun-dried tomatoes, basil, parsley, olive oil, garlic and black pepper; stir to blend.
Toss sauce with hot pasta and serve at once.
(Use tubetti, ditalini or small shells.)

title: broccoli lima bean casserole
directions: Mix soups and sour cream together with veggies.
Next layer is water chestnuts.
Brown Rice Krispies in oleo; sprinkle on top of casserole.

title: chicken coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, chicken, apples, grapes, celery and walnuts in large bowl.
Set aside.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise, honey, lemon juice, salt and pepper; stir until smooth.
Pour over chicken mixture and toss gently.
Cover and chill 1 to 2 hours. To serve, spoon coleslaw into a lettuce-lined bowl if desired. Yields 6 servings.

title: crab soup
directions: Dilute with 3 cans of whole milk.
Heat and add crabmeat and seasoning.
Some cream may be used in place of milk (optional).

title: lime jell-o salad
directions: Mix jello according to pkg. directions.
Dissolve cream cheese while jello is hot.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill until set.
Use the largest size of Pyrex dish.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut potatoes in quarters.
Place potatoes in large roasting pan with olive oil and remaining ingredients; toss to coat.

title: teriyaki burgers
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
In a large bowl, combine soy sauce, catsup and 1 tablespoon pineapple juice.
Remove 3 tablespoons of mixture.
Set aside.
To remainder, add marjoram, garlic powder and ginger.
Blend well.
Add onion, ground beef and Chex crumbs.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into 4 patties.
Add 1/2 teaspoon brown sugar to reserved soy sauce mixture.
Grill or broil to desired doneness, brushing with reserved sauce. Meanwhile, saute pineapple slices in remaining brown sugar and butter.
Serve atop burgers.
Serves 4.

title: pear pie
directions: Peel and cut up pears (same as for apple pie).
Cream butter, eggs, sugar and flour and add vanilla to mixture.
Mix pears into creamed mixture and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.
Can be baked without any crust.
Makes a good dessert.

title: baked apples
directions: Use a flat Pyrex dish.
Place apple halves cut side up. Sprinkle flour on top of apples; pour sugar evenly on top of flour. Sprinkle all sparingly with allspice or nutmeg.
Dot each half with a little bit of oleo.
Bake at 375° (uncovered) 30 minutes or until tender.

title: pork roast and sauerkraut
directions: Season roast with salt and pepper; brown in a skillet, then transfer to a roasting pan.
Combine undrained kraut with remaining ingredients; spoon over roast.
Simmer in a 350° oven, covered, for 1 3/4 hours or until done.
Baste with juice during last 1/2 hour.
Skim excess fat.
Slice roast and serve kraut as a side dish.
Serves 6.

title: tomato, montrachet and basil salad *
directions: Core tomatoes; cut into thick slices, then cut into halves. Transfer to a mixing bowl.
Peel onion; slice into thin rings. Add to bowl and turn gently with a spoon.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese and again turn gently.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Just before serving, transfer salad to a serving bowl and crumble cheese over all.
Makes 6 to 8 portions.

title: vanilla chunk chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Mix brownie mix (dry), syrup, flour, oil and eggs.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop onto cookie sheet by spoonfuls.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and add cake mix.
Bake. Frost with powdered sugar, strawberries and juice (other half of package of strawberries).

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix ingredients together to make dough for rolling, working with hands if necessary.
Sprinkle waxed paper with powdered sugar. Divide the dough into several balls.
Place 1 ball on the sprinkled wax paper.
Roll dough with rolling pin to desired thickness. Spread with peanut butter.
Roll up like jelly roll and cut into slices.

title: chocolate-mint cups
directions: Melt chocolate over low heat, stirring constantly.
Set chocolate aside to cool.
Combine butter and sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add chocolate and extracts; mix well.
Combine vanilla wafers crumbs and pecans; stir well.
Sprinkle half of crumb mixture into 12 ungreased muffin cups.
Spoon chocolate mixture over crumb mixture and top with remaining crumb mixture. Cover and freeze until firm.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix together butter, cream cheese and sugar until creamy; set aside.
Combine pudding with milk; mix until slightly thick.
Add butter, cream cheese and sugar mixture; mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Grind Oreos very fine.

title: paradise pudding
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Chill. When slightly thickened, beat to consistency of whipped cream.
Combine nuts, marshmallows, cherries, macaroons, sugar and salt.
Add to Jell-O. Fold in cream.
Turn into loaf pan (7 x 5 x 3-inch). Chill until firm.

title: rice pulao with peas
directions: Heat butter in a heavy pan.
Add cloves and cinnamon.
Add turmeric and caraway seed.
Fry spices slowly for a minute over low heat.
Add rice, peas and salt.
Mix and fry gently 2 to 3 minutes, stirring.
Add hot water; bring to a boil.
Then turn the heat very low and cook for 15 to 20 minutes with the lid on.
Add hard-boiled eggs, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: santa fe casserole bake
directions: In medium skillet, brown meat and stir until bubbly; drain fat.
Add taco seasoning and blend well.
In a small bowl, combine broth and flour.
Add to meat mixture; bring to a boil to slightly thicken liquid.
Stir in sour cream and chilies; blend well.
In 9 x 13
container, lightly greased, placed 1/2 of the green onions. Layer again with remaining ingredients, ending with green onions. Bake uncovered, in 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Yields 6 servings.

title: bridge meringue torte
directions: To egg whites, add vanilla, cream of tartar and dash of salt. Beat to soft peaks.
Gradually add sugar, beating to very stiff peaks.
Cover two cookie sheets with parchment paper.
Spread meringue into 9-inch circles on paper.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour. Turn off heat; let dry in oven (door closed) for at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: wedding punch
directions: Chill together.
Before serving, stir in 1 quart of ginger ale.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Add pumpkin, syrup, eggs and vanilla, mixing well.
Pour into pie shell and top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until set.
Chill and serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: chicken salad(serves 4)
directions: Coat nonstick pan with cooking spray.
Arrange chicken in single layer in pan.
Cook covered on medium heat until cooked through, about 7 minutes, turning once.
Let cool.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: zucchini elegante
directions: Wash and slice zucchini about 1/2-inch thick.
Cook in boiling, salted water, covered, until tender.
Saute onion in oil until yellow.
Add parsley and remove from heat.
Drain zucchini. Place in casserole in layers with tomatoes and the oil and onion mixture.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with grated cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: coffee cake
directions: Beat first 7 ingredients for 8 minutes.
In separate bowl, mix together next 3 ingredients.
Pour half of batter into Bundt pan. Sprinkle sugar, nuts and cinnamon mixture on top and swirl through batter.
Pour remaining batter into pan.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.
Add glaze.

title: boiled frosting
directions: Combine sugar, cream of tartar, salt and water in a heavy saucepan.

Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until clear. Cook over medium heat without stirring to soft boil stage (240°). Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until soft peaks form. Continue to beat, slowly adding syrup mixture.

title: hot herb bread
directions: Cut bread diagonally into 1-inch slices.
Blend margarine, parsley, oregano, dill and garlic.
Spread margarine between slices.
Wrap foil around bread boat-fashion, twisting ends and leaving top open.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Heat in hot oven (400°) for 10 minutes.

title: fudge cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, eggs, syrup, 1 teaspoon vanilla, flour and nuts.
Pour into sheet pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: four pepper barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Lightly coat a 2-quart saucepan with nonstick spray and place over low heat. Add the onion, scallions, peppers and garlic. Cover and cook about 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Add ketchup, tomatoes, molasses, vinegar, oregano, Worcestershire sauce and black pepper.

Cover and simmer until thickened, about 10 minutes. Grill chicken for 4 minutes, turn, then spread 2 to 3 tablespoons over each piece of chicken breast. Continue grilling until chicken is done, about 5 to 6 minutes.
Serve with the remaining sauce. Serves 4.
Contains 354 calories and 4.3 grams fat.

title: everything omelette
directions: Saute ham, onion, pepper and mushrooms in about 1 teaspoon butter. Beat eggs and milk together in a bowl. Heat frying pan with enough oil to coat pan, at about medium heat. Then reduce heat to low-medium and add half of the eggs. Make sure the eggs coat the pan. Then add the cheese and tomatoes on half of egg. After cheese melts and eggs cook, add the other ingredients. Then put the other half of egg on top of ingredients and serve. Then repeat recipe for the other omelette. Yields 2 (3 egg) omelettes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Add liquids and beat well. Bake in 2 greased loaf pans or 4 greased 1-pound coffee cans. Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes. Let cool and remove from cans. Freezes well. (May bake in 1 large tube pan.)

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain. Add sauce, sugar and water. Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes. In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 1/3 sauce, layer of noodles, and 1/2 cottage cheese. Repeat layers again. Top with remaining sauce and Mozzarella cheese. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Turn off oven and remove foil. Let stand for at least 30 minutes. The longer it stands before serving, the better it is.

title: cowboy chili
directions: Crumble beef into heavy pot or Dutch oven.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook over medium to high heat until meat is browned, about 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, beef bouillon, chili powder, cumin, oregano, salt and cayenne.
Cover.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, for 1 hour.
Add the beans and continue simmering until beans fall apart.
Add water if chili becomes too thick.
Serve piping hot. Serve with tortilla chips and green salad.

title: lemon-yam puff
directions: Cook yams in boiling salted water until tender.
Peel; mash or put through a ricer.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until light.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Dot with butter before serving.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: new england noodles supreme(microwave)
directions: Place water and salt in a 2-quart dish.
Cover dish and microwave at High for 10 to 11 minutes. Stir in noodles.
Cover dish and cook on High for 8 to 9 minutes. Stir once.
Drain.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain. Stir in refried beans, tomato sauce, taco seasoning, onion, green pepper, dry mustard and 1/2 teaspoon chili powder.
Heat until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Spread in ungreased chafing dish. Combine sour cream and 1/4 teaspoon chili powder in small bowl; mix well.
Spread over bean mixture.
Garnish with shredded lettuce and chopped black olives, tomatoes and green onions. Serve with tortilla chips.
A double recipe may be kept warm in an electric skillet.

title: mounds candy
directions: Mix milk, sugar, butter, vanilla and coconut together. Place in refrigerator over night. Roll mixture in to 1 inch balls and place on wax paper. Put in freezer overnight. Melt chocolate bark coating and dip coconut balls in it. Place on wax paper to set.

title: lentil soup
directions: Place lentils in water with salt and cook over medium heat for about 1/2 hour (while preparing vegetables).
Skim the film that develops at the top of the water.

title: annie's banana loaf
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and continue to beat.
In a separate bowl, chop bananas and add to mixture; add pecans.
Add flour and mix well.
Pour in a loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: calico beans
directions: Place all ingredients in a 3-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done. Do not stir while cooking.

title: cookies 'n cream dessert
directions: Dip your cookies in the milk and spread them out on your dish. You've made one layer, then spread out a layer of Cool Whip. Next, add a layer of cookies and another layer of Cool Whip.
Put wrapping paper on your dish; keep it in the refrigerator for 3 hours or overnight.

title: oriental salad
directions: Chop cabbage and green onions.
Melt margarine in skillet. Break up noodles into small pieces.
Add noodles, almonds and sesame seed to margarine.
Stir until lightly browned.
Cool.
Mix remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute.
Cool.
Just before serving, toss noodle mixture with cabbage and dressing.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Arrange potatoes in 13 x 9-inch baking dish; salt and pepper. Spread onion, soup, sour cream and cheese on top.
Spread corn flake crumbs over top and then top with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crunchy chocolate pie crust
directions: Melt chips and butter in double boiler.
Add cornflakes and mix well.
Press over bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate. Chill until firm.

title: fudge roll
directions: Mix sugar, milk, Karo and chocolate and cook to soft ball stage (232°).
Remove from heat and add butter.
Blend.
Put pan of cold water and cool until cool enough to hold hand under pan.
Add vanilla and beat with electric beater until hard.
Knead by hand and form into rolls.
Roll in pecans, pressing nuts into roll. Wrap in foil; chill and slice.

title: my favorite rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and combine last 3 ingredients. Add flour to
yeast mixture.
Cover and let rise 1 hour.
Roll out dough
and	cut
with
biscuit
cutter.
Dip
each roll in melted butter
and
fold
into
pocketbook rolls.	(I cut with biscuit cutter
and
brush	or spoon on melted margarine.) Let rise 2 hours.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for about 8 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate-coconut cheesecake
directions: Stir together first 3 ingredients; press mixture in bottom of a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes; cool.

title: chicken spaghetti for a crowd
directions: Saute vegetables in margarine.
Add to remaining ingredients. Pour into two 9 x 13-inch casseroles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: covered bridge salad
directions: Prepare vegetables and drain.
Chop eggs.
Toss together in deep dish.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours before serving.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Heat margarine in rectangular pan until melted.
Mix baking mix, paprika, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken. Place chicken, skin side down, in pan.
Bake, uncovered, 35 minutes.
Turn; bake until done, about 15 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hidden valley club salad
directions: In a 3-quart clear glass layered salad bowl, carefully layer lettuce, 1 cup dressing, diced tomatoes (place cherry tomato halves up against the side of bowl), croutons, ham, cheese and turkey.
Line ingredients up against side of bowl to make distinct layers.
Pour remaining 1 cup dressing over top.

title: crabmeat on english muffins
directions: Defrost fish and go through to make sure there is no shell. Melt cheese and butter; to this, add fish and mayo.
Toast muffins and spread the mixture on the muffins.
Before serving, put in oven at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Muffins can be cut into fourths for bite size appetizers.

title: peanut butter bloomers
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, brown sugar and peanut butter.
Add egg and vanilla,
Add dry ingredients. Mix well.
Add milk.
Make into balls and put on a cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° 8 to 10 minutes.
Put a Hershey Kiss in center of cookie while it is still hot.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage; crumble; drain. Mix sausage and cheese, and sprinkle in pie shell. Combine remaining ingredients, and add to eggs. Pour into shell, and bake at 375 degrees for 40 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape "juicy" mixture. Place in bread pans.
(Can fall apart if not dry enough, too.) Press 2 green pepper rings or bacon strips atop meat loaf(s).

title: mike's special
directions: Cook ground beef, garlic and onions together in large skillet until meat is brown and onions are clear.
Drain grease.
Add spinach, mushrooms and wine (if desired).
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer until well blended, about 4 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove cover.
Add eggs and cook until eggs are scrambled hard, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat, sprinkle Parmesan cheese to taste.
Serve immediately with crusty French bread.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Pour in pan 1/2 inch thick. Bake at 350°.

title: german fruit cake
directions: Mix
dry
ingredients.
Mix
butter and eggs.
Mix soda with buttermilk.
Mix
all together.
Add preserves.
Fold in pecans. Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for
1/2 hours or until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes a large cake.

title: mexican roast
directions: Pour flour onto roast and season.
Brown quickly on both sides in 3 tablespoons of very hot fat.
Add tomatoes, onion, chili sauce and 3 cups of hot water.
Cover and bake in a moderate oven until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: mama's sauce cake(50 years or older)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in oblong pan at 325°.

title: gooseberry or rhubarb pie
directions: Beat together eggs, flour and sugar. Pour over gooseberries or rhubarb in a pie shell. Place a top shell over the custard and bake in a 375° oven for 40 minutes until fruit is done and crust is browned. Sugar could be sprinkled over top crust before baking.

title: egg noodles mom made
directions: Sift dry ingredients, make a hole in the center.
Add egg and stir from center with fork until mixed completely.
Roll out on well floured board.
Use plenty of flour because it will be sticky.
Cut in strips for noodles or squares for dumplings.
(I use a pizza cutter, very quick and easy.)
Boil in rich broth until tender.

title: egg salad
directions: Cut up the eggs coarsely.
Add celery, grated onion, seasoning and mayonnaise.
Mix lightly.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add cranberries and nuts.
Beat egg and orange juice.
Stir to mix.
Grease pan and flour.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Butter top while hot.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute hamburg in oleo.
Cut up 1/4 cabbage, coarsely, then combine meat, onion and 1/4 cabbage.
Pour tomato soup (undiluted) over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: holly red punch
directions: Combine spices, sugar and 2 1/2 cups water in saucepan. Simmer 10 minutes.
Strain and cool.
Combine with lemonade, orange juice and cranberry juice.
Just before serving, add ginger ale mixture.
Pour over ice in punch bowl before serving.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except noodles.
Put in casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle noodles on top. Return to oven for 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream margarine, peanut butter and sugars; add egg and vanilla. Beat until creamy.
Stir in dry ingredients until blended.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Press into 1 1/2-inch muffin tin lined with miniature muffin papers.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and press miniature peanut butter cup into hot cookie crust.
Cool and remove from a muffin pan.

title: strawberry mousse
directions: Pour water in blender.
Add gelatin and blend on low until completely dissolved. Add ice cubes and stir by hand until ice is mostly melted.
Add strawberries and the Cool Whip.
Blend on high until smooth.
Pour into jello mold or individual glasses.
Set in refrigerator at least 30 minutes. Garnish with strawberries.

title: creamy artichoke-parmesan dip
directions: Place all ingredients except pita wedges into slow cooker, stir to blend well.
Cover, cook on low 2 hours.
Serve with pita wedges.

title: sausage balls
directions: Knead well together.
Form into small balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in 325° oven about 20 minutes.
Excess balls may be frozen and baked at a later date for 30 minutes.

title: white buns
directions: Boil water, salt and sugar for 5 minutes.
Add shortening until melted, then add milk.
Cool.
Have yeast ready.
Add 4 to 5 cups of flour to cooled liquid before adding yeast.
Add yeast, then more flour.
Beat eggs, one at a time.
Stir between adding each egg and then add the rest of the flour until you get a dough that isn't sticky to the touch.
Let stand and raise.
Knead and when it is raised, put in pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
This dough can be used for rolls also.
If you wish, you can make this about 4 p.m. and put in pans in the evening and let stand, covered, until morning to bake.
Makes about 8 dozen buns.

title: fresh beef brisket
directions: Partially freeze meat.
Place in heavy casserole lined with foil so you can wrap tight.
Put lots of sliced onions, lots of salt and pepper, 1 teaspoon garlic powder, 2 tablespoons butter and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Squeeze lemon juice and sherry over meat. Fold over foil and cook at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Check to see if meat is tender at 2 1/2 hours.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Slice dinner rolls lengthwise.
Make sauce with Worcestershire sauce, grated onions, poppy seed and softened butter and spread on rolls.
Layer with cheese and ham.
Put top back on rolls.
Put in pack.
Cover with tinfoil and chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (with foil).

title: zareens' saffron rice
directions: Pour rice in colander and set in pot of cold water.
Change water 4 or 5 times; wash rice until water remains clear.
Drain rice.
Place saffron in bowl with 3 tablespoons boiling water and soak for 10 minutes.
In 3 to 4-quart pot, heat oil to medium.
Add cinnamon and cloves, then add onions.
Fry until onions are soft and brown.
Add rice in and stir until rice browns.
Add 4 cups of water (boiling), brown sugar, salt and cardamon seeds and bring to boil over high heat.
Add saffron and reduce heat.
Cover and heat for 25 minutes.
Fluff rice with fork and serve at once.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: marshmallow icing for lane cake
directions: Cook granulated sugar, salt and water to a temperature of 238° or until syrup spins a thread.
Pour slowly over beaten egg whites, beating mixture as you do.
While icing is still hot, fold in marshmallows, which have been cut in pieces.
Beat until of a consistency to spread.
Cover cake.
Use your favorite white cake recipe.
Three layers are needed.

title: brisket of beef in horseradish sauce
directions: Put meat in heavy kettle.
Add onions, carrots, celery, bay leaves and salt and pepper.
Just about cover the meat with boiling water.
Cover kettle and simmer for 3 to 4 hours.
Remove, slice and serve in Horseradish Sauce (recipe follows).
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Put flour in bowl.
Make well in center of it with hand.
Add water and egg. Mix with hand until it forms a workable ball.
Place on heavily floured rolling pin until thin.
Roll as you would a jelly roll.

title: coleslaw
directions: Place coleslaw mix in large bowl.
In small bowl, whisk remaining ingredients.
Pour over coleslaw; toss.
Cover and chill.

title: cauliflower au gratin
directions: Place cauliflower in 1 1/2-quart glass dish.
Add water. Cover and microwave on High 8 to 9 minutes.
Combine mayo, onion and mustard.
Spoon sauce on top of cauliflower and sprinkle with cheese.
Put in microwave on Roast setting for 2 minutes.
Let stand 2 minutes before serving.

title: chicken with wine
directions: Take skin off chicken.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Put in celery, onion and wine.
Cook at 400° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn chicken half way.

title: cauliflower and broccoli toss
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli into bite size pieces.
Add chopped green onions.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over veggies. Cover and chill overnight. Add cheese if desired.
Serve 6 to 8.

title: old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to mixture alternating with milk.
Stir in vanilla.
Bake in a tube pan or long loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
(It is very important to start cake in a cold oven.)
Cool 10 minutes, then turn out on cake plate.

title: summer peach cobbler
directions: Put peaches in a casserole that's either greased or sprayed with Pam.
Mix flour, sugar and egg together; put over peaches. Pour melted oleo over top of all.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done and let cool.
Mix soups and sour cream. Cut chicken into pieces.
Mix together.
Put in casserole dish, then sprinkle cheese on top.
Sprinkle Ritz crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian lemonade
directions: Dilute lemonade with 3/4 cup water; stir in apricot nectar and pineapple juice.
Pour fruit juice mixture over ice cubes in 6 glasses.
Fill glasses with ginger ale; garnish with lemon slices.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine first 3 items and cream them with mixer.
Mix flour, salt and soda in sifter.
Add to the creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and sour milk.
Mash bananas with mixer and add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Grease two loaf pans (9-inch).
Divide mixture.
Bake at 350°
about 45 to 50 minutes.
Test with toothpick.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour and milk alternately.
When well mixed, add bananas, vanilla, soda and nuts.
Bake in a Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Put first 6 ingredients in large bowl.
Make hole in center, put remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Add 1 cup pecans.
Put into 3 pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions and put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake.
After cake is done, punch holes in it and pour half of the caramel over it.
Let cake completely cool and then crumble 6 candy bars over it.
Next pour remaining caramel. Then top with the Cool Whip.
Crumble remaining candy bars over top.

title: simply elegant beef tips
directions: In a
large
skillet,
brown
meat in oil on high heat. Add onions.
Saute until tender and crisp.
Blend soup, sherry and liquid
from
mushrooms
and
garlic salt. Pour over meat. Add mushrooms.	Reduce	heat and cover; then simmer for 1 hour or until meat	is
tender
(or cover and bake at 350°).
Serve over fluffy rice or mashed potatoes.

title: cinnamon blintzes
directions: Trim crusts from bread and roll thin.
Cream together cream cheese, egg yolk and sugar.
Spread on bread slices.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Dip folded bread into butter, then in sugar mixture.
Place on cookie sheet or 9 x 13-inch and freeze.
(If keeping for a long time, put them in a Ziploc bag after they are frozen.)

title: oreo delight
directions: Save 5 Oreo cookies, crush the rest.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt margarine and pour over cookies, press into pan.
Beat milk, cream cheese and pudding mix until smooth.
Pour over cookies.
Top with Cool Whip and crush 5 cookies.
Sprinkle over Cool Whip.
Keep chilled.

title: german apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil until foamy.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat 5 minutes.
Add flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Ice with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: b b q abalone
directions: 1. Clean abalone and tenderize with hammer wrapped in T-shirt. 2. Put meat in shell without shirt. 3. Add 1/2 c. dressing or wine. 4. Wrap in foil and cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Drain peaches; to the syrup, add sugar, vinegar, salt and spices.
Heat to boiling and simmer until sugar is dissolved. Pour this spiced syrup over peaches.
Let stand overnight.
Store in covered jar in refrigerator.

title: chicken loaf
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion and sausage until done.
In another pan, cook Stove Top stuffing and vegetable mix well.
Set aside. Mix chicken, sausage, onion, egg and stuffing.
Form a loaf.
Mix 1/4 cup catsup with 2 tablespoons of water and mix.
Pour over loaf.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: priscilla's chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add beaten egg and melted chocolate and mix well.
Sift the dry ingredients together and add alternately with the milk.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sausage balls in cranberry sauce
directions: Combine sausage, eggs, bread crumbs, salt and poultry seasoning.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake in a 350°
oven for 30 minutes.
Combine cranberry sauce and mustard in medium saucepan and heat until melted.
Add sausage balls.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Yields 24 to 30.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together.
Add water and cook over medium heat until thick.
Add lemon juice, then Jell-O.
Pour over strawberries which have been sliced and arranged in baked pie shell.
Chill.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain excess fat.
Add ingredients and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer 45 minutes.

title: glorified rice
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill very thoroughly before serving.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix jello in 1 cup boiling water and let set until it begins to congeal, then add all ingredients.
Set in refrigerator until jelled, but not firm.
Whip in 1 cup cottage cheese plus 1/2 cup mayonnaise. Return to refrigerator until set.

title: blackie's southern cornbread
directions: Stir all ingredients together; mix well.
Have dressing soft, like thick soup, must be soupy or it will dry out in baking process.

title: granny black's persimmon pudding
directions: Place persimmons in sieve to separate seeds from pulp.
Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake in pie plate or sheet pan at 375° until firm.
Do not jiggle in center.

title: chicken bake
directions: Stew chicken until tender (cut up).
Save broth (1 1/2 quarts).
Cook macaroni in broth. Add cheese while hot.
Add onion and celery soup and the rest of the ingredients.
Stir well. Put in buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes a lot.

title: almond cookies
directions: Grease cookie sheets.
Melt butter and brown sugar; bring to a boil.
Stir in almonds.
Spread on graham crackers one at a time. Bake in 350° oven about 8 minutes.
Do not let graham crackers burn.
Remove from cookie sheets while still hot; cool on open grids.
Store in fridge or freezer.

title: black banana cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° until tested done.
This makes a large cake.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
(Can use coconut instead of pecans.)

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together.
Use 2 teaspoons tea per cup hot water.

title: deviled egg dip
directions: In bowl, stir cream cheese and mustard until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Serve with fresh vegetable dippers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: "alfajores"(cookies)
directions: Mix together cornstarch, flour, soda and baking powder.
Blend butter and sugar together.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add lemon peel and vanilla.
Mix, blend.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Roll out 1/4 of dough and cut in 1 1/2-inch rounds.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Place on cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on racks.
When cool, make sandwich with jelly, etc. as filling.
Roll edges in very finely shredded coconut.
Store in airtight containers.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll out crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 19 minutes.
Mix up next four ingredients.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix up rest of ingredients and pour over mixture on crust. Cut in little pieces with a pizza cutter.
Keep refrigerated.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain and rinse in cold water.
Place in a large bowl; add tomatoes, zucchini, cucumber and peppers.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over salad and toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for at least two hours.
Serves 16 - 20.

title: sweet-sour meatballs
directions: Season ground chuck and shape into miniature meatballs, using a heaping tablespoonful for each.

title: easy strawberry jello salad
directions: Combine jello and water; dissolve.
Stir in sour cream until blended.
May use rotary beater.
Add strawberries.
Pour into serving dish and chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: amish pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix everything together except cheese.
Put 1/2 of mixture in baking dish. Layer 1 cup of cheese over this and repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: janice's praline pumpkin pie
directions: Line pie pan with pastry.
Mix pecans, soft butter and 1/3 cup brown sugar together.
Press the pecan mixture firmly into the bottom of pie shell.
Bake in 425° oven for 10 minutes.
While baking, combine eggs, pumpkin, brown sugar and spices.
Last, add milk.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix the oil, cocoa and sugar together.
Add eggs, 1 at a time; add rest of ingredients.
Make in a ball and roll in powdered sugar.
Put in refrigerator for 3 hours.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic.
Drain good.
Add spices to taste.
Add tomato paste and sauce.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat to let simmer about 20 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain. Layer in a greased casserole dish the sauce, noodles, Mozzarella cheese, sauce, Cheddar cheese, Parmesan cheese and finish with noodles.
Cover with foil and bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Add 1 teaspoon each of garlic salt, cumin, chili powder, salt and pepper again.
Cook until carrots are done.
Serve with grated cheese, sour cream, salsa and chips.

title: angel cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together; add egg and vanilla and blend thoroughly. Combine dry ingredients and add to butter mixture. Using spoon, scoop small balls of dough and dip tops into sugar before placing on baking sheets. Will flatten by itself. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: brunch for a bunch
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan well.
Layer the following: potatoes, sausage, cheese, veggies, mixture of milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
May also use chopped ham with 1/2 cup Swiss cheese and 1/2 cup Monterey Jack hot cheese.

title: apricot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: low-fat snickers pie
directions: Mix and freeze in pie plate.

title: whole glazed beets
directions: In a saucepan, combine orange marmalade, orange juice, butter and pineapple.
Bring this to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add beets.
Simmer for 5 minutes, stirring until beets are coated with glaze.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Grease and flour angel food cake pan.
Beat together shortening and sugar in large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed.
Add salt, vanilla, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Set aside.
Place flour in large bowl.
Add cornstarch.
Set aside.

title: chicken o'brien
directions: Slice onion and celery, Pour small amount of oil in skillet and heat.
Add chicken, celery and onion.
Stir-fry.
Put 2 cans of soup in bowl.
Add 1 can of water, 2 tablespoons of cooking wine and 1 teaspoon of garlic powder.
Mix well.
Pour over chicken. Reduce heat.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add frozen Japanese vegetables and sliced mushrooms.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: blueberry stuff
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Refrigerate overnight.
Enjoy.

title: chocolate buttermilk cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add soda to flour and alternate flour and buttermilk.
Melt chocolate in hot water and add to batter. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into cake batter. Bake at 340° about 30 minutes (until just slightly sticky).
Do not overbake.
Bake in 4 layers.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp; remove bacon, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet.
Saute onion in drippings until crisp-tender.
Drain all beans (except pork and beans).
Add beans and all other ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with cooked bacon. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: tostada salad
directions: Combine lettuce, red cabbage, tomatoes, onion and shredded Cheddar.
Toss with salad dressing; add avocado.
Brown hamburger; add kidney beans and simmer 10 minutes.
Cool meat mixture and add to rest of salad.
Add tortilla chips.
Add hot sauce to taste.

title: chocolate peanut dessert
directions: Mix cream cheese, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Add 2 cups Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix pudding with milk. Pour on top of mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with chopped peanuts and grated Hershey bar.

title: texas caviar #1
directions: Mix and refrigerate 6 to 8 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: batter for fish, shrimp, etc.
directions: Mix and blend all ingredients and set in refrigerator for 1 hour before use.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Bring water and margarine to boil and then add flour. Add eggs, one at a time. Spread on a greased jelly roll pan. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Push down lightly with fingers. Cool. Prepare vanilla pudding. Add almond flavoring and cream cheese. Spread on cool crust. Top with Cool Whip. Drizzle with chocolate syrup. Cool and serve.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Mix Pet milk, sugar, egg yolks, margarine or butter and grated coconut (I use the blender to grate the fresh coconut).
Cook until thick.
Cool; ice the 3 or 4 layers of cake.

title: quick peach melba
directions: Place 1 peach half in each of 5 or 6 dessert dishes.
Spoon 1 teaspoon jam into peach cavity.
Pour milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat at lowest speed of mixer until blended, 2 or 3 minutes. Pour at once over peaches.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Chill. Garnish with additional jam or jelly.

title: caramel bars
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, sugar, soda and salt.
Add melted butter and mix thoroughly.
Pat half of crust mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
In a medium saucepan, melt caramels with milk; pour over baked crust. Sprinkle with chips and nuts.
Sprinkle remaining crust mixture over top.
Bake another 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican lunch
directions: Brown sausage, onion and green pepper in large skillet. Add tomatoes, buttermilk, macaroni
and
seasonings.
Stir and cover. Use high heat until steaming.
Turn
to low and simmer 25 minutes. (If using sour cream, add after cooking.)

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Beat eggs and milk; add to well drained zucchini.
Add cheese and seasonings.
Put ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Arrange bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° until consistency of baked custard.

title: steak and rice
directions: Place round steak in large, flat pan.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over steak.
Add rice, which has been cooked nearly done.
Spoon milk over rice.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli-cheddar meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, 2 tablespoons steak sauce, bread crumbs and onion. On waxed paper, pat to 12 x 8-inches; top with 3/4 cup cheese and broccoli.
Roll up from short end; seal.
Place in baking pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with remaining cheese; bake 2 minutes more.
Heat tomatoes and remaining steak sauce; serve with meat loaf.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apple butter(made in crock-pot)
directions: Slow cook for 24 hours on low.
Stir occasionally.
Put toothpicks under lid to let steam out.
Makes 11 1/2 pints.

title: raisin bread
directions: Combine raisins, baking soda, butter and water.
Let stand overnight or at least 3 hours.
Then add sugar, flour, cinnamon, nuts and eggs.
Stir until blended.
Pour batter into 3 (1 pound) size coffee cans that have been well-greased.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Test with toothpick.

title: skillet macaroni and beef
directions: Cook beef in large skillet until it loses its redness.
Drain off liquid and fat.
Cook macaroni per package directions; drain. Add to beef in the large skillet the cooked macaroni, onion, green pepper, salt, tomato sauce, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mom's rhubarb cake
directions: Mix as for cake and pour into a greased 9x13 inch cake pan. Top with 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Bake at 350 degrees for 50 minutes.

title: macaroni-mushroom casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until tender; drain. Cook green pepper and onion in small amount of fat in skillet until tender.
Combine all ingredients except cracker crumbs in large mixing bowl.
Place in 2 buttered medium casseroles or 1 large casserole.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cheese melts and cracker crumbs brown.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: tomato hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients to make a stiff batter.
Roll out hush puppies with your hands to about the size of one finger.
Fry in hot fish grease until golden brown.
You can add hot peppers if you like them spicy.

title: pauline's apple pancakes
directions: Beat egg by hand and add milk.
Fold in flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and shredded apple.
Do not beat.
Will be lumpy.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cube chicken; slice celery and blend all ingredients.
Cover and chill several hours.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: chicken canapitsit
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Dredge chicken in flour, shaking off excess.
In large skillet, heat butter.
Saute chicken breasts 3 minutes per side.
Remove to shallow casserole or gratin dish.

title: easy country rolls
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together in a large bowl.
Dissolve yeast in 1 cup of warm water.
Make a cavity in the center of the flour; put in shortening, egg and yeast mixture.
Blend well.
Add the remaining warm water gradually.
Mix well until a soft dough is formed.
Knead dough for about 5 minutes on a lightly floured board.
Let it stand in a warm place until it doubles its size. Shape dough and place in greased pan.
Let it rise again about 45 minutes.
Bake in a 450° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: overnight green salad
directions: Layer lettuce, peas, bacon and eggs in 11 x 13-inch dish. Blend remaining ingredients in bowl.
Spread over salad, sealing to edge.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken and dressing bake
directions: Toss stuffing mix with 1/2 can of soup, broth and eggs. Spread in an 11 x 7-inch baking dish; top with chicken.
Combine rest of soup and milk; pour over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Cut chicken in small pieces and mix with the remaining ingredients except grated cheese and onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes and then sprinkle with grated cheese and crushed onion rings.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
This fits well in a 9 x 13-inch glass cake pan.

title: baked beans (2)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Fry bacon until crisp; crumble and set aside.
Saute onion in 2 tablespoons of drippings from bacon. Combine all ingredients in casserole and bake about 30 minutes.

title: snickers bars
directions: Bottom Layer:
Melt 1 cup milk chocolate chips, 1/4 cup butterscotch chips and 1/4 cup peanut butter.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set until cool.

title: ice cream sandwiches
directions: In medium size bowl, stir together corn syrup and peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir until well coated.
Press half of mixture evenly in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Place in freezer or coldest part of refrigerator until firm.
Spread softened ice cream over firm mixture.
Return to freezer until ice cream has hardened.
Top with remaining cereal mixture.
Press firmly. Return to freezer.
When firm, cut into sandwich sizes and wrap individually in plastic wrap.
Store in freezer.

title: dried beef log
directions: Blend together the cream cheese, mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce.
Add the black olives, parsley and onion, mixing well. Refrigerate the mixture for 1 hour, then shape into a ball and roll in the dried beef.
Wrap in waxed paper or foil until ready to serve.
Serve with stoned wheat crackers, Triscuits, etc.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: potato cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add the well beaten eggs; mix well, then add the creamed potatoes.
Mix well.
In a separate bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, salt, cocoa, cloves, allspice, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add this sifted mixture and milk a little at a time to the mixture of butter, sugar and eggs.
After this mixture is mixed well, add the nuts and cherries.
Bake for approximately 1 hour at 375°.
Test with toothpick to determine when done.
This cake can be made in a loaf or in layers (I prefer layers).

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake; immediately after taking out of oven, take fork and punch holes in it. Pour Eagle Brand milk over it. Let cool completely. Mix 1 large can of pineapple, drained, with Cool Whip. Spread and sprinkle with coconut.

title: blueberry belle crunch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except oleo.
Cut in oleo until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle over blueberries.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: bread sticks
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In square 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan, melt butter in oven.
Remove pan from oven.
Measure flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Add milk; stir just until dough forms, about 30 strokes.
Turn dough onto well floured board.
Roll dough around to coat with flour.
Knead lightly about 10 times.
Roll into 8-inch square.
With floured knife, cut dough in half, then cut each half into nine 4-inch strips.
Dip each strip into melted butter, coating both sides.
Arrange strips close together in 2 rows in pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: marshmallow chip crunchies
directions: Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt margarine and marshmallows for 3 minutes in large bowl in microwave.
Add 1/2 of the chocolate chips and stir until smooth.
Stir in the Rice Krispies. Press into pan.
Top with remaining chocolate chips.
Cut into 24 squares when cool.

title: old fashioned jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs until foamy:
Gradually add sugar and continue beating until mixture is thick.
Gradually fold in dry ingredients (which have been mixed together).
Add vanilla.
Line a 15 X 10 X 1 inch jello roll pan with waxed paper.
Grease wax paper and sides of pan.
Pour batter into pan and bake in hot oven at 400° for 13 minutes.
Turn cake out on cloth which has been sprinkled with powered sugar.
Remove paper, roll up cake in cloth.
Cool.

title: cinnamon rolls (low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 13 pan lightly with vegetable cooking spray.
Blend 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl and set aside.
Blend 2 tablespoons sugar, 2 tablespoons margarine, milk, and low-fat biscuit mix in a medium bowl. Add a little milk if needed for dough consistency.
Turn dough onto a surface sprinkled with additional mix.
Roll into a 14 x 16 inch rectangle.
Spread yogurt over dough.
Sprinkle sugar/cinnamon mixture over top.
Sprinkle nuts or raisins across dough.
Roll dough from long side, gently.
Cut into 1 inch slices and place in prepared pan, cut side up.
Bake 25-28 minutes or until golden brown.
Blend powdered sugar, vanilla, and 3 tablespoons water.
Drizzle over cinnamon rolls.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Add flour.
Mix.
Make into small round balls.
Place on cookie sheet 3 inches apart.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake until set, but not brown.

title: microwave jam strawberry
directions: Clean and remove hulls from strawberries; crush them to make 2 cups.
Add lemon juice, sugar and butter or margarine.
Prepare fruit and flavorings and place in a 2-quart glass measure or a 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole.
Add sugar and butter; stir thoroughly. Cover with waxed paper; microwave on High for about 6 minutes or until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove waxed paper and stir fruit. Microwave, uncovered, on High 2 minutes; test by dripping fruit mixture from side of metal spoon, they should be thick.
If not thick enough, reheat to boiling, then microwave, uncovered, for 2 more minutes on High; test consistency again.
Pour into sterilized jars; fill about 2/3 full.
Cool and cover with lid.
Can refrigerate or freeze.
Makes 2 cups.

title: pasta fasoola
directions: Saute celery and onion in oil until soft.
Mash tomatoes. Cook macaroni.
Add all ingredients to onion mixture.
Simmer 20 minutes or so.
Serve with a little grated cheese.

title: tex-mex tortilla casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat 2 (13 x 9-inch) baking dishes with cooking spray.
In large pot or Dutch oven, cook first 7 ingredients, stirring often until beef is browned 10 minutes. Drain, if necessary.
Line bottom of each baking dish with 6 tortillas.	Divide beef mixture between dishes.
Top each with 1 can beans, then sprinkle with 3/4 cup cheese.
Top with remaining tortillas.	Spread 2 jars salsa over each casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cover with foil; bake 45 minutes.
Remove foil; bake 10 to 15 minutes until cheese is golden.
To freeze, cool completely.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Spread pan with a layer of rice (Uncle Ben's).
Place a layer of sliced onions, strips
of
green pepper and slices of tomato on top.
Salt and
pepper
pork chops and place on top. Soak entire casserole with
diluted
tomato
sauce
and
baste every 15 minutes.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: company chicken salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Toss with salad dressing or mayonnaise.
Just before serving, stir in shoestring potatoes (optional).

title: cream of eggplant soup with curry
directions: Pierce the eggplant with a fork several times.
On a baking sheet, cook in a 425° oven for 40 minutes.
Allow to cool slightly.
Scrape as much pulp from the skin as possible and then discard skin.

title: apricot crunch bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Stir in oats and sugar.
Cut in butter and stir until mixed and crumbly.
Pack 2/3 of pastry into bottom of 7 x 11-inch pan. Combine jam and peel; spread over pastry.
Sprinkle remaining pastry evenly over top.
Bake 25 minutes and cool in pan.
Cut in squares.

title: oktoberfest pockets
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Saute sausage and onion in large skillet about 10 minutes.
Stir in sauerkraut, cheese, mustard and caraway seed.
Unroll dough; cut into halves lengthwise and crosswise. Press each piece into a 6-inch square.
Place 1/4 of the sausage filling in a triangle over half of each square, leaving 1/2-inch edge.
Moisten edges with water.
Carefully fold dough over filling, pressing edges together.
Place on greased baking sheet. Pierce top with knife.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 pockets.

title: saucy louisiana chicken
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Add green pepper and chicken.
Cook until peppers are tender-crisp and chicken is cooked.

title: cha-soh juhn(korean vegetable pancakes)
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients in medium bowl.
Add vegetables. Drop mixture by heaping tablespoonfuls onto hot, well-oiled skillet.
Turn when edges begin to brown.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring to boil sugar, syrup and water.
Stir in peanuts and cook until hard crack stage is reached on candy thermometer.
Add baking soda and pour into well-buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool and break into small pieces.

title: paradise pumpkin-cheese pie
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing until well blended.
Add egg; mix well.
Pour onto bottom of pastry shell.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Carefully pour over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes (or until done).
Cool; brush with maple syrup.

title: macaroons
directions: Mix sugar and corn flakes.
Add butter.
Beat in egg whites and coconut.
Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 325°. Watch carefully.

title: peanut butter candy recipe
directions: Mix together by hand powdered sugar, graham cracker crumbs and peanut butter in bowl.
Add enough melted margarine to mix thoroughly.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour; set aside.
Combine eggs and next 3 ingredients; add sugar mixture, stirring well.
Stir in 2/3 cup coconut; pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Bake an additional 30 minutes or until set. Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add pretzels and sugar; press in bottom of dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool well.
Cream 1/2 cup sugar and cream cheese with mixer.
Add Cool Whip and 2 tablespoons milk.
Spread over cool pretzel crust.
Mix gelatin, boiling water and strawberries; let set until beginning to gel.
Pour over cheese mixture and refrigerate.

title: brunswick stew
directions: This recipe calls for fresh vegetables, but frozen or canned will suffice.
Combine first 4 ingredients and simmer in pot until chicken is tender.
Bone meat, cool and remove fat from broth and return all to kettle along with the veggies and seasoning until tender.
Except the corn, put it in the last 10 minutes.

title: meatball casserole
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine 2 tablespoons tomato sauce with beef, egg, bread crumbs, onion and salt.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on a jelly roll pan and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until browned.
Meanwhile, in a skillet, combine remaining tomato sauce with vegetables and seasonings.
Cover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes or until heated through.
Stir in meatballs and set aside.
Place hash browns in greased 11 x 7 x 20-inch baking dish.
Brush with butter and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and top with meatball mixture.
Arrange cheese strips in a lattice pattern on top; return to oven for 20 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Stir in flour and the sugar. Add 1/2 cup milk at a time, stirring. Add cocoa after 1/2 milk. Add egg yolks, salt and vanilla. Stir until thick. Pour into cooked pie shell. Beat egg whites to a stiff peak. Place on top of pie and bake until golden brown.

title: almond cream-puff ring
directions: About 3 hours before serving:
In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat water, butter or margarine and salt until butter melts and mixture boils.
Remove saucepan from heat.
With wooden spoon, vigorously stir in flour all at once until mixture forms a ball and leaves side of saucepan.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: cole slaw topping
directions: Bring to boil.
Pour over cole slaw; let cool.

title: chili
directions: Crumble ground beef in large skillet.
Add onions and garlic. Cook until meat is brown, stirring frequently.
Add all ingredients.
Bring to rolling boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
If too thick, may add 1 cup water.

title: hot dried beef spread
directions: Mix well.
Sprinkle pecans
over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, uncovered.
Serve with crackers.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add one egg yolk at a time and beat well.
Add sour cream and soda; beat.
Add flour, beat and add beaten egg whites.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 45 minutes in 300° oven.
Turn out immediately.
Do not open oven door while cake is baking.

title: black bean dip
directions: In blender or food processor, combine beans, 1 tablespoon chopped onion, vinegar, orange juice and garlic.
Blend until smooth.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle remaining onion on top.
Serve with assorted fresh raw vegetables or pita bread, cut into triangles and toasted in a 325° oven until crispy.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix refried beans and 1/4 of the jar of picante sauce.
Layer in 9 x 12-inch dish.
Grate 1/2 of cheese and layer over beans.
Mix 3/4 cup picante sauce, ground beef and tomatoes*, cumin and salt together.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Layer over cheese and beans.
Top with remaining grated cheese.
Cook in oven for 20 minutes.
Serve with side order of tortilla chips.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add all other ingredients and pour into uncooked pie crust.
Bake 5 minutes in 475° oven.
Reduce heat to 300° and cook 30 minutes or until firm.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, cocoa and milk in 2-quart saucepan. Simmer on medium heat until mixture comes to boil, stirring occasionally.
When rolling boil is reached, set timer for exactly 7 minutes; stir for entire 7 minute boil.
