Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter, vanilla and marshmallows quickly.
Add oatmeal, stirring constantly.
Spoon out quickly on waxed paper. Cookies will set up within 10 to 15 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: Heat cider to boiling.
Add orange juice, lemon juice and cinnamon sticks.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer for 15 minutes. Serve in mugs.
Particularly enjoyable indoors by a fireplace during a January blizzard, but it even tastes great in summer.

title: green rice
directions: Cook rice.
Add milk, egg, Cheddar cheese and green pepper. Mince parsley and garlic.
Mix thoroughly; put in baking dish. Pour salad oil all over and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix the sugar, syrup, margarine and raw peanuts together. Boil 17 minutes until brown.
Add the baking soda, stir and pour it on to a greased cookie sheet fast.
Cool.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook the hamburger until brown. Then dump the can of chili in with it. Put as much as you want of the green hot sauce, too. Cook until hot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bake breasts approximately 45 minutes.
Drain off any liquid. Combine sour cream and soup together.
Spread over breasts. Sprinkle with Hi-Ho cracker crumbs.
Pour melted butter over crackers.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 20 minutes.

title: easy-do-fudge
directions: Combine butter, sugar and milk in a large, heavy pan.
Over low heat, bring to full boil; stir.
Boil for 5 minutes; stir. Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir; make sure all is mixed well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool completely.
Makes 3 pounds fudge.

title: sausage-cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Place cheese in glass bowl.
Microwave on Medium for 1 minute and 30 seconds or until cheese melts.
Stir in sausage.
Microwave for 30 seconds or until heated.
Serve with butter flavored crackers or corn chips.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Add all ingredients together in casserole, except crackers and butter, or put in layers.
Crumble crackers in butter and mix together.
Make enough to spread over top of casserole.
Bake at 325° until cheese is melted, about 5 to 8 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Make layer of noodles.
Sprinkle with cheese, onion, corned beef and soup mixed with milk.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Cover with crushed potato chips or bread crumbs.
Dot with butter and cover with tinfoil.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.

title: plano chili
directions: Brown ground beef in a
large skillet or saucepan.
Drain off excess fat.
Add tomato sauce, whole tomatoes, kidney beans and water.
Stir in all ingredients except masa flour.
Cook on low heat approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add masa flour for thickening, then continue to cook another 30 minutes.

title: chocolate marshmallow cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cocoa.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour, nuts and vanilla; mix well.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately put the marshmallows on hot cake.

title: hot water corn bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well, then pour boiling water over and mix.
Form into balls about the size of an egg, then press into patties and fry until done.

title: potatoes basquaise
directions: Peel potatoes; rinse.
Place in 3-quart saucepan.
Cover with water.
Add 1 teaspoon salt.
Bring water to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer for 20 minutes until almost tender.
Drain. Cut in 1/8-inch slices.

title: homemade biscuit mix
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Store in air-tight container for up to six weeks at room temperature or six months in freezer.
Use for apple cobbler biscuits.
This makes about 2 1/4 cups.

title: left-over mashed potato patties
directions: Mix egg with potatoes.
Blend in onion; add flour and mix well.
Spoon out mixture in a pan of flour and roll to coat both sides.
Drop in skillet of hot oil and fry on both sides until brown.
Any leftover meat pieces can be added to the mixture before browning.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put sugar and milk in a saucepan; bring to a boil and cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat, add butter, vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until mixture begins to thicken.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool.
Either creamy or chunk style peanut butter may be used.

title: big mama's cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar; let stand 2 hours or more. Whip the cream and combine marshmallows with cream.
Let stand 2 hours or more.
Combine these ingredients and add pineapple and nuts.
Let stand overnight.
(It's better, but not a must!)

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: butter beans and ham bits
directions: Slice small bits of ham from shank end.
Cook ham bits in a large saucepan in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Add beans and pepper.
Return to boiling; reduce heat.
Cook according to package directions.
Add sugar; cook 1 minute more.
Drain well. Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: copper penny salad(marinated carrots)
directions: Mix onion, green pepper, sugar, soup, vinegar, oil and seasonings.
Pour over carrots and let stand overnight.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Blend well the ice cream, milk and Cool Whip.
Parch pecans at 250° for 30 minutes in 3 tablespoons margarine.
Stir often and stir after cooked.
Stir in nut pieces.
Crumble Oreos.
Begin with Oreos, then ice cream, layering.
Repeat layers.
Place in freezer.

title: kolaches
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm milk. Add sugar and flour. Set aside in a large bowl. Mix all other ingredients together. Add to yeast and mix well. Let rise until double in size. Spoon a little at a time, roll out and make indention in middle and add fruit and topping. Let rise again. Bake at 350° until golden brown. Pat with butter.

title: break away bread
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the warm water.
In a large bowl put the boiling water and Crisco. Add the sugar, flour, eggs and salt. Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Dip in butter.
Put in layers in Bundt pan, then overlay in seams.
Let rise 2 hours.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.
Makes 2 pans.

title: cauliflower sandwich filling
directions: Mash the cauliflower.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Serve as a sandwich filling on whole grain toast with sliced tomato as a stuffing for pita pockets with sprouts, lettuce and chopped tomato or as a stuffing for tomatoes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half.
Drop yolk in mixing bowl with added ingredients.
Mix with blender until creamy.
Garnish with paprika.

title: barbara nicklaus' marinated flank steak
directions: Combine liquid ingredients and then stir in seasonings and green onions.
Pour over flank steak in glass bowl. Marinate, refrigerated, overnight.
Remove steak from marinade, reserving marinade.
Grill no more than 5 minutes per side.
Meanwhile, heat marinade and bring to a boil and boil 2 minutes.
Cut steak in thin diagonal slices and serve with marinade.

title: spanish meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef, garlic salt, meat tenderizer and egg.
Form into balls and fry in oil until golden brown.
When done, fry onions and pepper in same oil.
When they are done, drain the oil off and add tomato sauce and soforito.
Then add meat balls, corn and green beans.
Let simmer for 5 minutes.

title: cornish game hens with wild rice stuffing
directions: Prepare rice mix (serving four) as directed on package, using bouillon cubes in water.
Saute chopped celery and hen's livers in butter.
Add to rice mixture along with mushrooms and 1/2 of mushroom juice.
Clean hens and salt inside and outside.
Stuff with rice and place on backs in pan.
Baste with butter and bake approximately 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chocolate boiled cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Bring to rolling boil. Boil exactly 1 1/2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Press into a well-greased square pan or spoon on cookie sheet; cool and cut into squares.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Beat cream cheese with salad dressing, lemon juice and salt until smooth.
Stir in pineapple, walnuts, bananas and 1/2 whipped cream.
Lightly fold in cranberry chunks.
Turn into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch bread pan lined with waxed paper.
Freeze.
Turn out on dish 30 minutes before serving.
Slice 1/2 inch thick.

title: hopscotch
directions: Melt the peanut butter and butterscotch chips over low heat. Remove from heat and add the potato sticks and marshmallows.
Mix, then drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto a plate that has been lined with wax paper.

title: no fail egg custard pie
directions: Mix in blender 3 to 5 minutes. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then 325° for 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot meal
directions: Saute hamburger, onion and pepper in skillet.
Put all in crock-pot.
Cook for 4 hours.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Separate butter into 8 pieces and place in mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: beef and broccoli stir-fry
directions: Slice steak across grain into thin slices.
Add 2 teaspoons oil to wok and cook meat quickly over high heat.
In small bowl, combine beef broth, soy sauce and cornstarch until the cornstarch is dissolved.
Set aside.
Remove meat from wok.
Add remaining oil and cook vegetables, onions and garlic; stir-fry 4 to 5 minutes.
Add steak to vegetables.
Pour cornstarch mixture into steak until sauce thickens.

title: alex and nikki koller's window cleaner
directions: Fill spray bottle. Spray and wipe with gift box tissue or squeegee.

title: orange jello salad
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve jello in 2 1/2 cups boiling water. Add thawed orange juice and undrained pineapple.
Chill until it begins to gel, then fold in all but a few mandarin orange segments.
Chill until firm.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Mix with spaghetti, soup and tomato juice.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Place pork chops in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Top with mushrooms.
Next top with chopped onion.
Next cover top with Bull's Eye barbecue sauce.
Bake for 2 hours.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix 1 cup of baking mix and the water until soft dough forms; beat 20 strokes.
Gently smooth dough into ball on floured board.
Knead 5 times.
Roll dough 2 inches larger than your pie plate.
Ease into plate.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion until brown.
Drain.
Stir in salt, pepper, 2 tablespoons of baking mix and Worcestershire sauce.
Spoon into pie crust.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake until set, about 30 minutes.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; mix ingredients, including water, in medium bowl.
Let rise 30 to 45 minutes, then spread onto two greased pizza pans or large cookie sheet.
Add sauce, Mozzarella cheese and favorite toppings.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: kathleen's rolls
directions: Mix together lukewarm water and yeast.
Mix boiling water and Crisco and cool until lukewarm.
When cool, mix in sugar, salt and yeast.
Add flour.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; let boil for 3 minutes.
Add vanilla.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Blend all ingredients except pecans.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons sugar mixture (1 tablespoon sugar mixed with 1 teaspoon cinnamon) over top.
Add rest of batter. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let cool in pan.
Remove and drizzle over the top, 1 cup powdered sugar and 2 tablespoons milk or lemon juice (optional).

title: christmas cake #1
directions: Cream butter, sugar and browning until soft and fluffy.
Sieve all dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs, sherry, brandy or milk together.
Add egg mixture to creamed butter and sugar.
Add fruits.
Fruits should be lightly floured, if sticky.
Add flour and fold in.
Do not overbeat when mixing.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or steam for 2 hours.
Yields a 9-inch round or 8-inch square cake.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
and bake, uncovered, at 350° for
1 hour.
(When in a hurry, I microwave 15 to 20 minutes, covered, and stirring after 5 minutes.)

title: corn bread salad
directions: Bake corn bread according to directions on package.
Cool and crumble in large salad bowl.
Add all other ingredients. Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate-oatmeal bars
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Reserve 1/2 cup of mixture for later.
Press mixture into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: red hot jello salad
directions: Boil red hots and water together until red hots are dissolved. Take off fire.
Add jello; let set until partially set.
Add pineapple.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into a square or oblong pan; set in refrigerator.
Keep other 1/2 in pan.
Mix in bowl the cream cheese and milk; spread over congealed mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Pour the remaining jello mixture over cream cheese.
Let set.
Good holiday salad!

title: salmon and potato scallop
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a 2-quart baking dish, layer half of each of the following:
spinach, potatoes, seasoning from potato mix and dry salad dressing mix.
Pour on 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup milk.
Top with all of salmon, distributing evenly. Repeat layers with remaining ingredients in same order, ending with milk.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake 30 to 35 minutes, or until hot and bubbling.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix together with Miracle French or Western dressing.
Crush 1 large package Doritos or corn chips.
Wait until ready to serve before putting in.
Or instead, serve on tortilla shells.

title: cookies rough
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add oatmeal, Grape-Nuts flakes, raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Mix and drop on cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: crabbies
directions: Let margarine and cheese soften to room temperature.
Mix together with mayonnaise and spices.
Add crab meat.
Spread on split English muffins.
Freeze at least an hour or leave in freezer until needed.
Cut in quarters and broil until bubbly crisp, about 10 minutes.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breasts in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top each with a cheese slice.
Combine soup and wine and spoon mixture over cheese.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle margarine over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: chocolate fizz
directions: Combine all ingredients in covered shaker and shake until well blended.
Pour into tall glass. Serve with or without ice.

title: wacky cake
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl and beat with electric mixer until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Can dust cake pan with baking cocoa.)
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, 25 minutes for double layer.

title: homemade streusel mix
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and then cut in the melted butter. Store in airtight container for quick use in fruit crisps and quick breads and coffee cake toppings.

title: surefire brisket
directions: You will need 1 Reynolds baking bag (according to size of brisket).

title: farrah fawcett's lentil soup
directions: In large saucepot bring beef bones and 2 quarts water to boiling.
Add 1 carrot, 1 rib celery and onion.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 1 hour.
Strain; discard vegetables.
Return broth to saucepot.
Chop remaining carrot and celery; add to broth with lentils.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 40 to 45 minutes until lentils are tender.
Season to taste.

title: hungarian sweet-sour carrots
directions: Wash and scrape carrots.
Cut into 3 x 1/2-inch strips.
Place in saucepan with salted hot water to cover.
Cook until tender. Drain and add butter, vinegar and sugar.
Cook slowly until translucent.
Serve hot garnished with parsley.
Can substitute 1 large bag of frozen baby carrots.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: turkey ragout
directions: In 4 tablespoons butter, saute onion, celery and zucchini until lightly browned and almost tender, 10 to 15 minutes. Combine with turkey in a 3-quart casserole.
In same skillet, brown mushrooms.
Add more butter, if necessary.
Add to casserole. Brown carrots. Add.
Stir wine into skillet plus soups and spices. Bring to boil.
Pour over turkey and vegetables.
Bake in 350° oven until vegetables are done.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks one at a time to creamed mixture.
Save whites for beating.
Sift flour, baking powder and cornstarch together.
Combine milk and vanilla and add the dry ingredients and milk alternately to creamed mixture, beating well.
Beat egg whites until they form stiff peaks. Gently fold them into mixture
Pour into buttered and floured cake pans. You may use 3 (8 inch) pans, 2 (9 inch) pans or a 9 x 13 pan (it will be very full).
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes. The oblong pan takes longer to bake, about 40 minutes.

title: pudding cake
directions: Bake a yellow cake mix; let cake cool.
Make Jell-O.
Poke holes in the cake.
Pour Jell-O over cake.
Top with sliced bananas and Cool Whip.

title: chicken for a king
directions: Beat chicken to 1/2-inch thick.
Salt and pepper each breast. Lay a slice of ham and cheese on each breast.
Roll breast and stick a toothpick to hold together.
Dip in egg and bread crumbs. Put in baking dish.
Pour on melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: dotty's frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and mayonnaise.
Add cranberries, pineapple and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Freeze.

title: oatmeal chewies
directions: Combine oats and sugar with the oil.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Add egg, salt, vanilla and coconut and combine well.
The dough will have a crumbled appearance.
Place level tablespoons of the dough on greased cookie sheet and bake in a moderate oven (325°) for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Combine egg, water and vinegar; pour liquid into flour mixture all at once. Blend with a spoon just until flour is all moistened. Yield: 2 double crusts.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix together until creamy.
Put one vanilla wafer on bottom of cupcake paper in muffin pan.
Fill 1/2 full with cheese mixture. Top with maraschino cherry (half).
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely at room temperature.
Remove paper.
If to be kept for a length of time, refrigerate.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: parmesan garlic cheese spread
directions: Beat all ingredients except French bread in medium bowl until creamy.
Pack into 2-cup crock or non-metal container; cover tightly.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours, no longer than 2 weeks. Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before serving.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese if desired.
Serve with toasted French bread.

title: hard candy
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients to 300° hard crack.
Use candy thermometer.
While candy is cooking, prepare cookie sheets with 10x powdered sugar, making several long tunnels.
Have a second pan with 1/2 flavoring ready.
When candy reaches 300°, add 1/2 of mixture to pan.
Add another 1/2 flavoring to cooking pan.
Pour into cookie sheets in long, thin strips.
Work quickly but carefully.
Best to do with 2 people.
Let cool, then break into pieces.
Will need 3 to 4 prepared sheets.
Recipe will make 2 flavors in divided, or add 1 teaspoon for 1 flavor.

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: Place ingredients in a crock or glass jar. Cover with cheesecloth and let stand for 24 hours.
Then cover container and let ferment in refrigerator for 2 weeks. Keep stored in refrigerator in covered jar.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Brown together beef, pork, onion, celery, salt and pepper to taste.
Combine; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Last minute, sprinkle top with chow mein noodles.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Do not beat.
Mix 2 tablespoons cinnamon, 3/4 cups white sugar, 1/2 cups nuts, chopped.
Grease pan well (Bundt pan).
Sprinkle cinnamon mix and cake batter alternately.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 2 hours and remove from pan.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Stir cocoa and baking soda.
Blend in 1/3 cup oil.
Add boiling water.
Stir until thickened.
Stir in sugar, eggs and 1/3 cup of oil.
Stir until smooth.
Add flour, vanilla and salt. Blend completely.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or can use two 8-inch pans (bake for 30 to 35 minutes).

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: *Use whole cut up chicken, deboned.
Season chicken as you boil it.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix milk, sugar, and flour, adding each slowly to prevent lumping.
Melt butter in a deep dish and pour mixture into the butter.
Pour peaches and juice in the middle of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: make ahead eggs
directions: Melt butter in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add bread to cover bottom of pan.
Put ham, cheese, mushrooms and onion on top of bread.
Combine remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour over the ingredients already in the pan.
Cover with foil and let stand overnight in the refrigerator.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oven tender chicken
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 1 hour or until tender. Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; mix sugar (2 2/3 cups) and oil together in mixer.
Add eggs, beating well.
Add vanilla and orange juice; mix well.
Add flour mixture.
Mix well. Place apples in a separate bowl and coat well with cinnamon and 1/3 cup sugar.
In a floured greased tube pan, add 1/3 batter and 1/3 apples; repeat 3 times, ending with apples as last layer. Bake at 350° for 1 3/4 to 2 hours.
Cool in pan on rack one hour. If cake sticks, return to preheated oven for 5 minutes.
Now turn on rack and then place on cake plate, top side up.
Real good. Enjoy.

title: stuffed artichokes
directions: Add olive oil to large heated pan.
Add garlic, shallot, onion, parsley and celery.
Saute until celery is almost tender.
Remove from heat.
Add bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, Romano cheese, pepper and salt.
Mix. Olive oil may be added if too dry.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In large baking dish, combine cup of chicken, soup, broth and vegetables.
Season with salt and pepper.
Combine flour, milk and Crisco; pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, or until crust becomes lightly browned.

title: pudding-wiches
directions: Add milk gradually to peanut butter, blending until smooth. Add pudding mix.
Beat slowly until well blended, about 2 minutes. Spread filling 1-inch thick on half of the crackers.
Top with the rest of the crackers and freeze until firm, about 3 hours.

title: peach crinkle
directions: Place peaches in lightly greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle with lemon rind.
Combine pie crust mix and brown sugar; sprinkle over peaches.
Dot with oleo.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve with ice cream.

title: dirt cake
directions: Put cookies in blender until it looks like dirt; set aside. Cream margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix pudding and milk and add to creamed mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer cookies and creamed mixture, ending with cookies.
Top with gummi worms.

title: sondra's strawberry bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add sugar, eggs, oil, strawberries and pecans.
Mix carefully.
Pour into greased loaf pan or tube pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: sunburst stir-fry
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/3 cup juice for sauce.
Cut chicken into chunks.
In large skillet, stir-fry chicken with garlic and ginger in oil for 2 minutes.
Add pineapple, carrots and bell pepper.
Cover; steam 2 minutes until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Stir in spaghetti.
Combine pineapple juice, soy sauce, cornstarch and sesame oil.
Also add green onions.
Toss until all ingredients are covered.

title: graham cracker pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar, flour, starch and salt.
Add beaten egg yolks, milk, water, vanilla and oleo in large pan.
Cook, stirring until thickened; cool.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Beat egg whites until stiff; beat in 1 tablespoon sugar.
Spread on top of pie and bake at 350° until meringue is slightly brown.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except noodles.
Sprinkle the noodles on top of casserole.
Bake for 90 minutes at 350°.

title: date roll candy
directions: Boil sugar and milk 15 minutes. Add dates, cook until a small amount dropped into cold water forms a soft ball. Remove from heat. Add nuts and vanilla, beat until creamy. Pour on damp cloth, roll. When cool, cut into pieces.

title: chocolate thumbprint cookies
directions: Cream butter, 2/3 cup sugar, egg yolk and milk.
Add vanilla in small mixer bowl.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt; blend into cream mixture.
Chill dough about 1 hour or until firm enough to handle.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
Fill the thumbprint after baked with vanilla filling.

title: pancake mix
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended smooth.
Cook on hot griddle.

title: pineapple pecan loaf
directions: Combine egg, milk, butter, pineapple, nuts and dates.
Sift dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 2 1/2-inch.
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes or until loaf tests done.

title: cynthia's twice baked potatoes
directions: Be brave and use whatever amount needed until it tastes good to you!

title: quick shepherds pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix beef, bread crumbs, onion, egg, water, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Mix well.
In 9-inch pie pan, press meat mixture over bottom and sides.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes until brown.
Reduce heat to 350°.
In bowl, stir together potatoes, cheese, peas and carrots.
Spoon into meat shell.
Bake for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Heat until boiling; reduce heat and simmer 8 minutes.
Pour in jar; add hard-boiled eggs.
Store at room temperature.

title: lemon pie
directions: In double boiler, mix cornstarch and sugar; add boiling water slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook until clear.
Add butter, beaten yolks, lemon juice and rind.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell; cover with meringue and bake 15 minutes at 350° or until browned.

title: strawberry angel food cake
directions: Tear cake into small pieces.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch serving dish.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Stir in strawberries.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon over cake.
Chill until serving time. Yield: 12 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Add dry ingredients to apples.
Add oil, vanilla and eggs.
Do not use a mixer, stir by hand.
Pour batter into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: spiced cranberry ring
directions: Mix Jell-O with salt, cinnamon, cloves and boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce.
When thickened, add orange sections and apples. Pour into 6-cup molds.
Chill.
Serves 12.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: In a large bowl, beat with a spoon the eggs.
Add the sugar (more or less to taste).
Beat until smooth.
Add the 3 cans of milk; stir good.
Add the 1/2 pint of half and half and vanilla. Pour all into the freezer bucket.
Then add 1/2 gallon of milk or whatever it takes to finish filling the bucket.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef in skillet; drain and combine with all other ingredients in Dutch oven and bring to boil.
Then simmer for 1 to 2 hours.
Or you may prepare in crock-pot and let simmer all day long.
Serves 6.

title: microwave "pecan" brittle
directions: Mix together in a 1 1/2-quart casserole the sugar and Karo syrup.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Add and stir well the pecan halves.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes (depending on microwave.
I have 600 watt and use 4 minutes 30 seconds).
Add baking soda and stir gently until light and foamy.
Turn quickly onto very lightly greased cookie sheet or ungreased if Teflon coated.
Cool 20 to 30 minutes.
Break into pieces and store in airtight container.

title: aunt ruth's peanut butter cups(dream bars)
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and peanut butter.
Mix together.
Gradually add powdered sugar.
Mash into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook in a casserole dish in oven at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes.
Take casserole out of oven and place biscuits on top.
Let biscuits almost brown, then take casserole out of oven and top with cheese.
Put casserole back in oven until biscuits are done and cheese is melted real good.

title: potatoes in the round
directions: Mix butter or oleo, water and onion soup. Pour over potatoes and cover with foil. Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: apricot dream jello
directions: Drain fruit.
Save all juice.
Drain apricots and chop until mushy in a food processor.
Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups hot water. Add 1 cup fruit juice.
Let partially set up, then add fruit and marshmallows.
Allow to set up.

title: aunt judy's hot slaw
directions: Grate first 4 ingredients. Mix remainder of ingredients well. Simmer 3 minutes. Mix all together and simmer 30 minutes. Can or freeze whatever you want or keep refrigerated.

title: tallerine
directions: Melt shortening in skillet. Add chopped onion, chopped green pepper and ground beef. Cook until brown, stirring constantly. Season. Add noodles, tomatoes and grated cheese. Steam slowly on low temperature for 30 minutes.

title: carrot sandwich filling
directions: Mix all ingredients and it is best made the night before using, in order for garlic to season well.
Use garlic freely.

title: punch
directions: Mix together in 3-gallon container.
Freezes very well.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, sugars, dressing and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer.
Add flour and baking soda.
Set aside 1 cup of the batter.
Spread remaining batter into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Blend vinegar slowly into mustard in saucepan.
Add water, sugar, salt, celery seeds, mustard seeds and cloves.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Cool.
Place eggs into glass container.
Add sliced onions in container with eggs.
Pour cooled mixture over eggs and onions.
Cover.
Allow to marinate in refrigerate for several days before serving.
Marinade may be used for a second dozen eggs.

title: broccoli rabe ala napilatano
directions: Boil water to cook rabe.
When boils, put in broccoli rabe until tender.
Drain most of water.
Add oil, garlic, capers and diced olives.
Combine mixture.

title: cinnamon-coffee rolls(scandinavia)
directions: Combine flour, salt and 1/4 cup sugar in large bowl.
Cut in margarine with pastry blender until mixture looks like meal. Dissolve yeast in very warm water.
Add to flour mixture with egg yolks and cooled milk.
Beat well; refrigerate overnight.
Roll one-half chilled dough into 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Brush with melted margarine or butter; sprinkle with mixture of 1/4 cup sugar and the cinnamon.
Beginning at wide side, roll as for jelly roll. With sharp knife, cut roll into 1-inch slices.
Place in greased muffin cups.
Roll and cut other half of dough same way.
Cover; let rise about 1 hour in warm place.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes until golden brown.
Remove from pans while hot.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter, sugars and egg.
Add remaining ingredients.
Shape in 1-inch balls.
Bake at 375°.

title: vegetable rice
directions: Combine rice and vegetables in boiling water in saucepan. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Saute onion in butter in skillet.
Stir into rice mixture.
Season to taste.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: banana milkshake
directions: Slice the banana.
Put in a blender.
Add milk.
Mix 30 seconds on low. Add ice cream and blend on medium until smooth.

title: creamy scrambled eggs
directions: Mix eggs and cream cheese.
Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Pour egg mixture into skillet.
Cook.
Just before eggs are thickened throughout, but still moist, stir in bacon. Sprinkle with chives.

title: unusual vegetable casserole
directions: Precook vegetables separately; drain.
Blend soups and milk. Saute cereal in margarine; mix in curry powder.
Combine ingredients; pour into greased casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dijon mustard dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a jar and shake well or blend in a blender.
Refrigerate in a covered container. Will
keep for weeks.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: ham with raisin sauce
directions: Blend cornstarch, mustard and sugar in saucepan.
Gradually, stir in syrup, vinegar and water.
Add raisins and margarine. Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Pour over ham in baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: potato bread
directions: Combine mashed potatoes, milk, butter, honey and salt. Sprinkle yeast into warm water.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Add yeast mixture, eggs and 3 cups flour to potato mixture.
Beat with wooden spoon. Gradually add flour until dough forms.
Knead on floured surface for 10 minutes, adding more flour if necessary. Place dough in greased bowl.
Cover with towel and let rise until double.
Punch down.
Divide dough into thirds.
Shape into loaves.
Place in three 5 x 9-inch bread pans.
Cover and let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown. Brush tops with butter. Cool.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Mix eggs and Ricotta cheese. Set aside. Brown meat. Drain. Add taco seasoning and tomatoes. Cook 10 minutes. Add onions and chili. Layer in 9 x 12 baking pan.

title: chinese red sauce pork
directions: Heat heavy pot (no oil).

When hot, place the green onions on bottom of pot, place pork on top of the green onions, then drizzle sherry wine over the pork until it sizzles for several minutes. Add mashed ginger, soy sauce and water to cover almost 3/4 of the pork.
Bring to rolling boil, then reduce to low heat and simmer, covered, for an hour, turning occasionally to brown pork.
After an hour, add sugar.
Additional soy sauce and water may be required (add as necessary).
When nice and brown (minimum of 2 hours), and when pork is easily pulled with chopsticks, boil pot of water, drop spinach leaves into boiling water for a couple of seconds and drain immediately.

title: candy coconut balls
directions: Mix powdered sugar, coconut, butter, milk and pecans.
Make into balls and chill 1 hour.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin over double boiler.
Keep mixture warm.
Dip each ball by a toothpick in chocolate mixture.
Place on cookie sheet and chill a few minutes.
Makes 100 balls.

title: chunky potato soup
directions: Fry bacon and drain.
Cook and stir onion and celery in 2 tablespoons of reserved bacon fat until tender, 6 minutes.
Stir in potatoes, broth, water, thyme and pepper.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in milk and bacon.
Heat just until
hot.

title: chocolate-coconut candy
directions: Combine ingredients, except coating.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Roll in balls; refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
If mixture is too soft to form balls, refrigerate first, then shape balls.
Dip chilled balls of coconut mixture in coating, turning to coat on all sides.
Keep chocolate over hot water while dipping candy.
With tongs or fork, lift balls out of chocolate on waxed paper.
Place candies in refrigerator to harden.
Store in tightly sealed container.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: potato soup
directions: Chop onion and celery.
Saute in butter until soft.
(Do not brown.)
Add broth and simmer 30 minutes.
Dice potatoes and cook. Add to mixture.
Just before serving, add half and half along with milk.
Do not boil after adding milk.

title: chili caribe con huevos(red chili with eggs)
directions: Fry or scramble eggs in bacon drippings in cast-iron skillet. Pour hot chili sauce over eggs.
Serve immediately with hot tortillas.
Makes 2 servings.

title: italian chop suey
directions: Brown onion, celery and green pepper with meat.
Cook until barely done, adding as little water as possible.
Add remaining ingredients.
Makes a large amount.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream sugar with butter and blend vanilla and 2 tablespoons milk into mixture.
Gradually stir remaining milk into frosting until desired consistency is reached.

title: nutter butter frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Crush cookies in zipper style plastic bag with rolling pin or in food processor. Mix cookie crumbs and butter. Press onto bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Beat cream cheese, oleo and powdered sugar.
Add vanilla. Beat with electric mixer.
Put on cake, then nuts.
Store in refrigerator.

title: hot taco salad
directions: Heat beans in skillet on medium low heat until very hot. Turn off heat and add the rest of the ingredients and stir gently. Sprinkle more grated cheese on top. Serves 3-4.

title: orange refrigerator salad
directions: Sprinkle dry gelatin over cottage cheese; add oranges and pineapple.
Stir gently to mix.
Fold in whipped topping.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.
May spread Cool Whip on top and garnish with orange slices.

title: apple crunch
directions: Cut and place butter tabs in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Peel and cut apples; pour over butter.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add eggs; mix.
Pour over apples.
Top with cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and 1 teaspoon vanilla until fluffy.
Stir in nuts; set aside.
Cut bread into 1 1/2-inch slices; cut a pocket in the top of each slice.
Fill each pocket with about 2 tablespoons of cream cheese mixture.

title: delicate coconut cake (with pineapple)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together the sugar and butter and add the flavoring.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add them alternately with the milk to this mixture.
Add 1/2 of the pineapple (drained).
Fold in the egg whites beaten stiff.
Add the coconut; stir well.
Place in greased and floured pans.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: island style chicken
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve syrup.
In skillet, brown chicken in shortening; pour off fat.
Add reserved syrup, broth, vinegar, sugar, soy sauce and garlic.
Cover and cook over low heat 40 minutes.
Add green pepper and pineapple; cook 5 minutes or until done.
Combine cornstarch and water; gradually stir into sauce. Cook, stirring until thickened.
Serve with cooked parsleyed rice.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Spray large casserole dish with Pam.

Apply layer of torn tortillas, top with seasoned meat (I use 1 package taco seasoning). Spread out whole chilies and open a can of soup and put it on; then throw on your grated white cheese and repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Last 15 minutes, put on yellow grated cheese.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a glass casserole dish. Dab top with butter, then sprinkle top with 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: teriyaki chicken with linguini
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and divide in half.
Pour 1/2 over chicken and marinate for 1 hour.
Grill chicken until no longer pink.
Meanwhile, stir-fry carrots and celery until crisp-tender. Chop chicken into bite size pieces.
Combine chicken, vegetables and linguini and toss with heated remaining sauce.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown ground beef and onions, drain.
Mix in chile peppers. Mix corn meal, milk, eggs, creamed corn and oil.
Pour 1/2 of batter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place meat, onions and pepper on top of batter.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Pour remaining batter in.
Bake 50 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
(Reduce heat to 300° for electric oven and check at 45 minutes.)

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage 10 minutes and drain.
Mix melted margarine with crushed crackers.
Cover bottom of casserole dish with cracker crumbs.
Spread drained cabbage over crumbs.
Add soup mixture, Cheddar cheese, milk and mayonnaise.
Spread over cabbage.
Bake at 350° until "bubbly" and lightly brown, about 20 minutes.
Add light layer of cracker crumb mixture and bake 10 more minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl. Cover and chill for at least 4 hours. If dry, add more dressing before serving.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in four cups salted water.
Drain and place macaroni in baking dish.
Mix together the butter, flour, salt, milk and grated cheese.
Pour over macaroni.
Cover with crumbs. Bake 30 to 40 minutes, or until milk is thickened.

title: graham cracker toffee bars
directions: Line bottom of a cookie sheet with crackers and set aside. Combine butter or margarine, sugar and nuts in a heavy saucepan. Cook on high heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Reduce heat. Cook, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Pour evenly over crackers.
Place chocolate pieces in top of double boiler.
Melt over hot, not boiling, water.
Spread evenly over toffee mixture. Cool. Cut into bars.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen bars.

title: minted chicken soup
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, melt the margarine over moderate heat, then blend in the flour and cook, stirring for 4 minutes. Slowly whisk in the chicken broth, the lemon rind and lemon juice and heat, stirring constantly, just to the boiling point (about 5 minutes).
Adjust the heat so that the mixture simmers and cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes.
Add the chicken and cook 1 minute more over low heat.
Stir in the mint.
Serves 4. Preparation:
approximately 10 minutes.
Cooking time: 16 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place a layer of potatoes in bottom of casserole dish and top with onions. Place a layer of green beans and top with onions. Alternate until all are used. Pour soup over all. Cook at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes, until potatoes are tender. Put cheese on top last 5 minutes of cooking.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and peanut butter.
Add milk, confectioners sugar and whipped topping.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shells and freeze.

title: ham stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes well.

Rub with cooking oil. Bake in a 425° oven for 45 minutes or until tender. Remove from oven. Cut off tops horizontally and remove about 1/4 of the insides of the potatoes. Toss chunk ham with sauerkraut.
Mound meat mixture on top of potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven for 5 to 7 minutes until ham is hot and cheese melts.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain salmon; remove skin and bones.
Flake.
Dilute soup in milk.
Heat soup until well blended.
Add part of soup to salmon and mix well.
Save remaining soup for sauce.
Chill salmon mixture.
Shape croquettes; roll in crumbs.
Dip in slightly beaten egg to which a little water has been added.
Roll again in crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: baked nut pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased baking dish. Bake 25 minutes in 425° oven.

title: quick and fake chilli(easy)
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Chop onion, bell pepper and tomatoes. Add to meat.
Saute about 15 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, cumino and garlic.
Saute another 10 to 15 minutes.
(You may add a small amount of water if needed.)
Add beans and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Warm soup and milk together.
Mix chicken and soup mixture with stuffing.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine oil and eggs; mix until creamy.
Add sugar until smooth.
Combine baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix until blended.
Add pumpkin, then gradually sift in flour.
Then add walnuts, pecans or raisins.
Mix well.
Pour into loaf pans about 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put 2 teaspoons of mixture in cup and add hot water.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package directions.
While fettuccine is cooking, prepare Alfredo mixture.

title: whipped caramel frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk in saucepan over low heat until very thick, stirring constantly.
Cool completely. Cream the sugar and butter until light.
Add vanilla. Add creamed mixture to cooled flour mixture. Continue beating until of consistency of whipped cream.
Spoon flour into dry measuring cup; level or follow directions on bag.

title: linguini with garlic-spinach clam sauce
directions: While linguini is cooking, heat olive oil in a skillet.
Add garlic and saute for about a minute.
Add the spinach and saute over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add clams and their liquid and hot pepper sauce to taste and cook just until heated.
Serve tossed with the linguini, adding freshly grated Parmesan cheese and black pepper to taste.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Thoroughly cream first 6 ingredients together.
Sift flour and soda; chill on lightly floured board.
Roll dough 1/4 inch thick; then cut with cutter.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle lightly with granulated sugar for sparkle.
Trim with red candies and raisins.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes. Cool slightly; remove to rack and cool.
Makes 6 dozen gingerbread men.

title: pickled beets
directions: *This varies with texture, etc.
You need to have extra jars available as needed.

title: fish chowder
directions: Cover fish with water lightly salted. Boil about 15 minutes. Remove fish from water, let cool, then flake fish. Take water fish was boiled in and strain through cheesecloth or fine strainer. Save the water, (you should have about 1 quart of water.) Add vegetables to water and add another quart of water. Cook 20 minutes. Add salt, pepper, poultry seasoning, and garlic powder, and fish. Cook until potatoes are done.

title: orange cottage cheese
directions: Sprinkle jello over cottage cheese.
Fold in.
Add pineapple and oranges; mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all of the ingredients except the flour and mix well. Then blend in the flour and pour into the unbaked pie shells.

title: onion rings shoestring style
directions: Whip eggs and add to milk.
Mix well.
Mix together all dry ingredients and put in paper sack.
Dip onion in egg wash; drain excess wash.
Toss onion in sack.
Remove onion.
Shake off excess.
Deep fry in 4 cups vegetable oil at 375° until light brown.

title: brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, salt, 1/4 cup water and vanilla extract in mixer for 3 minutes.
Gradually add balance of water and mix for 1 minute.
Pour batter into lightly greased 10-inch square baking pan.
(One 8-inch square and one 8 x 4-inch pan can be used instead.)
Sprinkle batter with chopped almonds.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cut bars in pan.
Makes 2 dozen bars (2 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch), 45 calories per brownie.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients until thick.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ensalada valenciana(valenciana salad)
directions: Soak endive or lettuce in water; drain.
Place in salad bowl with olives, garlic, onion, tomato and salt.
Separate egg yolk from white.
Mash yolk.
Add oil and vinegar gradually.
Chop egg white; add tuna to salad.
Salt to taste; pour egg yolk mixture over salad.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: butter roll
directions: Roll biscuit dough on floured surface.
Spread spoon of butter and sugar on dough.
Sprinkle nutmeg, if wanted.
Roll dough and place in baking pan.
Repeat for each piece of dough.
Sprinkle tops with extra sugar that's left and pats of butter.
Pour milk over dough and bake at 325° until lightly brown.

title: lasagne-in-a-bun
directions: Cook ground beef and drain.
Add tomato sauce, soup mix, oregano and basil.
Cook, covered, on low for 5 minutes.
Uncover and cook 15 minutes.
Combine egg, Ricotta cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Cut thin strips off tops of rolls and hollow out bottoms. Fill with layered meat mixture, cheese and more meat mixture and roll top.
Cover each sandwich with foil and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
May be frozen and reheated.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together; heat until red hots are melted. Serve hot.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Tear up tortillas and put in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Top with cooked, cubed chicken (turkey is good too).
Mix together in a large bowl the mushroom and chicken soup, salsa and chili. Top with Cheddar cheese and Jack cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, covered, and then 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 9 x 13 pan.
Place apples in pan. Mix other ingredients and sprinkle over apples.
Bake 45 minutes. Serves 12.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then add remaining ingredients.
Just mix, do not beat.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: parmesan tomatoes
directions: Peel tomatoes; trim out cores and cut each in half crosswise. Gently squeeze out juice and seeds.
Blend crumbs with 3 tablespoons of oil, garlic, anchovy paste and cheese.
Divide crumbs among the tomato halves, mounding firmly in place.
Set tomato halves, with crumb sides up, in a close-fitting baking pan and pour the 2 tablespoons olive oil into pan.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine first 7 ingredients in a bowl; stir well with a whisk.
Stir in cheddar cheese and crabmeat. Spoon crabmeat mixture into a 1 1/2 quart casserole coated with cooking spray, and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serve with crackers or breadsticks.
Yield:
3 2/3 cups.

title: old fashion teacake
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream together margarine, shortening, egg, vanilla and sugar.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Blend until smooth.
Pinch off in bits about the size of a marble and flatten out with palm of hand on well-greased pan.
Bake at 300° for about 10 minutes or until brown.

title: strawberry pie glaze
directions: Cook sugar, water, corn syrup and cornstarch until clear. Stir in strawberry Jell-O and vanilla.
Pour enough glaze to cover bottom of baked pie crust.
Fill with berries.
Add rest of glaze to cover berries.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix corn syrup and sugar in large glass container (preferably one that has a handle).
Microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Remove and stir in peanuts.
Microwave 7 minutes.
Remove and stir in butter and vanilla.
Microwave for 2 minutes.
Remove and add the baking soda.
Be very careful, and work fast; the mixture will become very foamy while you are stirring.
However, mix well and pour onto large cookie sheet or Teflon coated pan.
When the peanut brittle becomes hard, crack and place in an airtight container.

title: meat loaf 1
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cracker crumbs and scalded milk.
Put cracker crumbs on top of mixture and pour milk over all and mix in.
Shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Combine.
Bake in oven at 350° in long oblong pan.
Do not grease pan.
Go around edges with a fork and stick the fork in places on top of shortbread.
Cut into slices while still warm.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini 3 minutes and drain.
Saute onion in 2 Tbsp. oleo.
Stir in 1/2 c. stuffing, soup and sour cream.
Turn into casserole dish and top with remaining stuffing and oleo.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
May be prepared a day ahead, except for baking.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Mix cooked apples, sugar and cinnamon and place in a small, greased casserole dish.
Combine oats, flour, brown sugar and margarine.
Crumble over apple mixture and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: baked macaroni
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Stir in dry macaroni and shredded cheese.
Pour milk over mixture and don't stir.
Bake, uncovered, in 360° oven for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine fruits and coconut in a large bowl. Fold in Cool Whip. Chill.

title: bostom clam chowder (soup) or corn chowder (soup)
directions: Peel and slice onions and potatoes.
Fry out the salt pork; cut in cubes in bottom of large pot.
Add potatoes, onions and seasonings.
Pour 1 cup of water over potatoes, etc., and let simmer until done.
Add clam broth and the same amount of milk. Let come to boil and serve with oysterettes (small round soda crackers).

title: sarah johnson's aspic
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Cool slightly.
Chop tomatoes and add.
Chop celery fine and add.
Put in refrigerator until firm. Aspic may be done in a bowl or fancy tube pan.

title: taco salad
directions: Toss onion, lettuce and tomatoes with grated cheese.
Add dressing and chill.
Brown and drain ground beef.
Add can of drained Ranch Style pinto beans and simmer 10 minutes.
Cool and add to cold salad.
Chill.
Slice and add avocado.
At last minute, crush and add Doritos chips.
Mix together and serve.

title: ham pie
directions: Remove all fats from meats and cut into small pieces.
Cut Mozzarella cheese into small pieces.
Chop hard-boiled eggs.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Add Ricotta, parsley, raw eggs and grated cheese and mix together very well.

title: fish-cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spread half the cheese and the onion over the bottom of baking dish.
Place fish on top and cover with remaining cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cheese.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hickory nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into grease pan. Bake at 350 degrees for one 1 1/2 hours. Ice with 7 minute frosting or frosting of choice.

title: egg nog
directions: Separate the white of the eggs from the yolks. Beat egg yolks. Gradually add salt, vanilla, milk and Eagle Brand milk. Chill. Just before serving, beat egg whites and fold in.

title: tuna-rice balls
directions: In bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
Blend soup, water and sugar in skillet.
Mix 2 tablespoons into rice mixture along with eggs.
Press into twenty 1-inch balls.
Bring soup mixture to boil. Add rice balls.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: orange pecan pumpkin crunch
directions: Blend together pumpkin, sugar, eggs, salt, orange extract, cinnamon, allspice and evaporated milk. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over top.
Dribble melted margarine over dry cake mix.
Sprinkle top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve warm or cold, topped with Cool Whip.

title: easy caramel icing
directions: Heat ingredients until sugar is dissolved. Add powdered sugar to make spreading.

title: whole grain banana oatmeal muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 12 medium muffin cups with paper baking cups or spray bottoms only with nonstick cooking spray. Combine dry ingredients; mix well.
Add bananas, margarine, milk and egg whites.
Fill muffin cups almost full.
Bake.

title: maple nut butter
directions: Chop the walnuts.
Combine with the remaining ingredients and blend.
Try on waffles or pancakes.
Yields 3/4 cup.

title: zucchini pie(serves 4)
directions: Dice or chop zucchini into 1/2-inch cubes.
Chop onion.
Saute together in oil until soft.
In large bowl, beat eggs.
Add cheese, Bisquick and zucchini mixture and mix well.
Place in greased pie pan and bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Take seeds out of green chili peppers and place on bottom of 7 1/2 x 11 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Place layer (1 1/2-inches thick, more or less) of zucchini on peppers; salt and pepper.
Then add a nice layer of cheese.
Mix Bisquick, eggs and milk.
Beat lightly and pour over mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in 4 tablespoons of butter until soft.
Stir in flour.
Add water and cook over low heat, stirring until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Blend in cheese.
Combine sauce and broccoli.
Add eggs, mix gently until blended.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Dot with remaining butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: breakfast egg casserole
directions: Put bread on bottom of 13 x 9-inch greased casserole dish. Distribute the cheese over the bread, then add the sausage. Beat eggs and add 2 1/2 cups milk and dry mustard; mix. Pour the egg mixture over the sausage and refrigerate overnight.

title: low cholesterol yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast and warm water together.
Blend well all of the ingredients.
Let rise.
Punch down and pinch off into rolls.
Let rise to desired size.
Bake at 350°
until browned.

title: clam chowder soup
directions: In a pan, saute onion and celery with butter or oleo.
Add 3 cans of cream of potato soup and 1 1/2 cans milk
Add parsley and simmer.
Add 2 cans minced clams with juice.
Add butter or oleo, salt and pepper.
If too thick, add more milk.

title: homemade macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni in salt and drain (do not rinse).
In saucepan combine cheese soup and milk on a low fire with continuous stirring.
Add Velveeta squares, slowly, making a creamy sauce. Combine sauce with macaroni.
In a large pan layer macaroni mixture with grated Longhorn cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes uncovered.

title: catfish stew
directions: Put fish in water, boil until they flake, take out of water, remove all bones.
Put onions in water fish was boiled in and cook until done.
Put fish back into pot and boil about 10 minutes. Add ketchup, boil 5 minutes and serve over rice or toast.

title: corn stuffing balls
directions: Heat margarine with water until margarine is melted.
Stir into stuffing mix.
Add remaining ingredients.
Shape into 20 to 22 balls, pressing together and adding a little more water. Arrange in buttered shallow baking dish; cover and refrigerate. About 1 hour before baking, remove from refrigerator.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated 400° oven 15 minutes or until heated and light brown.
Arrange around roast or serving dish.
Yield:
20 to 22 balls.

title: pear relish
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Cook until all pears are tender. For smaller quantity cut down each ingredient proportionally.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with raw vegetables.
Yield:
Serves a crowd.

title: ribs
directions: Rub spareribs on both sides with salt and pepper.
Put ribs in foil lined shallow pan. Bake for 15 minutes at 450°. Drain fat. Pour sauce over ribs.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°, basting occasionally.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the softened margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add beaten egg and mix well!
In another bowl mix together 1 1/4 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Add these dry ingredients alternately with the buttermilk mixed with baking soda.
Mix well! Add another 1 1/2 cups flour to make a soft dough.
Chill overnight, covered.
Roll 1/4 inch thick on floured surface.
Cut and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Store covered to stay soft.

title: raspberry dessert
directions: Combine the ingredients; press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Save some crumbs for the top.
Bake for 5 minutes in a 375° oven. Cool before adding filling.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour loaf pan. Pour mixture in pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugars and cream again.
Add eggs 1 at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in large greased and floured tube pan 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours at 325°.
Cool in pan.

title: pizza crust
directions: Combine flour, yeast, salt, and sugar and stir.
Heat vegetable oil and water to very warm (105° to 115°).
Add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Then allow to rest for 5 minutes.
Divide into 2 portions for two 12-inch pizzas or leave in one piece for one 16-inch pizza.
Spray pizza pan with no-stick vegetable oil and spread dough with fingers to cover pan.
Add sauce, topping, and cheese.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: hattie's chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, 3/4 cup sugar, cocoa, egg yolks and salt in top of double boiler with about 1/2 cup milk.
Stir mix to reduce lumping.
Put on top of boiler.
Add rest of milk; whisk until thick.
Add vanilla.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Beat egg whites with 1/3 cup sugar until stiff to make meringue.
Place on top of pie; bake at 450° until golden brown, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Yum, yum.

title: candied cherry macaroons
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon about 1 inch apart onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes or until delicate brown.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Mix all ingredients except the cooked spaghetti which is added last.
Mix well.
Pour in buttered 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
During last 15 minutes, top with 1/2 cup cheese and buttered bread crumbs. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased 8 X 8 X 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine flour, brown sugar, cinnamon, and oats.
Add melted butter.
Mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for about 25 to 30 minutes or until apples are tender and top is brown.
Ready to eat warm or cool.
The recipe can be doubled.

title: cube steaks parmigiana
directions: Season steaks.
Brown, remove fat.
Add sauce and mushrooms. Top each steak with cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Simmer, covered, 5 minutes.
Serve hot over spaghetti.

title: stakki uppi dinner
directions: *Chicken Gravy:
Gravy is very hot.
Use broth from chicken or Campbell's chicken broth (no milk) or Spice Island chicken base or Franco-American gravy or a combination.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in the oven until golden brown at 350° approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: refrigerator chocolate cake
directions: While cake is still warm, punch holes in it with a wooden spoon.
Pour ice cream topping over cake.
Wait 5 minutes and then pour milk over cake and wait 5 more minutes.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with pecans.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix together soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Pour hot marinade over vegetables. Refrigerate overnight or 12 hours.

title: herb toast
directions: Cut bread loaf into thirds, making cuts in the already-sliced bread. Lay the slices on a cookie sheet. Mix all the ingredients together and brush on bread. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 225° for 1 hour.

title: swenson's potato cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil; add egg yolks, then potatoes.
Mix all dry ingredients separately, sifted together 3 or 4 times.
Add alternately the dry ingredients and milk to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites last.
Bake at 350° until done, approximately 1/2 hour or so.

title: hobo stew
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain grease.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peach cream pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Add evaporated milk and stir. Drain juice off peaches and add to mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 50 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Chop onions, tomatoes (may use 1 large can of canned tomatoes), green pepper and celery.
These may be chopped as small or large as you like, depending on how chunky you like your salsa. This may also be done in a food processor.	Mix all ingredients and enjoy!

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix macaroni and cream cheese.
Blend in mushroom soup.
Stir in tuna (drained and flaked).
Add chopped pimiento, onion and milk.
Mix 1/2 cup bread crumbs and 2 tablespoons melted butter. Sprinkle over top and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375° in 1 1/2-quart bowl.

title: italian sausage spaghetti sauce
directions: In medium skillet, cook sausage until no longer pink; drain. Add onion, green pepper and garlic; cook until onion is tender. Stir in spaghetti sauce. Simmer 10 minutes. Prepare spaghetti according to package directions; drain. Toss with softened butter. Serve sauce over hot spaghetti. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt, pineapple and cherries in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thickened and bubbly. Remove from heat and add gelatin, stirring well.
Cool.

title: rice supreme
directions: Fry onions, pepper and beef in fat; add rice, tomatoes and water.
Season to taste.
Cook over low heat for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: easy peach pie
directions: Note:
Frozen or canned peaches can be used.
Must drain.

title: nut bread
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Mix milk and egg and add to dry mixture.
Mix thoroughly, but do not beat.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for about 1 hour or until straw comes out clean.
Beat if kept for a day or two, then slice as thin as possible and serve with butter or cream cheese.
Can be made 3 or 4 days in advance.
Also freezes well.
Makes 1 small loaf.
May use batter to make muffins.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers and onions for 48 hours in salt water to taste. Heat sugar and vinegar just enough to dissolve the sugar.
Drain cucumbers and onions.
Pour sugar and vinegar over cucumbers and onions.
Mix well and freeze.

title: tomato spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour 2 round layer pans or 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong pan.
Combine ingredients. Bake about 30 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Serve with confectioners sugar.

title: yummy pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar together.
Combine dry ingredients (flour, baking powder and salt).
Alternate 1 egg and the dry ingredients until all 5 eggs are mixed in.
Add coconut and coconut flavoring and blend.
Spray 3 (2 pound) loaf pans with Pam and flour lightly.
Pour in mixture.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 325° (not preheated).

title: brownie pie
directions: Mix ingredients, then pour into pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Let the pie cool.
Then top the pie with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: cherry breeze
directions: Mix flakes and oleo in a 9-inch pie pan; press over bottom and sides.
Chill.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy; add milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Turn into crust; chill 2 hours.
Add cherry pie topping.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix everything together.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Fry and drain bacon.
Mix in 9 x 13-inch pan ketchup, brown sugar, salt, onion, pepper, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Add the beans.
Mix in meat and bake for 2 hours at 325°.

title: vegetable salad(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Arrange the ingredients in a large bowl and serve with the dressing.

title: strawberry angel delight
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water in a large bowl. Add strawberries with their juice (break up and distribute thoroughly if still partially frozen).
Refrigerate until partially set, 45 minutes to one hour.
tags: frozen whipped topping plus additional topping

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Pour melted butter over crumbs, stirring well.
Spread 1/3 of crumbs on bottom of buttered casserole dish.
Cover with half of oysters.
Add another layer of crumbs.
Add last half of oysters and then remaining crumbs.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover with 2 cups cream or half and half.
Bake in moderate oven about 40 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine sugar, salt, cinnamon, butter, vanilla and egg.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Add bread cubes and raisins. Pour into well-buttered baking dish.
Set in pan of warm water and bake in moderate oven at 350° about 1 hour or until inserted knife comes out clean.
May be eaten warm or cold with cream or whipped topping.

title: corn pancakes
directions: Preheat griddle or waffle iron. Grease lightly. Blend ingredients. Batter will be slightly lumpy. Bake on hot griddle or waffle iron. Griddle is hot when a few drops of water dance on surface. For pancakes, turn when bubbles appear and edges begin to dry. Makes 10 to 12 pancakes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat.
(Microwave is quickest!) Stir.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: stuffing balls
directions: Cut up bread and set aside.
Finely chop onion and celery. Saute until limp, but not brown in melted butter.
Add 1/2 cup chicken soup, thyme, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Mix with bread and form balls (about 12).
Place in greased baking dish.
Mix remaining soup with water until smooth.
Pour 1 tablespoon of mixture
over each ball.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°. Remove cover.
Pour remaining soup over balls.
Bake uncovered 10 minutes.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Combine sliced berries, sugar or honey and orange juice.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Sift all dry ingredients together into a medium bowl.
Add orange rind.
Add butter and shortening and work them into flour mixture thoroughly.

title: angel fluff
directions: Mix and pour in ice tray lined with graham cracker crumbs. Scatter crumbs on top and put in freezer for 1 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: lois's rolls
directions: Mix yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Add sugar, then other ingredients, including remainder of water, alternating between liquid and dry ingredients.
Makes a firm dough.
Let rise 1 hour or more.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 450°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Flour and grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle butterscotch chips on top of batter before baking.
Cake is best served 1 day after it is baked.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together cocoa, flour, salt and baking soda.
Then mix sugar and cold water.
Blend mayonnaise mixture with dry ingredients and turn into 2 (8-inch) round cake pans or regular size cake pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until when touched, it springs back in place.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add shredded cabbage (at least one-half head or more if desired).

title: lettuce roll-ups
directions: Wash one leaf and dry it on a paper towel.
Roll leaf and meat together and eat.

title: ma-ma's crispy cheese rounds
directions: Mix with hands.
Yes, you
do
use 1 stick of margarine and
1 stick of butter.
Roll
into
small
balls.
Place
on ungreased cookie sheet and press down with fork.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 100 small or 75 large.

title: honey punch
directions: Mix all juices and honey together.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Pour over ice.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: easy no bake candy cookies
directions: Melt margarine or butter in heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Stir in sugar, salt, cocoa and milk; bring to a boil exactly 2 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, then oats.
Mix thoroughly and drop by rounded teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Cool and then chill.
Store airtight.
Yields about 56 cookies.

title: snowballs
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and milk in a large bowl with a wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion in butter, add remaining ingredients and heat.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Combine all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into a chocolate pie crust. Decorate with chocolate bits or ground peanuts.

title: microwave baked apples
directions: Put each apple half in custard cups.
Dot each with butter. Spoon corn syrup into each half.
Sprinkle with spice.
Cover with plastic wrap and cook on High for 2 minutes.
Baste and turn apples.
Cook 2 more minutes on High.
Let stand 2 minutes.

title: workday meal
directions: Combine celery and mushroom soups.
Add water to soups and set aside.
In a buttered baking dish, layer beans, potatoes and onion. Pour half of soup mixture on top.
Place ground beef on top of this.
Pour remaining soup over the ground beef.
Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
At end of cooking time, top with buttered Ritz crackers and return to oven until crumbs turn brown.

title: lunch box cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 8-inch cake pan.
Combine all ingredients except chocolate chips and nuts in a large mixer bowl. Blend well at low speed.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate pieces, nuts and a little white sugar.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except for 1 cup cheese.
Put into a large greased casserole.
Top with the 1 cup grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add water.
Stir until thickened.
Add lemon juice and butter.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Chop all together in food processor.
Let stand for 1 hour. Follow directions on package of jello.
Mix in fruit mixture. Refrigerate.

title: quiche aux crevettes
directions: Bake pie shell at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Set aside 4 shrimp for garnish.
Dice remaining shrimp.
Combine eggs, milk, cream and seasonings.
Arrange shrimp and cheese in partially baked pie shell.
Pour in egg mixture.
Top with reserved shrimp. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before serving.

title: burritos
directions: Heat refried beans.
Warm tortillas and spread with beans and cheese.
Roll tight and place in baking pan.
Before serving, heat burritos in oven for 10 minutes and serve with green chili burrito sauce.

title: avocado green salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large bowl. Tear lettuce and toss with mixture in bowl. Coat heavily with Parmesan cheese and toss until well coated. Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple strudel
directions: Unthaw the pastry as directed on box. You can cut each sheet into 4's or you can leave whole. Mix sugar and cinnamon. Spread over dough not getting on the edges if making squares. Mix pie filling, raisins and nuts together and put a small amount on each square. Take water and dampen edges of dough; bring up opposite corners and press together real well. If making roll, spread on dough and roll up. Place on a lightly sprayed baking sheet and bake for 35 minutes at 375°.

title: stir up chocolate cake
directions: Pour water over cocoa.
Pour all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Bake in oblong pan at 350°.

title: hawaiian rollers
directions: Separate dough into 8 pieces.
Put a teaspoon of preserves in the middle of each roll.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll dough up and seal.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: sunday morning brunch
directions: Spray a 9 x 13 pan with Pam.
Fry sausage and drain.
Layer 6 slices of bread in bottom of pan.
Put all of sausage on bread. Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese on sausage.
Layer 6 slices of bread on top.
Sprinkle rest of cheese over bread.
Break eggs into blender (can be done by hand), add milk (more or less to suit) and blend well.
Carefully pour over pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Next morning bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: bessies dumplings
directions: Work flour into ingredients listed to make stiff dough.
Roll out and cut in 1 1/2-inch squares.
Drop into chicken broth and cook until done.
Very good!

title: chinese stuff
directions: Cube chicken and fry.
While chicken is frying, cook rice in microwave.
When chicken is done, remove from skillet.
Scramble eggs.
Return chicken to skillet with eggs.
Add rice, soy sauce and onions.
Heat and serve.

title: three cheese ham puff
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 2-quart round casserole. Beat eggs with hand beater.
Beat in baking mix and milk until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients; pour into casserole.
Bake until knife inserted near center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
Let stand about 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except crackers, margarine and garlic and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Crush the 25 crackers and mix with the melted margarine.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Sprinkle this mixture over the baked vegetables and bake for an additional 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and take off bone.
Place in 13 x 9-inch dish. Mix soup and sour cream together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Melt oleo; stir in Ritz crackers, crushed. Mix thoroughly.
Sprinkle over chicken and bake 15 minutes longer or until light brown.

title: cheesy mashed potatoes
directions: Fix the whole box of potatoes as directed. Add cream cheese and sour cream. Mix well with mixer. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Grease crock-pot with 2 teaspoons oil or Crisco.
Mix all ingredients together and put into crock-pot.
Cut thin slices or pieces of cheese on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cook 3 to 4 hours on low.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Remove skin and bones from salmon.
Add all ingredients except egg whites.
Cool slightly before folding in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in buttered mold or loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken pie with biscuit topping
directions: Saute the onion, green pepper and celery in butter.
Blend in flour, garlic salt and pepper.
Dissolve bouillon cube in water or broth.
Stir into mixture.
Add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened.
Then add chicken, bacon and soy sauce.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart lightly buttered baking dish.

title: fish fillets thermidor
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Split fillets lengthwise and roll up; use toothpick if necessary.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Pour milk over fish; add salt and pepper.
Bake for 30 minutes.
When done, pour off milk and add slowly to melted margarine into which flour has been added.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add lemon juice and pour sauce over fillets.
Brown quickly under broiler.
Serves 3 to 4, depending on size of fillets.

title: torte pie
directions: Beat egg whites with vanilla and salt until very stiff. Gradually add sugar.
