Fold in nuts, cracker crumbs and coconut. Bake in 9-inch buttered pie pan (glass) at 325° for 30 minutes. Remove and cool.
top with unsweetened whipping cream.
Make the day before serving.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: In a large bowl, blend all ingredients at medium speed 5 minutes.
Pour into 10-inch Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool 15 minutes, then turn out.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk, Karo and salt.
Cook until hard ball forms when small amount is dropped in cup of cold water.
When hard ball forms, take off the fire and put pan in cold water.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat until stiff, then add pecans.
Put in buttered platter.
Cut into squares.
Enjoy.

title: chicken-a-la-can
directions: Mix both cans of soup, water, chicken and rice in skillet. Bring to a boil.
Stir occasionally.
Turn on low and simmer ten minutes or until thick.

title: bread dip(servings:  10)
directions: Hollow out the shepherd's bread like a bowl.
Mix ingredients together and put inside bowl of bread.
Cube French bread so that every piece has a crust.
Use for dipping with skewers.
Also may use dip with chips.

title: deer sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Use a little oleo and saute onions, celery and garlic.
Combine rice and soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cover with foil.
Grated cheese on top the last few minutes of cooking adds to the taste.

title: bleu cheese dip for vegetables
directions: Put in blender; cover.
Run 6 minutes at high speed.
Use with cucumbers, cherry tomatoes, zucchini squash, cauliflower sections, carrots or celery.

title: deer casserole
directions: In greased casserole dish put a layer of deer mixture
with a layer of tortilla chips, grated cheese and black olives chopped, layer until deer mixture is all used up.
Put in 300° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix cheese, chopped onions, 2 1/4 ounces beef (chopped) and sauce.
Roll into a ball.
On outside, put other half of chopped beef.
Serve with crackers.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Pour cola and ketchup over chicken placed in electric skillet at 275°, vent open at 275° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and cook another 30 minutes at 250°.
It's done and it's yummy.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into bowl.
Scoop out 3 holes in mixture and add vanilla, vinegar and oil, each in one hole.
Pour cold water over mixture.
Stir with spoon until smooth.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: neiman marcus dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl. Stir with a wooden spoon and pour into a serving dish. Good warm or chilled. Serve with Ritz Crackers, Waverly Crackers, or Cracked Pepper Corn Crackers. Truly a Terrific Dip! Enjoy!

title: sausburger dip
directions: Brown sausage and beef.
Cut cheese in small cubes.
Place in crock-pot with tomatoes and dressing.
Mix.
Add sausage and beef. Cook on high, stirring occasionally, until cheese is melted. Cook on low for 30 minutes.

title: cheese olive balls
directions: Blend cheese and margarine; add flour, paprika and salt.
Roll heaping teaspoonfuls around olives.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Can be frozen before baking.

title: delicious healthy strawberry shake
directions: In a blender, combine milk, honey, vanilla and frozen strawberries.
Blend until smooth.
Pour and serve.
Makes 2 servings.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat in the eggs thoroughly.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until set.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Debone and pound chicken flat.
Dip in seasoned eggs.
Fry in butter until brown; set aside.
Dissolve bouillon in boiling water.
Add lemon juice, flour and butter.
Pour mixture over chicken; garnish with fresh lemon.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: quick chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Spray a medium casserole dish with cooking spray.
Put mixture in casserole dish.
Cover casserole.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Remove cover and microwave another 10 minutes or cook in conventional oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove cover for last 15 minutes.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine flour and salt; add shortening and work in well.
Add eggs and water; mix well.
Roll out on floured board or counter; roll very thin and cut into noodles.
Drop in boiling chicken broth; cook until tender.

title: eggless zucchini brownies
directions: Mix together in a large bowl the flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, cocoa and nuts (optional).
Then add zucchini, oil and vanilla.
Mix by hand until moistened.
Pour in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: henry's barbecue
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; mix and put in jar.
Makes about a quart.
Keep in refrigerator until needed.
Will keep for months.

title: four tiered delight
directions: Mix and mash into sheet pan or casserole dish.
Cook at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes and cool.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Combine in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: thumbprints
directions: Mix well. Roll in small balls.
Dot on egg white and nuts. Bake 5 minutes at 350°.
Put in thumbprint.
Bake 8 minutes more. Take from oven and put dab of frosting and 1/2 colored cherry. (Thumbprints can be made with back of teaspoon or a small stick.)

title: suckers
directions: Combine sugar, water and corn syrup.
Cook to hard crack stage. Remove from heat.
Add color and flavor.
Stir about 2 minutes. Pour into greased molds or onto marble slab or greased cookie sheet.
Makes 10 to 20.

title: rainbow cream cheese fruit salad
directions: Combine all the fruit, add lemon juice and toss. Blend together the cream cheese, brown sugar, vanilla and cinnamon. Add fruit and pretzels, fold together. Serve immediately with a dollop of lite whipped topping or refrigerate until chilled.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Bring first 6 ingredients to a boil and let cool.
Put the remaining ingredients in a colander and drain.
Pour liquid over vegetables and refrigerate overnight or 1 day ahead of time.

title: polish sauerkraut
directions: May add tomatoes and sour cream.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; set aside.
Combine sugar and eggs in a large bowl; beat at high speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add oil and pumpkin, beating well.
Gradually add flour mixture, 1 cup at a time, beating at low speed just until blended.
Pour batter into an ungreased 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake springs back when lightly touched. Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and let cool completely on a wire rack.
Frost top and sides of cake with Cream Cheese Frosting and garnish with pecan halves.

title: knox blocks
directions: In bowl, sprinkle gelatine over cold juice; let stand 1 minute.
Add
hot
juice and stir until gelatine is completely dissolved.	Pour
into 8 or 9-inch baking dish and chill until firm
in
refrigerator.
To
serve,
cut
into 1-inch squares. Makes about 6 dozen blocks.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add egg yolks and vanilla and blend.
Stir in baking powder and flour.
When evenly crumbled pat lightly into a greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup of finely chopped walnuts over the crumbly mix.

title: outer banks poor man's cake
directions: 1. Boil raisins in 2 c. water for 15 minutes and let cool. 2. Sift dry ingredients together. Add raisins and mix with
1 c. water.
3. Melt shortening in baking pan. Pour in batter with the
rest of the shortening mixed in it and into pan.
4. Bake for 1 hour at 350° in
oven.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: In a large pot, boil water.
Place head of cleaned cabbage in water until cabbage leaves are soft and wilted.
Remove from water and cool; separate leaves.
Place 2 tablespoons of meat mixture in center of each cabbage leaf.
Roll cabbage around meat mixture.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook apples, sugar and vinegar for 30 minutes.
Stir in candy while cooking.
Remove from heat and stir in spices.
Put in jars and seal.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and nut meats.
Add sifted dry ingredients, alternating with milk.
Add vanilla; fold in egg whites.
Bake 70 minutes in loaf pan in moderate oven.

title: sauerkraut sausage casserole
directions: Pan-fry sausage until lightly browned.
Remove sausage from skillet.
Drain off all but 2 tablespoons drippings.
Saute onion in drippings.
In 2-quart casserole, place half the sauerkraut, then half the onions and half the caraway seed.
Repeat layers and top with sausage links.
Pour apple juice over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover last 15 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel the eggplant and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Soak in water for about 10 minutes.
Remove from water.
Pat dry and fry lightly. Grease a casserole dish and layer the following ingredients in the dish:
eggplant, browned hamburger, chopped onion, salt, pepper, oregano and tomato soup.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour with a cover and for 1/2 hour without a cover.

title: nichole's savory cheddar bread
directions: Combine
flour,
baking
powder,
sugar,
onion
salt, oregano,
dry
mustard
and grated cheese; set aside.
Combine well
beaten
egg, milk and melted butter;
add all at once to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spread batter in a greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Yield:
1 loaf.

title: fluffy baked omelet
directions: Beat egg yolks; add flour, cornstarch, salt and pepper and beat until smooth.
Add milk gradually, beating constantly.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into egg yolk mixture. Melt butter in a heavy 9-inch skillet.
Pour in egg yolk mixture and bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 20 minutes.
Fold onto hot platter.
Serve at once.

title: sugar free punch
directions: Can use 7 up instead of ginger ale.

title: cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine graham crackers, butter and walnuts.
Press into bottom and sides of 10-inch springform pan.

title: dump cake
directions: Butter an 11 x 14-inch pan and add ingredients in order.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°.
Top with Cool Whip (optional).

title: pinto bean - coconut pie
directions: Combine beans, sugar, butter, eggs, coconut and pecans.
Beat well by hand about 1 or 2 minutes.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: surprise (black bottom) cupcakes
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add all liquids to sifted ingredients and mix until smooth.
Fill cup cake pans 2/3 full. Top with heaping teaspoon of filling.
Bake at 350° approximately 25 minutes.

title: quickie fudge
directions: Pour all ingredients into a microwaveproof saucepan, or an 8-cup measuring cup, except for the vanilla and the nuts. Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Add the vanilla and nuts and stir well.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch buttered pan.
Freeze for 20 minutes or refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: sausage cake
directions: Mix all ingredients (it's easier to use your hands to work dry ingredients with sausage).
Spread evenly in a 10-inch tube pan. Bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: parfait salad log
directions: Drain fruit cocktail; gradually add salad dressing and sugar to softened cream cheese.
Mix in a few drops of food coloring until well blended.
Fold in drained fruit cocktail, marshmallows, nuts and whipped cream, then spoon mixture into two 1 pound coffee cans; cover and freeze.
Remove from cans onto lettuce leaves. Serves 10 to 12.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown onion and ground beef in a little oil (1 tablespoon). Mix all ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cover first 30 minutes and take lid off last 15 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Whisk milk gradually adding egg yolks, vanilla, and other ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Makes enough for 15
biscuits.

title: chicken crescent squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, blend the cream cheese and margarine until smooth.
Add the next 5 ingredients; mix well.
Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture onto center of each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners of dough to top center of chicken mixture; twist slightly and seal edges.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: In large bowl, mix by hand the eggs, oil and sugar.
Add and beat by hand all the rest of the ingredients.
Add cut, drained apples and nuts last.
Be sure apple pieces are no bigger than half and slice.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.
It is done when it starts to pull away from sides of pan.
Do not overcook.

title: chicken divine
directions: Boil chicken; debone and place in bottom of casserole dish. Boil broccoli and add layer of chicken.
Mix soup with mayonnaise; spread over broccoli, then spread grated cheese over the soup-mayonnaise mixture.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients; form into ball.
Roll in extra nuts and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: strawberry glazed pie
directions: Wash, drain and hull strawberries.
For glaze, simmer 1 cup of sliced berries with 2/3 cup water until berries start to break up, about 3 minutes.
Blend sugar, cornstarch and remaining 1/3 cup water.
Stir into boiling mixture.
Add some red food coloring. Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Cool.

title: breast of chicken "magnifique"
directions: Use 1 large skillet or prepare in 2 skillets (10-inch) by dividing the ingredients equally.
Brown chicken in butter; remove.
Brown mushrooms.
Stir in soup, garlic and seasonings; add chicken.
Cover; cook over low heat for 45 minutes.
Stir now and then.
Blend in cream; heat slowly.
Serve with wild rice mix. Garnish with toasted, slivered almonds.
Makes 8 servings.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift together plain flour and sugar and set aside.
Mix butter, oil, Coca-Cola and cocoa in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and pour over dry mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
(Do not use mixer.)
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: green beans with sour cream
directions: Brown mushrooms in fat; add beans, cream, salt and pepper. Heat thoroughly.
Serves 6.

title: finger paints
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in cold water.
Mix into boiling water; stir until clear.
Cool; add a few drops of food coloring.
Paint with fingers on paper.

title: danish pastry apple bars
directions: Combine flour and salt; cut in shortening.
Beat egg yolk in measuring cup; add enough milk to make 2/3 cup liquid.
Mix well; stir into flour mixture.
On floured surface, roll half the dough to 17 x 12-inch rectangle; fit into and up sides of 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with cornflakes; top with apples.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle atop.
Roll remaining dough to 15 1/2-inch rectangle; place over apples.
Seal edges; cut slits in top.
Beat egg white until frothy; brush on crust.
Bake in 375° oven for 50 minutes.
Combine 1 cup sifted powdered sugar and 3 to 4 teaspoons milk; drizzle on warm cookies. Makes 3 dozen.

title: louisiana okra gumbo
directions: Cook grease and flour 30 to 45 minutes, stirring constantly. Saute chopped onions, celery and garlic in roux; add 1/2 pot of water, okra, tomatoes (cut up) and seasonings.
Cook 3 hours. Toward the end, add seafood or chicken and file.

title: rancho beans
directions: Saute onion in shortening.
Add ground beef and cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into casserole dish.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven or simmer 25 to 30 minutes in Dutch oven on low heat.

title: grilled chicken with dijon mayonnaise
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken in a bowl.
Stir.
Add chicken and coat well.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight or at least 4 hours.
Spray nonstick sheet with nonstick spray.
Arrange chicken on tray.
Spread remaining mayonnaise mixture over chicken.
Broil 5 to 6 inches from heat until chicken is light brown and cooked through, 8 to 10 minutes.
Serves 2. Contains 177 calories, 6 gm fat and 412 mg sodium.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Cool eggs and peel.
Mold sausage around eggs. Dip in flour; easier if you keep hands floured.
Dip in 3 beaten eggs.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Chill 24 hours.
Deep fry; cool and chill.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Blend corn meal and sugar.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with oil and dust with corn meal. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine on low heat; remove from heat.
Add sugar and cocoa and blend.
Add eggs.
Stir, don't beat.
Add milk and vanilla and stir.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Turn to 350° and bake for 20 minutes.
Let set before cutting (about 1 hour).
Top with Cool Whip.
Makes 6 to 7 servings.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook meat and onion.
Mix all other ingredients and add cooked meat.
Put in a large pan a layer of tortillas and pour mixture over these.
Cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour, then add cheese.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa.
Cook to a rolling boil for 1 1/2 minutes (timed).
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and drop on wax paper.

title: safflower oil biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 475° (very hot).
Mix dry ingredients in a bowl.
Pour oil and milk into measuring cup, but do not stir. Pour all at once into flour.
Stir with fork until mixture cleans sides of bowl and rounds up into a ball.
Smooth by kneading dough about 10 times without any additional flour.
With dough on waxed paper, press out 1/4-inch thick with hands or roll between waxed paper.
Cut with unfloured biscuit cutter.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased baking sheet.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease (Pam) a 10-inch quiche dish or 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onions in plate. Beat remaining ingredients for 1 minute with electric mixer.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife comes out clean (35 to 40 minutes). Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: merkle's creamy potato casserole
directions: Butter a baking dish, 13 x 9-inch.
Toss all ingredients together in a bowl.
Transfer to the greased dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.
Serves 12.

title: french-vanilla apple cake
directions: Beat cake mix, eggs, oil and 1/4 of the pie filling on low speed for 30 seconds.
Increase to medium speed and beat 2 minutes.
Pour batter into two buttered and floured 8 inch round pans.

title: justin's favorite congealed salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Boil sugar, sorghum, water and spices 5 minutes.
Pour over tea and let stand 10 minutes.
Strain and add fruit juices and water.
Preheat and serve in cups or tall glasses.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in

margarine, medium heat, about 10 minutes. Add flour, salt and pepper. Stir constantly for 2 minutes. Add broth slowly. Add broccoli. Bring to a boil. Stir frequently. Cover and simmer until broccoli is tender. Puree in blender. Return to pan add milk, and bring to simmer.

title: mexican salsa
directions: Peel and chop tomatoes or put can of tomatoes in bowl.
Thinly slice scallions or onions and add.
Add fresh chopped parsley and chopped chiles.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix gently. Cover and refrigerate.

title: fish stew
directions: Parboil fish in water; lift fish out to cool.
Fry bacon and saute onions in drippings.
Boil potatoes in fish broth until almost done.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and onions.
Cook for 5 minutes, until potatoes are tender.
Bone/flake fish and crumble bacon.
Add to other mixture in pot.
Heat to simmer.
Break 1 egg into the stew for every person who will be eating and one or two extra for the pot.
Cover for about 5 minutes.
Dish into large soup bowls, ensuring that every person gets an egg.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Add all ingredients and mix well. Pour into 9-inch deep-dish unbaked pie crust. Bake in 350° oven for at least 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix together cake mix and 1 can pie filling.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool completely.
Top with 1 can lemon pie filling.
Top with Cool Whip a few hours before serving.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring the first 5 ingredients to a boil for 2 minutes.
Add the oats.
Drop onto waxed paper by spoonfuls.

title: simple chicken stir-fry
directions: In small bowl, combine soy sauce and cornstarch; mix well. Add chicken and toss to coat.
In wok, heat 1 tablespoon oil.
Add chicken mixture; stir-fry until chicken is no longer pink.
Might have to cook chicken in several small batches for optimum results. Remove chicken and set aside.
Heat remaining 1 1/2 teaspoons oil in wok.
Add vegetables, garlic and ginger.
Stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender and hot.
Return chicken to skillet with duck sauce and broth.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Serves 3 to 4.
Serve on noodles or rice.

title: chicken divan lisa
directions: Boil, skin, bone and cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Spread chopped broccoli in the bottom of a 13 x 8-inch dish.
Layer chicken on top.
Mix milk, soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder in a bowl.
Pour mix over chicken.
Spread cheese and then bread crumbs over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan and top with a combination of 2 cups corn bread stuffing mix and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 45 minutes.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Pour over vegetables and refrigerate.
Better if it is made a day ahead of time.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Chop lettuce into bite size.
Chop the green onions fine. Grate the hard-boiled eggs.
Slice the bacon bite size and cook crisp.
Thaw the peas. Combine all ingredients.
Top with Hellmann's mayonnaise. Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.

title: pepsi chicken
directions: Cook in Dutch oven with 12 to 14 pieces of charcoal underneath and line the rim of lid with charcoal. Cook until bubbly and chicken is done.

title: hot mulled cider(microwave)
directions: Combine apple cider, whole cloves and cinnamon stick in a heat-resistant, nonmetallic mug, cup or glass.
Heat uncovered on Full power 2 to 3 minutes (170°).
Garnish with a dollop of whipped cream and a sprinkling of nutmeg.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter 8-inch square baking pan.
In heavy, 4-quart saucepan, combine sugars, milk, butter and cream of tartar.
Heat to boiling over medium heat.
Reduce to low.
Cook, without stirring, until mixture reaches 240° on a candy thermometer or soft ball stage.
Remove fudge mixture from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until fudge begins to get firm.
Pour into buttered pan.
Refrigerate until firm; cut into squares.

title: like whipped cream frosting
directions: Combine cornstarch and milk in a saucepan.
Cook until thick, stirring (when removed from heat) until cool.
Combine margarine, Crisco and sugar; beat in electric mixer until creamy.
Add cooled mixture and beat until like whipped cream.
This icing tastes like true whipped cream if allowed to remain at room temperature.
If refrigerated and served cold, it is almost like ice cream.

title: aunt helen springer's old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add egg and flour.
Add vanilla. Can be shaped into a roll and refrigerated until cold and then sliced.
Can be rolled and cut with cutter.
Cook in 350° oven on greased cookie sheet just until browned.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen large or 3 dozen small cookies.
Sugar can be sprinkled on before baking.

title: frozen salad
directions: Combine maple syrup and cream cheese; beat until light and fluffy.
Add dates and pineapple.
Prepare Dream Whip according to directions; add all together and freeze.

title: cheddar chowder
directions: In large saucepan, add first 7 ingredients and simmer gently for 10 minutes.
Make a white sauce with the butter, flour and milk.
Add the grated cheese to the sauce and stir until all cheese is melted.
Add to cheese sauce one 16 ounce can cream-style corn and the precooked veggies with their liquid. Heat thoroughly and serve.

title: chili-cheese hors d'oeuvre
directions: Spread chopped chilies in 9x13 pan.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Beat 2 eggs, chili juice and milk.
Pour over chili-cheese.
Bake 350° for 1/2 hour.
Cut into squares and serve on crackers.

title: easy rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the warm water and set aside.
In a bowl, put the oleo and sugar and pour the boiling water over until the oleo melts.
Cool. Add the egg and beat well with whisk.
Add to yeast mixture.
Add the flour and pinch of salt.
Make out in pan or muffin tins and let rise.
Bake at 375° until golden brown. May refrigerate dough (covered) for a few days.

title: refrigerated crescent rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, add remaining 1 1/2 cups water, sugar, egg, salt and shortening; beat well.
Add yeast and flour; mix well.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Will keep 1 week.
When ready to use, divide dough into 4 balls.
Roll each into a 10 or 12-inch circle. Spread with soft margarine.
Cut into 12 pie-shaped pieces.
Roll up each piece, starting with large end.
Place on greased cookie sheet; let rise at least 2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in hot oil until browned.
Add remaining ingredients in order given.
Cook slowly over medium heat for 1 hour, or until liquid is reduced by half.
Makes 2 c. sauce.

title: bacon cheeseburger balls
directions: In a bowl, combine egg and soup mix. Crumble beef over mixture and mix well. Divide into 36 portions; set aside. In a bowl, combine the flour and milk until smooth. Add cheese and bacon; mix well. Shape cheese mixture into 36 balls. Shape one beef portion around each cheese ball. In a shallow bowl, beat the eggs. Place cracker crumbs in another bowl.
Dip meatballs into egg, then coat with crumbs. In a large skillet over medium heat, cook meatballs in oil for 10-12 minutes or until meat is no longer pink and coating is golden brown. Yield: 3 doz.

title: sausage cream cheese dip
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet.
Cook until well done and drain thoroughly.
Microwave cream cheese, sour cream and tomatoes until melted.
Add sausage to mixture and microwave another minute. Serve hot.
May add picante sauce if you like it spicier.

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: Chop together cabbage and carrot and let stand for 1 hour. Boil together sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed. Mix with vegetables and let stand for 2 hours. Drain and freeze. Add a little mayonnaise and vinegar to taste when ready to serve.

title: fresh corn and tomato casserole
directions: Cut corn from cob (there should be 4 to 5 cups of corn).
Melt butter in a skillet; add corn and saute quickly (about 5 minutes). Add crumbled bacon and salt.
Arrange in buttered casserole in alternate layers with the sliced tomatoes.
Place in a moderate oven (350°) and bake 30 minutes, or until corn is tender.
Serves 6.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Marinate spareribs at room temperature for 1 hour in combined Cointreau, soy sauce, honey, pineapple, vinegar, lemon slices, ginger, garlic and pepper. Remove lemon from marinade. Broil spareribs for 20 minutes on each side, basting frequently with the marinade. Serves 6.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Combine and place in shallow container or Ziploc bag.
Cover or seal and chill 1 to 2 hours.
Grill, covered, over medium coals, 300° to 400° for 4 to 5 minutes on each side.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour into an 8-inch baking pan.
Combine the remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Cut in margarine with pastry blender (or two knives) until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle over blackberry mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serve warm with Cool Whip or ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: easy fall punch
directions: Mix when ready to serve.

title: pesto for pasta
directions: Put in food processor.
Cook on low heat for 5 or 10 minutes. Add more oil to achieve desired consistency.
Spoon over angel hair pasta.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onion.
Break, cook and drain lasagna noodles, starting with noodles, alternate in layers twice. Cook on low setting in crock-pot 4 to 5 hours.

title: hi-rice
directions: Add Monterey jack cheese to warm rice.
Stir in sour cream and the green chiles.
Top with Cheddar cheese and bake for 20 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: home makers holiday
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Combine soup, milk and cheese. Simmer and stir until cheese is melted.
Mix all ingredients and pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ruth's quick caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in saucepan, add brown sugar and cook, stirring constantly, over low heat for 2 minutes.
Add milk and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat, cool.
Add sugar until spreading consistency is reached.
Makes enough frosting for 2 (9-inch) layers or a 13 x 9-inch sheet cake.

title: apple dump cake
directions: Mix pie filling and pineapple in pan. Sprinkle cake mix over this.
Pour melted butter over this. Mix pecans and coconut and pat over butter. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cabbage soup
directions: In large saucepan, brown meat; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Freezes well.
Better the second day.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix fruit and nuts in 1 c. flour.
Mix butter, sugar and eggs. lemon juice with flour and baking powder.
Add fruit an nuts.
Bake at 275° for 4 1/2 hours.

title: jam cake
directions: Put raisins in a pan of water; boil for a few minutes.
Drain. Cream sugar and butter; add eggs, milk and dry ingredients.
Mix well; add nuts and raisins.
Bake in 3 layers at 325° until done. Let cool.

title: york presbyterian chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing and melted margarine.
Reserve about 1 cup for top.
Mix remaining ingredients with stuffing mix.
Add reserved stuffing on top.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Heat to boiling.
Boil, stirring, for 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour gradually over popped corn, mixing well.
Turn into large shallow baking pans. Bake in 250° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool completely.
Break apart.
Store in lightly covered containers.

title: never fail peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix peanut butter and the marshmallow creme together.
Mix well; set aside.
In heavy pan mix the sugar and evaporated milk. (One small can equals 2/3 cup.)
Boil until soft ball forms in cold water.
Pour over marshmallow creme and peanut butter mixture.
Stir well.
Pour in greased pan.

title: banana pudding
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt; gradually stir in milk. Cook and stir over medium-high heat until bubbly, about 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir a moderate amount of hot mixture into egg yolks; mix immediately and return to hot mixture.
Cook about another 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.

title: pecan delight pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff while adding sugar and baking powder. Fold in crushed soda crackers, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan and bake at 325° for about 30 minutes. When cool, top with whipped cream and sprinkle with pecans.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise; remove yolks.
Mash yolks.
Stir in sandwich spread, onion, curry powder, salt and pepper.
Fill each egg white with yolk mixture; chill.
Sprinkle stuffed egg halves with paprika.

title: sausage and broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 to 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: Combine
in
large heavy pan, soda and buttermilk.
Rise during
first
minutes.
Continue cooking another 5 minutes, then add butter and pecan halves.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Spoon on greased wax paper, last
step must be done hurriedly, or it will set up too quickly.

title: the more you eat the more you lose soup
directions: Cut vegetables and cover with water in large pot.
Boil 10 minutes.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are soft.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil potatoes in skins until tender. Peel; put into bowl with butter.
Beat with mixer.
Add sugar and eggs.
(Every so often clean beaters to remove the strings.)
Add milk; beat.
Add vanilla, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Beat until smooth and free of strings.
Pour into pie shells and bake until slightly brown on top.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Add remainder ingredients, mixing well.
Chill.
Shape into ball or other shape.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Serve.

title: mom's barbecues(sloppy joes)
directions: Brown first three ingredients in small amount of vegetable oil.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, for 30 to 45 minutes until consistency desired for sandwiches.
Serve on toasted buns.
Leftovers taste great. Excellent for freezing.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat the egg yolks well in a medium size bowl; set aside.
Beat the egg whites in a large bowl until stiff, then add the sugar. Fold the egg yolks into the egg white and sugar mixture until thoroughly combined.
Stir in the rum, bourbon, cream and milk; beat well.
Pour into a punch bowl; sprinkle the nutmeg on top. Yields 12 servings.

title: fish chowder
directions: Fry up salt pork or bacon in soup pot until crisp.
Remove fat bits and leave fat.
Place onion and garlic in pot and fry until soft.
Add potatoes, celery tops and Worcestershire sauce.
Barely cover with water and cook until potatoes are just soft.
Lay fish fillets over potatoes.
Cover and cook until the fish flakes and crumbles.
Add rest of seasonings and evaporated milk.
Heat, but do not boil.

title: oven baked popcorn
directions: Boil margarine, Karo and sugar 10 minutes.
Take off heat and add vanilla.
Pop popcorn and coat popcorn with mixture.
Place in oven at 200° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine; add sage.
Stir into stuffing mix.
Mix together soup and sour cream.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 3/4 of stuffing mixture, soup/sour cream mixture, chicken or turkey and rest of the stuffing mix and pour broth over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk until smooth.
Drain crab meat and add to cheese mixture.
Add onion, horseradish and pepper to taste.
Blend all ingredients well.
Put in small, shallow casserole dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Mix with oil.
Add zucchini, sugar and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add nuts to dry mixture, coating nuts well.
Add dry mixture to wet; blend thoroughly.
Bake in loaf pans at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter.
Add hamburger and brown. Add flour, salt and pepper and cook 5 minutes.
Add soups and sour cream and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over your choice of noodles.

title: chili rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan drops
directions: Combine flour, salt and soda.
Set aside.
Cream shortening and butter.
Add brown sugar, eggs and flour mixture.
Add pecans. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Place tomatoes, onions and garlic in blender or food processor; blend until smooth.
Transfer to a large saucepan.
Add chicken broth and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes.
Cut tortillas into 1/2-inch strips.
Fry in hot oil until crisp and brown.
Drain.
Ladle soup into bowls.
Top with tortilla strips, sour cream and cheese.

title: grandma's ginger creams
directions: Cream together shortening, molasses, sugar and egg.
Add water.
Sift together flour, cloves, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger, salt and soda.
Add dry ingredients to cream mixture.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until done.

title: coconut divinity
directions: Grease side of heavy pan; combine sugar, syrup, hot water and salt in pan.
Stir to a boil.
Cook, without stirring, to hard boil stage.
Beat egg whites to soft peak.
Add gelatin, beating to stiff peaks.
Pour hot syrup into egg whites in thin stream, beating constantly.
Beat until candy begins to hold shape.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Mix well; spoon into mounds on greased platter.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with boiling water.
Add all other ingredients, except sour cream.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into glass baking dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch) and refrigerate until firm.
Then spread on sour cream and gently spoon rest of mixture on top (that has not been refrigerated) and refrigerate.

title: my mom's killer brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt chocolate and margarine over very low heat in a medium-size saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir. Add sugar, eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Stir in flour gradually. Pour into a greased and floured 9-inch pan.
(Note:
If your oven has a tendency to burn the bottoms of cookies, place the baking pan on a cookie sheet, particularly the kind with an air-filled base, available at local gourmet equipment shops.)
Bake about 45 minutes.
Brownies should have pulled away slightly from the sides of the pan.
Cool completely before serving.
Brownies will be moist.

title: hot artichoke and spinach dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise, Parmesan, Romano, garlic, basil and garlic salt. Put Mozzarella over the top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: fruit-berry freeze
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients in blender.
Pour into two glasses; add 1/3 cup soda to each glass.
Serves 2.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin and ice cream together.
Add pudding mix.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip and walnuts.
Refrigerate.

title: egg nog cream pie
directions: Early morning or day ahead:
Prepare nut pie crust.
Preheat oven to 300°.
In 9-inch pie plate with hand, mix coconut, almonds and margarine.
Press mixture firmly onto bottom and sides of pie plate.
Bake for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on wire rack.

title: dieter's egg salad
directions: Mix together and serve on lettuce or have on bread.

title: swedish butter cookies
directions: Cream the butter well.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Add enough flour to make a stiff batter.
Make into a roll as for icebox cookies and roll in colored sugar.
Chill a couple of hours and cut in rather thick slices.
Bake as any icebox cookie.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in hot water.
Add lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Stir to dissolve.
Chill until partially set. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well and refrigerate.

title: pumpkin pound cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer, about 2 minutes or until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.

title: aunt isabelle's pie crust (the best)
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder. Cut in the shortening. Add mixture of egg, vinegar and water. This makes 5 single crusts. Keeps in refrigerator.

title: italian style chicken
directions: Place chicken in well greased Dutch oven and add all ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Stir; uncover last 5 minutes to thicken.

title: mother's fruit cake
directions: Mix dates, candied cherries and pineapple with flour; mix until all is covered.
Set aside.
In another bowl, mix eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until frothy.
Add to fruit mix.
Add broken up pecans and stir.
Pack in 2 (8-inch) round pans with hole in middle.
Can use fruit glass in middle of regular pan. Line pans with brown paper.
Bake in 275° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Let set 5 minutes and peel off paper.
This cake will keep for up to 3 months.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place rice in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add chicken breasts.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix together milk and soups.
Heat mixture (do not boil) and pour over chicken.
Cover pan with foil and bake in preheated oven for 45 minutes or until chicken tests done; preheat oven to 350°.

title: mac's holiday eggnog
directions: Beat the egg yolks together with the sugar until the mixture is thick and creamy. Add the whole milk, bourbon and cognac.
Stir well.
(This mixture is the eggnog base and can be made a day or two in advance.)

title: blond brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Prepare an 8 x 10-inch (for thicker) or 9 x 12-inch (for thinner brownies) baking dish by spraying it with vegetable oil.

title: sea island bars
directions: Melt oleo and add other ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 9-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ham and cheese layered casserole
directions: Preheat oven to to 350°.

Place 6 bread slices in a lightly greased 7 x 11 inch baking dish. Sprinkle ham and 1 cup of cheese, top with remaining bread slices. Stir together eggs and next 3 ingredients, pour over bread. Bake for 40-50 minutes, sprinkle with remaining 1 cup of cheese, bake 5 minutes more. Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Serves 6.

title: crab meat casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions. Drain.
Mix with other ingredients, reserving 1/4 cup cheese for top.
Cook in two 8 x 8-inch greased pans in a 375° oven for 15 minutes. Do not overcook!

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes; peel and slice while hot.
Soak in salt and 1/4 cup water; drain.
Add oil, vinegar, onions, pepper and nutmeg. Toss and chill.

title: chicken yakitori
directions: Remove any skin from the chicken.
Cut meat into 1-inch cubes and
place in bowl.
Trim and wash scallions; cut enough thin slices for 1/4 cup.
Cut remaining scallions into 2-inch sticks and set aside.
Combine sliced scallions and remaining ingredients in a jar; cover.
Shake well and pour over chicken cubes.
Cover the bowl and marinate in refrigerator for 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally.
Thread chicken cubes on skewers, alternating with scallion sticks.
Place skewers on a broiler rack or out over grill 4 inches from heat and cook 1 to 2 minutes on each side until chicken is done.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: oriental casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onions and green peppers. Shred or chop cabbage. Place in casserole dish in layers layer of raw cabbage and layer of hamburger. Mix cabbage and hamburger. Pour tomato soup over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes approximately 6 to 8 servings.

title: sugar pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add boiling water.
Dissolve dry ingredients, then add half and half.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: turkey roll-ups
directions: Make stuffing according to directions.
Take 1 slice of turkey breast.
Place stuffing at one end and roll.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Make as many as desired.
Spread undiluted turkey gravy over rolls.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cube and melt cheese in crock-pot or saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir as needed.
Serve hot with tortilla/taco chips.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding according to directions on box, except use juice drained from fruit instead of milk or water.
Pour over fruit and mix.
Chill.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain.
Mix all remaining ingredients in casserole with beef.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with grated cheese if desired.

title: scalloped apples
directions: Peel and dice apples.
Put apples in a casserole.
Sprinkle water over apples, lemon juice, salt and cinnamon.
Mix flour, margarine and brown sugar with 2 knives or pastry blender until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until done.

title: party bake chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter and Italian dressing mix *(reserve 1/2 teaspoon of Italian dressing mix).
Place in baking dish.
Mix soup, cream cheese with chives and Sauturne.
Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste 2 to 3 times.
Serve over rice.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Carefully cut potatoes in half lengthwise and scoop out pulp. Reserve skin shells.
Beat potatoes together with yogurt, cheese, butter, milk, onion, seasonings and optional bacon (an electric beater works well).
Stuff the skin shells with the potato mixture and reheat in a 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: pizza
directions: Mix Jiffy mix and water into a dough; spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour half of mixture in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake with topping and swirl with a knife. Pour remainder of batter in pan and swirl.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Drizzle top of cake with icing.

title: fruit cake
directions: Combine butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift 1 cup flour, salt and baking powder.
Add pineapple juice alternately with dry ingredients. Mix fruits and the remaining 1/2 cup flour and add to the mixture. Place in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° until desired doneness.

title: brownie supremes
directions: Melt butter with chocolate square and chocolate chips.
Beat eggs; add sugar and beat well.
Add vanilla, then beat in melted chocolate mixture.
Stir in flour, nuts and marshmallows.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: rice and pork chop casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Brown pork chops in butter.
Transfer chops to casserole and combine remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture over and around chops.
Cover.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix the Dream Whip as directed on package.
Add softened cream cheese and beat well.
Add confectioners sugar and beat well.
Put this in baked pie shells.
Put blueberry pie filling on top and store in refrigerator overnight.

title: cheesy tuna medley
directions: In saucepan, cook bacon until crisp; remove and crumble.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons drippings.
Cook onion with thyme in drippings until tender.
Stir in soup, water, tomatoes and pepper; add potatoes and tuna.
Heat; stir occasionally.
Garnish with bacon.
Makes about 4 1/2 cups.

title: crab stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: Drain
crabmeat on several layers of paper towels.
Cut off
a thin
slice from top and bottom of each cherry tomato. With
a small melon ball cutter, remove pulp from tomatoes and drain upside
down
on
paper
towels.
In
a small bowl, mix crabmeat, mayonnaise,
parsley,
mustard
and salt until well blended. Stuff
tomatoes.
Chill
at
least 30 minutes before serving.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Trim crust and cube the bread.
Place on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Layer cooked sausage and grated cheese. Put Cheddar cheese on top.
Pour beaten eggs, mixed with milk, over top with undiluted soup.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cantaloupe bread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Cream the sugar and shortening together.
Add the egg and the cantaloupe.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a greased bread pan for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, milk, oleo and cocoa.
Boil hard for 1 minute.
Remove from heat, then add the vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper or greased pan.
Cool completely.

title: thin peach tart
directions: Combine flour and salt in bowl. Cut in margarine with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle with water and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir with fork until all dry ingredients are moistened.

Shape dough into ball and press into lightly greased pie plate. Set aside. Combine peaches, apple juice, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and 1 tablespoon brown sugar, tossing well. Arrange peaches in concentric circles on dough, starting 1-inch from edge.
Sprinkle with 2 teaspoons brown sugar. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until golden and crisp.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Add peanut butter to melt.
Add vanilla and salt.
Add milk.
Remove from heat and stir in 10x sugar to fudge consistency.
Cut and refrigerate.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and oil.
Add baking powder and cinnamon. Stir in zucchini, walnuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until top springs back.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Prepare 13 x 9-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Cut a circle from the center of each slice of bread.
Tear crusts and place in baking dish.
Spread cooked meat and shredded cheese over torn bread.
Place bread circles on top.
In a large mixing bowl, mix eggs and milk; pour over ingredients in baking dish.
Cover with aluminum foil and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake souffle approximately 1/2 hour, covered.
Remove foil and bake about another 1/2 hour or until golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: chewy chocolates
directions: Place 2 pecan halves and a date in clusters on lightly buttered baking sheets.
Melt caramels and cream in saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Spoon over clusters, leaving ends uncovered.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Spread over caramel mixture.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cream tacos
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add tomatoes, beans, chili, cheese and whipped cream.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over chips and sprinkle with cheese.

title: venison lasagna
directions: Finely chop onion and garlic, then lightly brown both in one tablespoon olive oil.
Add venison and cook until brown.
Stir in mushrooms, tomato sauce, tomato paste, tomato soup, oregano, basil and 1 teaspoon salt.
Let simmer gently for 2 hours.
During the last hour, cook lasagna noodles until tender and drain.
Beat egg slightly and add to thawed spinach; add 1 tablespoon olive oil, Ricotta (or cottage cheese), Parmesan cheese and 1 teaspoon salt; mix together well.

title: marinated smoked shrimp(appetizer)
directions: Marinate shrimp in Italian dressing and garlic 1 hour.
Smoke shrimp on slow grill containing hickory chips 1 hour.

title: peach plum fruit pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pie crust.

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
In large bowl or dishpan, combine Crisco, sugar and salt.
Pour the 1 1/2 cups boiling water over Crisco, sugar and salt; stir until Crisco melts and let cool until lukewarm.
Add dissolved yeast and beaten eggs. Add 4 cups flour; stir and add remaining 2 cups flour.
Knead into soft dough; if dough is real sticky, add a little more flour until you have a soft dough, but not stiff.
Form into a large ball; lightly grease the top and let rise at a warm temperature until double in size.
Slightly punch down and make into rolls, not too big, a little larger than a golf ball.
Grease tops.
Let rise to double in size.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes approximately 25 rolls.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Cut up and combine vegetables.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, salad oil and sugar; pour over vegetables.
Marinate for 24 hours in refrigerator.
Serve cold.

title: pneumonia (treatment)(enid, oklahoma, november 1938)
directions: Apply on wool cloth as hot as chest will stand.
Keep hot for 2 hours; fast as you can change.
Then every 15 minutes rest of day.
Enema in morning.

title: mother hood's chess cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix and pour over first layer the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Heat cider in a pan or in a crock-pot.
Add cinnamon, cloves, orange slices and lemon slices.
Aroma will fill house!
Serve hot!
Great for fall days and the holidays.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut round steak into strips.
In a large pot, melt butter (about 5 tablespoons) with the chopped onion.
Coat round steak with flour.
Add to melted butter and onion.
Brown a little, then add the soup and 1 can of water; stir and add seasonings.
Cover and cook on low, stirring once in a while, for about 1 1/2 hours. Serve over cooked noodles or rice.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix water and cornstarch.
Cook until bubbles form.
Remove from heat and sprinkle jello over mixture.
Stir.
Add sweetener. Cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 15 minutes more.

title: monterey chicken cutlets
directions: *For mild version, use Mozzarella cheese.

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: Cook beef and onion until tender; drain.
Combine beef, onion, corn, soup, pimento and 2 cups cheese.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with corn bread and rice.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Heat milk to scalding temperature and melt marshmallows in it. Pour over crushed graham crackers.
Cut up cherries, pineapple, dates and nuts.
Blend together and place into mold with wax paper around it.
Refrigerate.

title: famous pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine filling ingredients in order given; pour into pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake an additional 45 minutes or until knife inserted into center of pie comes out clean.
Cool. Garnish, if desired, with whipped topping.

title: mexican caramel custard(calabacitas guisadas)
directions: Heat the 3/4 cup sugar in a small skillet over low heat until it begins to dissolve.
Increase the heat slightly so sugar will caramelize.
When it has reached the caramel color, pour into a 3-quart baking dish, quickly tipping the dish so the caramel will coat all sides; set aside.
Place the milk, sugar and cinnamon stick in a saucepan and bring slowly to boil, stirring, until the sugar dissolves.

title: sinful hot fudge topping
directions: Place ingredients in microwavable container.
Heat approximately 1 minute on High.
Stir until completely smooth. (Additional heat in small increments if needed.) Serve over ice cream.
Store in refrigerator and reheat as needed.

title: fantastic salad
directions: Sprinkle dry Jell-O over Cool Whip in large bowl, being careful not to deflate Cool Whip. Add other ingredients and spoon into serving dish. Chill.

title: oatmeal chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add soda, flour and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add oats.
Mix.
Add both kinds of chips; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Mix jello and water; add strawberries, pineapple and nuts. Pour half into flat dish and let gel.
Spread half Cool Whip and add remaining half on top and gel.
Spread rest of Cool Whip on top.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: Cook and stir sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and water until thick and bubbly.
Add 3 tablespoons lemon juice. Peel and slice the apples. Pack in clean jars. Do not pack tight.
Fill to 1-inch from top with hot syrup. Put lids and rings on jars. Process in hot water bath: pints, 15 minutes and quarts, 20 minutes.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix yeast with water; cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add flour and salt alternately with water.
Let rise until double. Make into balls, dip into melted butter.
Put 2 or 3 balls in greased muffin pans.
Bake at 350° 15 to 20 minutes.
When removed from pans, pour melted butter over rolls.
These can be refrigerated before the dough rises.

title: sicilian medley
directions: Cook ziti.
In large skillet on medium heat saute sausage 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain fat and increase heat.
Add tomatoes, green pepper, parsley and paste.
Cook and stir 8 to 10 minutes.
Add ziti and olives.
Transfer to platter.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other 3 ingredients.
Pour into the pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, until brown.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon in cup.
Peel and slice apples in bowl.
Pour sugar and cinnamon over apples.
In large bowl mix flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Blend in oil, orange juice, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Pour half the batter in greased and floured tube pan.
Pour in apples.
Pour in rest of batter.
Bake at 400°
for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Pour in puree and seasoning.
Cook and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Remove from heat and mix in cottage cheese.
Cook and drain noodles in buttered pan.
Alternate noodles, meat sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli delight
directions: Cook broccoli until stalks are slightly tender and drain. In bowl mix flour, soup and sour cream. Add onion, salt and pepper. Place broccoli in baking dish. Pour soup over broccoli and sprinkle with stuffing mix. Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes until stuffing mix is golden brown and crisp.

title: pork chop skillet
directions: Blend lemon juice, catsup, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt and Tabasco sauce.
Pour over pork chops.
Let stand 1 hour. Drain sauce and the chops and brown lightly in the shortening. Watch closely not to scorch.
Pare and half the potatoes.
Blend the catsup mixture with water to cover.
Pour over pork chops, potatoes and prunes.
Sprinkle brown sugar over all.
Cover tightly and cook slowly for 45 minutes.

title: squash relish
directions: Thoroughly wash squash.
Trim off and discard each end of squash.
Slice squash thinly crosswise.
Place squash in deep pan, preferably a dishpan.
Cover with water and add salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain and wash.
Mix in a large pot sugar, vinegar, onions, peppers, pimentos, celery seed and turmeric.
Bring to boil.
Add squash and reduce heat to simmer.
Once this mixture is thoroughly hot, proceed to pack in prepared jars for canning. Follow general canning procedure, processing for 20 minutes in boiling water.

title: monkey bread
directions: Working with one can of biscuits at a time, quarter and roll in sugar and cinnamon that has been mixed together.
Put in greased Bundt pan.
Melt butter, brown sugar and water.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Add any leftover sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool for 5 to 10 minutes. Invert onto plate.
Serve warm.

title: rice and green bean casserole
directions: Mix chicken with cubed cheese. Add green beans, soups and rice.
Mix and bake in casserole dish. Top with crackers and melted margarine.
Now cook on top rack of oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: texas chicken
directions: Stew chicken.
Pull from bone and pull apart, shred-like. Combine onion, pepper and soups in a bowl.
Dip corn tortillas (one at a time) in broth from chicken.
Put a layer in bottom of 13 x 9 pan, then a layer of chicken, then spoon a layer of soup mixture. Sprinkle with chili powder and garlic powder, then sprinkle with cheese.
Then start over with layers.
Top layer should be tortillas.
Top with cheese, then pour can of Ro-Tel tomatoes on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: banana delight
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1 stick margarine with graham cracker crumbs and press in pan.
Mix 2 sticks margarine, cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar and pour over crust.
Top with bananas and pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle pecans on top.
Refrigerate.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Melt chocolate.
Sift flour with baking soda and salt.
In a large bowl, beat the butter, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Beat in chocolate.
Beat in flour mixture alternately with buttermilk in thirds, beginning and ending with flour.
Beat in boiling water until smooth.
Bake at 350° in 2 greased 9-inch round pans for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: grandma jane's calico beans
directions: Saute onion.
Cook bacon and dice.
Brown hamburger.
Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sweet "n" sour bites
directions: In a medium saucepan, stir together all ingredients.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat until boiling.
Boil for 2 minutes more or until sauce is slightly thickened.
Makes 2 or 3 servings.

title: caramel icing
directions: Cook 230°; boil to soft boil.
Add butter.
To test, drop syrup in cool water and see if it forms soft ball.
Remove from heat; let cool.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and spread.

title: quick and easy vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat.
In large cooking pot, add rest of ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for about 1 hour or until vegetables are done.

title: dutch windmill cookies
directions: Cream the butter, margarine and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix well with creamed mixture.
Add 1/2 cup sour cream. Knead well and form 2 rolls.
Wrap in wax paper and chill overnight.
Slice and top with sliced almonds.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Lay on newspaper to cool.
Cover with paper towel.

title: georgia coconut pie(makes 2)
directions: Mix together dry ingredients first to prevent flour from lumping.
Add margarine, then eggs, one at a time, buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into 2 pastry shells and bake 10 minutes at 450°; then reduce heat to 375° and bake until done. Top is very brown (about 40 minutes).

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, egg yolks, oil and apricot nectar together. Beat egg whites and fold into batter.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken "n" rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in large, greased baking pan.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Then take off foil and bake for another 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine and cook first 4 ingredients for 30 minutes. Add the remaining ingredients; bring to a boil and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: rice krispie balls
directions: Mix ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Add the vanilla and let cool for 30 minutes.
Add the Rice Krispies and form into balls.
Roll the balls in powdered sugar or crushed nuts.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: *Note: One whole chicken can be used instead of breasts.

title: homemade bread
directions: 1. Combine yeast and warm water. Add flour, sugar, salt, and shortening to yeast mixture. Beat until smooth.
2. Add more flour until dough cleans to the bowl. Turn out
on floured board and knead until dough is smooth. Place
in greased bowl and cover.
3. Let rise in warm place until double in size (appx 1 hr)
Punch down & turn over in bowl. Cover and let rise 15 minutes.
4. Turn out board and divide in 8 parts and form loaves.
Let rise 45 minutes. BAke 40-50 minutes at 400°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Roll graham crackers; mix with butter; press into pie pan. Save approximately 2 tablespoons mixture for top.
Cream the cheese and add milk a little at a time.
Add pudding.
Beat until thick. Pour into pan.
Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture over top. Refrigerate at least 1/2 to 1 hour.
Serve cold.
Yields 8 servings.

title: hueros rancheros
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Warm 4 ovenproof dinner plates.
Pour enchilada sauce into pie plate.
Dip tortillas in sauce.
Place 2 on each plate, overlapping slightly.
Sprinkle with onions and cheese.
Place in oven to melt.
Scramble eggs in melted butter. Remove plates from oven.
Top with eggs and salsa.
Serve with chopped, fresh tomatoes, sour cream and/or guacamole.
Serves 4.

title: easy salad
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Soften cream cheese.
Cut up or chop cherries.
Mix together with pineapple.
Add marshmallows and whip cream.
Add to cream cheese, a little at a time, mixing with each addition.
Add to fruit.
Add some cherry juice to color and moisten.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain fluid from beans; discard.
Mix well all other ingredients and marinate at least 8 hours.
Give beans a stir now and then.
Salad may be garnished with sliced purple onion.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel apples.
Slice into cool water with some lemon juice to keep from browning.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining until crumbs form.
May need to adjust amount of margarine. Spread over apples.
Bake until golden brown.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Boil chicken; reserve broth.
Take chicken off bones and chop meat.
Mix all ingredients except tortillas and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Put 1 tablespoon of mixture in each tortilla; roll up and place in bottom of casserole dish. Pour remaining mixture over top.
Bake at 250°
for about 30 minutes or until cheese bubbles.

title: christmas stollen
directions: Scald milk.
Pour over shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs; add yeast that has been softened in 1/4 cup water..
Add 4 cups flour and beat.
Add citron, raisins, rind, nutmeg and remaining flour.
Knead and place in covered pan to rise 3 to 4 hours.

title: curiouser and curiouser casserole
directions: Place wok over moderately high heat.
Add pasta sauce and chili, stirring to combine.
Add corn; mix well.
Add onion, peppers and parsley; stir.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring often.
Add noodles; cook for 10 to 15 minutes, until sauce reduced a bit.
Remove from heat; sprinkle cheese evenly over surface.
Cover 10 minutes, until cheese melts.
Garnish with chopped scallions.
(You can take it to the table in the wok and lift lid at last minute.)

title: fudge cake
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, flour and soda.
Let butter melt in hot water after removing from burner.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook in a 350° oven or 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: peanut pie
directions: Whip cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk, beating thoroughly into mixture.
Fold topping into mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
Freeze until firm and serve.
Can be frozen if not used.

title: *corn spoon bread
directions: Combine eggs, muffin mix, sour cream and melted butter.
Stir in both types of corn.
Pour into greased, oblong baking pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle grated cheese on the top and bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.
This is a good potato substitute with ham or pork dinner.
Serves 8.

title: cherries jubilee
directions: In small saucepan, combine cherry juice, sugar and cinnamon. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat. Simmer 10 minutes or until syrupy. Add cherries.
Heat through.
Transfer to chafing dish.
Add brandy.
Ignite carefully. When flame dies, spoon over ice cream.

title: hunters casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Saute onion and celery until tender. Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Good casserole for the deer hunting camp.

title: hash brown scallop potatoes
directions: Let hash browns, salt and pepper sit at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered baking dish.
Top with melted butter, pouring over all of top.
Top with croutons.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be made ahead of time.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until brown for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: corn bread cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Blend in nuts last.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla. Mix lightly but well.
Combine dry ingredients and add to mixture and stir until well blended.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: chocolate popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, corn syrup, vinegar and salt thoroughly in a heavy 4-quart saucepan.
Add butter and cook, stirring constantly, over low heat until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to a boil.
Gradually add evaporated milk.
Cook and stir over low heat until mixture reaches 265° (hard ball stage) or until small amount dropped in cold water forms a hard ball.
Stir into popcorn.
Butter hands.
Quickly roll large spoonfuls of mixture into 4-inch balls.
Makes 20 balls.

title: stewed crackers
directions: Heat the water to boiling.
Place crackers in a bowl with a tight-fitting lid.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour boiling water over the crackers and put on lid.
Let steam a few minutes.
Heat the milk and margarine to boiling and also pour this over the crackers.
Stir and serve in soup bowls.
Pour tomato juice over the crackers and serve.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Tie spices in a cheesecloth or place in a tea ball.
Add to cider along with the sugar and orange slices.
Heat to boiling; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: "sweet" sandwich spread
directions: Combine all the ingredients together. Spread on loaf bread for sandwiches.

title: quick mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground meat with onion. Add soups, enchilada sauce and green chilies. Layer with flour tortillas, starting and ending with soup mixture. Top with cheese. Heat until bubbly.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken for 30 minutes.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Put into a baking dish.
Chop and steam broccoli or cook frozen broccoli according to package.
Layer over chicken.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, curry and lemon juice.
Layer over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle with the cheese. Cut the bread into cubes. Drench into the melted butter.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken braccotillini with mushroom and wine sauce
directions: Pound chicken breasts.
Combine next 5 ingredients.
Spread mixture evenly over each breast.
Top each breast with a slice of Prosciutto.
Roll breasts and secure with toothpicks.
Heat oil and margarine.
Brown chicken rolls evenly.
Place rolls in pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Soak rice overnight and simmer while preparing the rest of ingredients.
Brown meat and drain off liquid.
Add onions and celery, mushrooms and soup.
Combine in 1 1/2-quart casserole and sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender.
Rinse well with cool water.
Put in large bowl and stir in dressing.
Stir until spaghetti is coated well.
Let stand overnight or 12 hours.
Put in veggies. May also add cheese, ham or turkey (cubed).
Add more dressing if needed.
Will keep up to a week in the refrigerator.

title: quick 'n easy chicken casserole
directions: Microwave:
Cook broccoli on High for 2 minutes.
Stir in rice, chicken, soup, milk, cheese and onion.
Cook for 6 minutes. Stir.
Add remaining cheese and cook 5 minutes longer.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix and press into 8 x 8-inch pan (or larger) the first three ingredients; bake eight minutes.
Mix cream cheese and 1 cup white sugar and beat until creamy.
Follow directions on Dream Whip package until stiff and fold into cheese mixture.
Spread over crust and cover with cherries.
(Strawberries or blueberries can be used in place of cherries.)
Chill in fridge and serve.

title: nana's baked beans
directions: In a large saucepan, bring beans, salt and 2 quarts water to a boil; boil for 2 minutes. Remove from the heat. Let stand for 1 hour. Drain beans and discard liquid. Return beans to pan. Cover with remaining water; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until beans are tender. Drain, reserving liquid. In a greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish, combine beans, 1 cup liquid, onion, molasses, bacon, brown sugar, mustard and pepper. Cover and bake at 325° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours or until beans are as thick as desired, stirring occasionally. Add more of the reserved cooking liquid if needed. Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Scald milk.
Allow it to cool.
Mix the milk with the rest of the ingredients.
Bake for at least 1 1/2 hours.

title: corn-mushroom bake
directions: In saucepan, stir flour into cream-style corn; add cream cheese and onion salt.
Heat and stir until cream cheese melts. Stir in whole kernel corn, sliced mushrooms and shredded Swiss cheese.
Turn mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Toss crumbs with melted butter to combine; sprinkle on top of casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 400° until heated through (30 to 40 minutes). Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: tia lola's casserole
directions: Boil the chicken until tender; then take out skin, bone and fat.
Shred meat.
Cut tortillas in 4 strips.
Grate cheese.
Mix enough water with the cans of soup to make consistency of a thick sauce.

Divide ingredients in thirds to make 3 complete layers. First, cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with 1/2 cup soup. Assemble by completely covering bottom with a layer of tortillas, followed by soup, chicken, tomato, chilies and cheese in that order.
Then do the following two layers similarly.

title: tamale pie
directions: In a 3-quart microwave-safe bowl, stir together onion, green pepper, oil and garlic.
Microwave uncovered on High (100%) for 3 minutes.
Stir in the chili powder, cumin and 1/2 teaspoon of the salt until absorbed.
Stir in the beef, microwave uncovered on High 5 minutes stirring once.
Stir in tomatoes, break them up with the back of a spoon, and microwave on High 2 minutes stirring once.
In a large bowl, stir together cornmeal, flour, baking powder and remaining 1 teaspoon salt.
Add milk, butter and egg. Stir until thoroughly combined.
Spread the cornbread mixture over the meat mixture in the bowl.
Microwave uncovered on Medium (50%) 18 to 20 minutes or until the cornbread is baked.
Let the dish stand 5 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: apple dump cake
directions: Flour and butter oblong pan.
Layer ingredients in order listed above in pan, ending with melted oleo poured over top. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: celery casserole
directions: In casserole, layer cooked celery, cream of mushroom soup, cheese and water chestnuts in that order.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole 3
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs on top and bake at 350° until firm.

title: apple butter
directions: Combine all ingredients; cook 30 minutes over low heat or cook 1 hour in slow oven.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown beef and drain well.
Mix in other ingredients and pour into a baking dish.
Top with a few strips of lean bacon if desired.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
(May substitute three 16-ounce cans of carrots for fresh carrots.)
Cool and drain.
Cut onion and green pepper and mix with carrots.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover and marinate 12 hours.
Keeps in refrigerator 2 weeks.

title: shrimp florentine
directions: Cook spinach; drain well and set aside.
Make a sauce of the butter, flour and milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick. Add wine, salt, pepper and scallions.
Add enough paprika to make a rosy color.
Add cooked shrimp to sauce mixture.
Arrange spinach in pie pan to form a crust.
Pour sauce over spinach. Top with shredded cheese and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, until bubbly, about 35 to 45 minutes at 325°.
Serves 2.

title: zippy beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook meat, stirring until browned. Drain off fat.
Cook macaroni as directed on package and drain.

title: pumpkin roll up
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Cover a cookie sheet with wax paper and pour mixture on top. Bake at 375 degrees for 15 minutes or until brown. Sprinkle 1/2 c. powdered sugar on to a towel. Flip cake onto sugar coated towel. Remove wax paper and roll cake up in a towel. Unroll when cooled. Spread 1 can sour cream or cream cheese icing over cake. Sprinkle with pecans and roll the cake again. Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Serve chilled.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Place all ingredients except soda in iron skillet over medium heat.
Boil, stirring constantly.
Cook until mixture smells scorched, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir with wooden spoon.
Take off heat and add soda.
Stir quickly.
Spread on buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool; pop out of pan and break in pieces.

title: banana hawaiian delight
directions: Whip the cream until stiff. Add sour cream and sugar. Whip at low speed until just blended. Dip bananas into cream mixture; coat well. Roll in coconut. Serve on tray with chilled fruit. May be prepared several hours ahead.

title: strawberry salad with pretzel crust
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake until brown (about 8 to 10 minutes) at 400°.
Cool.

title: dutch hodgepodge
directions: Melt butter in a heavy skillet. Add chicken and cook until brown on both sides. Transfer the chicken to a heavy pot.
Wash the vegetables.
Peel the carrots and slice into 2-inch pieces. Peel the onions.
Peel and quarter the turnips and potatoes.
Put all the vegetables on top of the chicken. Add parsley, marjoram, bay leaf, salt and pepper.

Add enough cold water to cover all this up. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours. Some liquid will boil away, but serve a piece of chicken and some vegetables in soup bowl with remaining broth.

title: cinnamon-apple oatmeal crisp
directions: In large bowl, mix oats, flour, brown sugar and cloves.
Cut in butter with pastry knife until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in almonds and cinnamon.
Arrange apples in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle mixture over apples.
In 400° oven, bake for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.
Can be topped with your favorite ice cream. Makes about 8 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well; roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: simmering potpourri
directions: Add water in pot and boil.

title: tuna-chip casserole
directions: Place 1 cup potato chips in bottom of greased 1-quart casserole.
Combine all other ingredients.
Mix well; spoon into casserole.
Top with 1/2 cup crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, salt, shortening and milk for pastry and roll into a large circle.
Spread with brown sugar. Mix apples and cinnamon and spread over the sugar.
Roll up jelly-roll style and using a sharp knife, slice into 2-inch pieces. Place in a large cake pan.
Cook sugar, hot water, flour and nutmeg for topping until thick in a small saucepan and pour over dumplings.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: candied pecans
