directions: Combine sugar, water, salt, vanilla and cinnamon. Simmer in a skillet over medium heat (about 5 to 6 minutes) until mixture forms a strong thread from wooden spoon.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pecans.
Stir until all nuts are coated.
Cool on waxed paper. Separate nuts that are stuck together.

title: potluck casserole
directions: Combine chicken, soups, milk and mixed vegetables in bowl. Spoon into 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Prepare stuffing using package directions.
Spread over chicken mixture.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: lemonade dessert
directions: Whip the milk, lemonade and Cool Whip.
Mix crackers and sugar; set aside a little to sprinkle on top.
Melt margarine; add crackers and sugar.
Put in bottom of pan and freeze.
Add filling; sprinkle remaining cracker mixture on top.
Freeze. Serve.

title: peach fluff
directions: In oblong Pyrex dish (approximately 7 x 9-inch) layer ingredients as follows:
1 layer graham crackers, 1 layer drained peaches cut in small pieces and 1 layer Cool Whip.
Repeat layers in same order.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Mix all ingredients, except meat.
Place meat in baking pan. Pour mixture over top.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 250° for 4 hours.

title: cinnamon s'mores squares
directions: Grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix chocolate chips, corn syrup, butter, vanilla and cinnamon in 3-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until boiling.
Stir. Fold in cereal until completely coated with chocolate.
Fold in marshmallows.
Press evenly in pan using buttered back of spoon. Let stand about 1 hour or until cool. Cut into 2-inch squares. Yields 18 squares. Contains 110 calories per square.

title: airedale biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl; make well in center. Melt margarine and syrup in saucepan.
Dissolve baking soda in 1 tablespoon of tepid water; stir into melted margarine and syrup. Pour into dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls the size of large marbles (walnut).
Place 2 inches apart on cookie tray.
Bake at 350° about 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: apple dip
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Slice apples into bottom.
Fill 3/4 full.
Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon.
Crumble together sugar, flour and butter until mixture is fairly fine.
Sprinkle on top of apples.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Double entire recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lemon chewies
directions: Melt your butter in cake pan.
Add two of your eggs, mixing with your butter.
Sprinkle lemon cake mix over your butter mixture, stirring together.
In bowl, blend 2 eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Pour on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: whipped cinnamon butter for quick breads
directions: Beat margarine and cinnamon in small bowl on medium speed until fluffy.
Makes 1 cup.

title: tomato salad
directions: Arrange tomato slices in slightly overlapping, concentric circles on a deep, round plate or platter.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix uncooked rice, soups and water.
Place chicken on top. Cover and bake 2 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: winter carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots in boiling salted water 10 minutes or until tender; drain.
Place in 1 quart casserole.
Combine mayonnaise, onion, salt, pepper and horseradish.
Spoon over carrots.
Mix crumbs and butter.
Put on top of carrots.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Prepare the crust by combining the flour, butter and chopped nuts.
Pat crust into a pan and bake at 325° for 15-20 minutes; watching that you don't overbake.
For the filling, mix together the lemon juice, sweetened condensed milk and the lemonade.
Fold in the cool whip and pour into the nut crust.
Chill 2 hours or overnight.
This pie freezes well.

title: joann's stir-fry
directions: Marinate meat or fish in 1/4 cup or less of teriyaki sauce for 2 hours.
Heat saute pan.
Add 1/2 both oils and stir-fry the meat or fish.
Remove from pan.
Clean pan.

title: hamburger hot dogs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in iron skillet and brown.
Cook until done.
Add black olives and Ro-Tel tomatoes with peppers.
Cook until done.
Add cheese which has been melted.
Place hot dog buns in foil and fill with mixture.
Seal each bun in foil and bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: baked fish
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen.
Rinse, pat dry with paper towels. Spray a 2-quart rectangular baking dish with nonstick coating. Place fish in prepared dish.
Brush with milk.
In a small dish, combine bread crumbs and ginger root.
Sprinkle the crumb mixture and almonds over the fillets.
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 450° for 6 to 12 minutes.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: hamburger, bean and tater tot casserole
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper.
Add chopped onion and put uncooked into bottom of 8 x 12-inch pan.
Add well-drained beans, spreading evenly over meat.
Spread undiluted cheese soup over beans.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4. (Can be prepared and stored in refrigerator or freezer until baked.)

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Blend in flour, soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Chill 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375°.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls two inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Bake for 10 minutes, do not overbake.

title: cuban piccodillo
directions: Brown beef; drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice.
Cook 10 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together vanilla, sugar, egg and shortening.
Add soda and sour milk.
Mix and blend with vanilla and sugar mixture.
Sift together baking powder, flour and salt.
Mix with milk and sugar mixture until well blended, then add enough extra flour to make dough stiff enough to roll and cut.
This makes several cookies.

title: play dough recipe
directions: Add flour until mixture isn't sticky.
Add food coloring according to the depth of color wanted.

title: schnitzel
directions: Mix milk and egg.
Pound pork thin; dip into milk and egg mixture.
Then coat with bread crumbs or Fryin' Magic.
Have frying pan with 1/4-inch oil heating.
Fry on each side until brown.
Only takes a few minutes.
Drain and serve.
I usually serve with green beans, rice and/or homemade French fries.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Add enough red food coloring to color this mixture.
Bake pie crust and make the mixture.
Cook this until boiling or until thickened.
Set aside and cool.
Put a layer of strawberries on cooked pie crust and then put on the cooled mixture.
Slice strawberries on top.
Chill for a couple of hours.

title: cheese crescent appetizers
directions: Unroll crescents and cut triangles in half.
Take cube of cheese and place on small triangle and roll into crescent moon shape.
Brush with beaten egg and bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm on warming tray.
Yield:

title: monkey bread
directions: With dough at room temperature, cut into small pieces. Stretch each piece; dip in melted butter.
Dredge in cinnamon and sugar.
Put into a greased Bundt cake pan.
(Let pieces flop every-which-way.)
Cover and let rise.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Turn down to 350° for another 30 to 35 minutes.
Share with others!
(Made this with many kindergarten children for many years.)

title: pat's party spaghetti
directions: Brown meat lightly in large skillet or stew pan.
Drain any excess grease.
Add tomatoes, Ro-Tel tomatoes, green chilies, mushrooms, olives and onion.
Mix thoroughly.
Add cheese and spaghetti.
Crumble bacon over all.
Mix gently and place in large baking dish or 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese, crusty rolls and a green salad.
Serves 12 to 14 people.

title: pineapple raisin cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add egg and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together and add to creamed mixture.

title: pimento and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients and enjoy. This freezes well.

title: cauliflower and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter; stir in soup and pour over vegetables.
Put cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until bubbly.
Top with onion rings and cook for 5 more minutes.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Melt margarine; add flour and nuts.
Spread in two pie plates.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 minutes.	Cool 15 minutes.

title: coquilles de volailles
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Boil the chicken until tender and remove meat from the bones; cut into pieces, not too small. Season with salt and pepper; pour the sherry over meat.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Blend melted margarine, sugar and vanilla. Add eggs and mix well. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt. Gradually add to egg mixture; blend well. Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool and frost with chocolate frosting.

title: sour cream chicken breast
directions: Salt, pepper and paprika each piece of chicken.
Spoon sour cream over pieces.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over this and pour melted oleo over all.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: turkey piccata
directions: In a large skillet, brown turkey with onion.
Drain fat. Place meat mixture in a large crock-pot and add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together well.
Cook on lowest setting for 8 to 10 hours.
Stir well before serving.
Stores well for up to a week, if you have it around that long!

title: brownie pizza pie
directions: Melt unsweetened chocolate.
Cream margarine with brown sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in vanilla.
Combine salt and flour and stir in gradually.
Spread in a 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 325° about 10 minutes.
Top warm pizza with pecan halves, milk chocolate (cut up) and semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Melt white chocolate and drizzle over the top to look like melted cheese.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix cooked, diced chicken with peas, drained oranges, drained water chestnuts, onion and mayonnaise, sour cream and slivered almonds.
Just pour boiling water over the peas; do not cook.
Top with Chinese noodles when ready to serve.

title: potato casserole
directions: In 13 x 9-inch casserole, mix potatoes and all ingredients. Top with 1/4 cup melted butter with 2 cups crushed cornflakes. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Grease or butter casserole dish.
Layer sliced potatoes, salt, pepper, soup mix, butter, crackers and ham.
Keep layering, ending with potatoes and crackers.
Pour milk in until you can just about see it (1/2-inch from top).
Cover with foil or lid.
Bake at 350° to 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: custard pie x 2
directions: Mix together well the first 3 ingredients.
Add the boiling water and vanilla.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 300° until knife comes out clean.

title: raisin and carrot salad
directions: Mix carrots and raisins in bowl.
Toss with mayonnaise and lemon juice.

title: cottage cheese pie
directions: Combine all. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 40 min. or until crust is done.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: german pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt butter in pan (in oven).
Mix other ingredients.
Pour into preheated pan.
Bake 15-20 minutes.
Top with fresh fruit, powdered sugar, lemon juice, syrup (use your imagination).

title: homemade biscuit mix
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in 1 cup shortening, using a pastry blender.
The mixtures should resemble coarse meal.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Use 1/3 cup milk to 1 cup of biscuit mix.

title: chicken divan
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put broccoli in bottom.
Cut up chicken breasts and put on top of broccoli.
Mix other ingredients and spread evenly.
Be sure to spread mix all the way to edges. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Put back in oven just to melt cheese.

title: maraschino party cake
directions: Place first 7 ingredients in mixing bowl and beat with electric mixer 2 minutes.
Add egg whites.
Beat 2 minutes more. Stir in cherries and nuts.
Bake at 350°.

title: holiday ham balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place about 2-inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° or until lightly brown. Immediately remove from pan.
Serve warm.
Makes about 7 dozen appetizers.

title: standard chicken dressing
directions: Melt butter and mix all ingredients, then place stuffing in poultry.
Cook your poultry in oven as called for.

title: quick sloppy joes
directions: Add beef and onion; brown in skillet.
Season with salt, pepper, garlic and seasoned salt.
Drain.
Add ketchup, tomato sauce, A.1. sauce, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Stir; simmer to taste.
Serve on buns.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine in large bowl oil, peanut butter and both sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla, flour, baking soda and salt.
Form into balls and put on cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 36 large cookies.

title: ziti spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Add seasoning, sauce, water and pepperoni; simmer 15 minutes.
Boil pasta, mix with sauce.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with cheese.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: gringo taco
directions: Brown ground beef, add onion, pepper and seasonings.
Cook until tender, then drain.
Mix in enchilada sauce, tomato sauce and Milnot.
Layer tortilla, meat mixture, cheese and sauce mixture until all used.
I usually layer three times.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
This is great served with a tossed green salad.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon, flattening with fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in medium bowl. Make well in center. Mix milk, egg, oil, banana and nuts in small bowl. Pour into well. Mix batter just until moistened. Do not overmix. Spoon mixture into prepared muffin cups. Bake about 15 minutes or until golden brown. Test with toothpick.

title: spiced tea
directions: *Optional with lemon or add 1 package lemon Kool-Aid.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix
vanilla
wafer crumbs, orange juice, margarine and powdered
sugar.
Shape
in balls.	Roll in pecans or coconut. Place in covered container and refrigerate.

title: apple dilly cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg until light.
Stir in dry ingredients; alternate with coffee.
Add apples, nuts and raisins. Double this recipe and bake in greased tube pan at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Can be frosted, if desired.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cornstarch and cocoa.
Add melted margarine and eggs, one at a time.
Then add vanilla and milk. Next add pecans and coconut.
Bake one hour at 300°.
Makes 3 pies.

title: traditional pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, combine filling ingredients.
Mix well and turn into crust.
Bake 15 minutes, then reduce oven temperature to 350° and continue baking 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean. Cool before cutting.
Garnish with whipped cream and nuts, if desired.
Refrigerate leftovers

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients and roll into small balls.
Place on a cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Ingredients mix together better if they are at room temperature.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Layer in punch bowl. Needs to set overnight.

title: marshmallow krispies
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows; stir constantly, until marshmallows are melted and mixture is syrupy.
Remove pan from heat.
Add cereal; stir.
Spread in buttered pan; press top with wax paper to spread to sides of pan. Cut when cool.
Yields about 24 (2-inch) squares.

title: layer salad
directions: Tear apart lettuce into a large bowl.
Chop cauliflower and spread over lettuce.
Spread a thin layer of mayonnaise on top of cauliflower (use as much as necessary to cover).
Sprinkle cooked bacon (crumbled) over layer of mayonnaise.
Chop green onions and spread layer next.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over entire salad. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
To serve, mix all ingredients and serve.

title: bean bake
directions: Fry together bacon, hamburger and onion.
Add to beans, then add brown sugar, catsup, vinegar, dry mustard and garlic.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or put in crock-pot for 2 or 3 hours.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, milk, salt, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, onion, egg and parsley.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Cook meatballs in 12-inch skillet over medium heat, about 15 minutes, turning occasionally, until brown.
Remove meatballs from skillet; drain.

title: lo-cal shrimp creole
directions: Brown onion and garlic in oil.
Add shrimp, tomato sauce, tomatoes, pepper and herbs.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Serve with rice.
For fat-free dish, omit oil.

title: johnny's mississippi mud pie
directions: Stir 1/2 cup cocoa into 2 sticks melted oleo.
Set aside.
In mixing bowl, mix together sugar, flour and salt.
Using mixer, beat in eggs.
Add cocoa mix.
Stir in pecans.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch prepared pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool.
Spread marshmallow cream on slightly warm cake.

title: tongue slapping special
directions: Mix dressing according to package directions.
Cut steak, about 1/2-inch thick.
Marinate in glass container for 48 hours, then grill.

title: chocolate-dipped strawberries
directions: Partially melt chocolate squares over very low heat in saucepan.
Remove from heat; stir rapidly until entirely melted. Wash and dry strawberries with stems.
Holding by stem, dip one at a time, in chocolate.
Cover 3/4 berry.
Put on wire rack, stem down, until chocolate is firm.

title: white chocolate raspberry cake
directions: Microwave baking bars and water in small microwave bowl on High, about 2 minutes or until bars are melted.
Cool.
Mix 1/4 cup flour, coconut and almonds in small bowl; set aside.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 round pans (9 x 1 1/2-inches).
Beat margarine and 1 1/2 cups sugar in large bowl on medium speed until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks and baking bar mix.
Add 2 1/4 cups flour and baking soda alternately with buttermilk, beating until thoroughly blended.
Stir in coconut mix.
Set aside.
Beat egg whites on high until soft peaks form.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, beat until stiff, but not dry.
Fold egg white mix into batter. Divide among pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until cake springs back when touched or toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks. Fill layers with jam.
Frost with Vanilla Buttercream Frosting. Garnish with additional coconut and grated white baking bar, if desired.

title: oven-fried zucchini
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Spray cookie sheet liberally with vegetable cooking spray.

title: french bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in bowl; add oil and warm water. Knead until dough is mixed well, about 15 minutes.
Grease bowl; cover dough with wet towel.
Proof in warm place until double in size.
Form into loaf (grease pan).
Let rise again until doubled. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; lower temperature to 350° until done.

title: fiery hot chili
directions: In a large skillet, braise meat in 1/4 cup oil until brown. Transfer meat to large kettle or electric slow cooker, leaving liquid in skillet.
Add water and tomato sauce to meat, cook over low heat.
Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in remaining 1/4 cup of oil and liquid in skillet.
Add remaining dry ingredients. Simmer about 30 minutes, then transfer to kettle.
Simmer about 2 hours.
Dip off grease that settles on top.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine corn oil and sugar and beat with a beater.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large bowl and mix by hand using a wooden spoon, stirring well after each addition.
When all ingredients have been added and mixed well, pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
(Spray pan with Pam.)

title: butter rolls
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, mix 2 cups of the water, milk, 1 1/2 cups sugar and vanilla.
Set aside.
In a mixing bowl, mix Bisquick biscuits according to box directions*.
Take half the dough and roll out in a rectangle about 3/8-inch thick.
Slice 1 stick butter over dough; sprinkle 3/4 cup sugar over butter.
Roll up from long side.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Place in pan with milk mixture.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar on top of rolls.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut butter bars(tastes like reese's cups)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and press into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Melt chocolate chips.
Pour on top.
Can refrigerate overnight.
Cut into bars.

title: peanut butter sundaes
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and water. Bring to boil. Boil 1 minute or until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Place in a blender. Blend on high until smooth. Sprinkle with peanuts, if desired.

title: taco potato sticks
directions: Cut potatoes in wedges, roll in butter.
Mix crumbs and taco sauce in bag.
Add potatoes and shake well.
Place on baking pan, skin side down.
Bake at 400° until tender.
Serve with sour cream.

title: pimento cheese sandwich spread
directions: Cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Take off heat.
Add 1 cup mayonnaise. Keeps in refrigerator a month.

title: horseradish salad
directions: Mix and chill Jell-O, water, salt and paprika.
Mix whipped cream and mayonnaise; fold into Jell-O mixture.
Add horseradish and olives.
Let set.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar thoroughly and until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; blend well.
Add flour, baking powder and milk; then add flavorings.
Blend well.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool cake 5 minutes before removing from pan.
Drizzle glaze over cake while still hot.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and drain.
Chop bell peppers and onion.
Cook and drain.
Cook egg noodles until almost done.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients together except cheese.
Use a large casserole dish and pour in mixture.
Add a layer of cheese slices, mixture, then a layer of cheese.
Put into oven and bake at 350° until cheese bubbles and is brown.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and vanilla well; add creams and mix.
Put mixture in drum and add milk to a little less 3/4 of the drum.

title: golden cream of potato soup
directions: Combine ingredients (except last 3)
in a heavy saucepan or Dutch oven.
Cook together until tender (approximately 20 minutes).

title: dollie's eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cook eggplant in water; drain.
Add salt and pepper. Mash.
Saute onion in oleo.
Mash tomatoes; mix with onion. Combine with eggplant.
Add beaten eggs and bread crumbs.
Grease casserole dish; spoon in mixture.
Cover with milk; top with cheese.
Bake at 375° until hot through and cheese is melted.

title: southern ambrosia
directions: Cut the oranges into bite size pieces.
This should make about 4 cups.
In medium size serving bowl, layer half of the oranges, half of the sugar, and half of the coconut. Repeat.

title: oreo cheesecake
directions: Finely roll 30 cookies.
Coarsely chop 20.
Combine finely rolled cookie crumbs and margarine.
Press on the bottom and 2-inches up sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels with milk in double boiler.
Set aside, but keep warm.
Combine cake mix with water, butter and eggs in a large mixer bowl and blend on low speed 30 seconds, then beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Pour half the batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until cake puffs up and is gooey.
Remove cake from oven and pour caramel-milk mixture over partially baked layer.
Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips evenly over caramel.
Pour remaining batter over all and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until top springs back when touched lightly.
Top with ice cream and cut into squares.

title: monkey bread
directions: Pop can and cut each biscuit into quarters.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in plastic bag, coating each of biscuit pieces with sugar-cinnamon mixture.

title: pork chops and peaches
directions: Drain peaches reserving syrup.
Moisten chops in 1/4 cup reserved syrup.
Coat chops as directed on package of Shake 'N Bake.
Reserve remaining mix.
Arrange chops in single layer on rack in ungreased shallow baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost with Cool Whip mixed with 1 package pistachio instant pudding mix.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: Place apples in baking dish (8 x 8-inch).
Combine remaining ingredients; crumble and spread over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix the above ingredients together and serve as a dip for sliced apples.

title: wild meat balls
directions: Mix beef, onion, salt and pepper.
Using 1 level tablespoon for each, shape into balls.
In large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon each of butter and oil.
Add half of the meatballs and brown on all sides.
Drain on brown paper; repeat.

title: cheesey corn and ham chowder
directions: Melt the butter in a Dutch oven over low heat.
Add the carrots and onion; saute over low heat until tender, but not brown, about 10 minutes.
Blend in the flour and cook, stirring, for 3 minutes.
Add the milk and broth; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until the mixture has thickened.

title: chili rice dish
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add salt & pepper.
Brown onion and garlic and add chili powder to taste.
Then add stewed tomatoes and RoTel tomatoes.
Next add raw rice; cover and simmer over low heat until rice is done.
Stir before serving.

title: german chocolate muffins
directions: Melt butter and chocolate over low heat in an iron skillet. Take off heat; add last 4 ingredients.
Stir gently.
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Remove from tins immediately.

title: cherry dessert
directions: In 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan, spread pie filling.
Cover with cake mix (as is).
Sprinkle with nuts.
Melt margarine.
Pour over evenly.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Mix together with oiled hands and make into rolls; then roll in saved crumbs.
Put in foil and refrigerate.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch; set aside.
Heat water and chocolate until chocolate is melted.
Stir in cornstarch and sugar.
Boil about 3 minutes or until mixture is thickened.
Take off heat, stir in butter and vanilla.
Enough for 2 layer cake.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: avy's catfish stew
directions: Cut onions into 1/4 inch slices.
Cut "taters" into 1/2 inch slices.
Salt and pepper catfish and "tater" slices.
In a large Dutch oven or stew pot, fry the bacon until crisp, leaving the grease.
Add 1/2 cup of water.
Lay one layer of fish, then a layer of onion, and then a layer of bacon.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used up.
Leave one thick potato on top. Cover and cook about 1 hour on low heat.
Do not stir!
When the top potato is done, its ready.

title: melissa's super-duper blizzard
directions: Spoon a couple of scoops of ice cream into a bowl.
Add the candy, banana slices and hot fudge.
Then stir it all up until the ice cream is soupy.
Dig in and enjoy!

title: omelette casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; line bottom with sliced cheese. Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix in some chopped ham or crumbled bacon, some chopped onion, chopped green peppers, sliced mushrooms (amounts according to taste).
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
To make a larger amount, add 2 more eggs and 1/4 cup milk.

title: zucchini-cauliflower toss
directions: In a small saucepan, combine water, vinegar, cornstarch, oil, mustard, garlic salt, celery seed and pepper.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat; stir in Equal.
In a large bowl, combine vegetables; toss with dressing.
Cover and chill 2 to 24 hours or until serving time, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Flake salmon with fork.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well in shallow pan over medium heat.
Add a little cooking oil.
Drop by spoonfuls and fry until golden brown on both sides.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Garnish with chives, cheese and bacon crumbs.

title: marshmallow creme fudge(never fail)
directions: Bring sugar, milk and butter to a boil.
Cook to medium soft ball stage (236°), stirring frequently.
Remove from heat. Immediately add Marshmallow Creme, chocolate chips and nuts.
Stir until Creme and chips have melted.
Pour into 2 plates that have been buttered good.
Let cool; cut in squares.
Yields about 3 pounds.

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain juice from clams.
Pour over vegetables in saucepan. Add enough water to barely cover and simmer until potatoes are done.

title: filled patty shells
directions: In a medium bowl, combine the cheese, drained mushrooms and pimento.
In small bowl, stir together the sour cream with salt, thyme and pepper.
Add the sour cream mixture to the chicken mixture; stir until well mixed.
Brush the dough with egg white. Place shells on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 425°
for 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Follow package directions. Fill shells with chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° until brown.

title: raisin sauce for baked ham
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add raisins, wine vinegar and water. Cook to a slightly thick syrup.
Cool.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix in order.
Shape in round shape, 1 or 2 balls, and place in pan.
Save 1/4 can of tomato soup and mix with water to make a full can of liquid soup.
Pour over the meat loaf.
Sprinkle with garlic powder on top of meat loaf.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
The last 1/2 hour, uncover meat loaf.

title: baked apples(microwave)
directions: Core apples.
Cut a strip of peel from the top of each.
Place apples in 8-inch round cake dish.
Press 1 tablespoon brown sugar into each hole.
Add 1/2 teaspoon butter and a dash of cinnamon or nutmeg.
Cook apples on Low for 5 minutes.
Turn dish.
Cook on Medium for 5 minutes.
Place apples in serving dish.
Pour any syrup left in the baking dish into the center of apples.
Cool before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: maxcine's tuna and rice casserole
directions: Mix all together and put 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese sprinkled on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is slightly brown.

title: ham and cheese frittata
directions: In a skillet, melt butter over medium heat. Saute mushrooms, pepper and onions until tender.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Make crust of pretzels, margarine and 1/2 cup sugar.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch dish at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: sticky buns
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Tear bread into chunks.
Melt butter, add brown sugar, milk, cinnamon and pudding. Stir until smooth and dump over rolls.
Cover tightly and leave in refrigerator overnight.
Pop in oven at 350° for one half hour before you plan to eat them.
Let cool a couple minutes and turn bottom side up.

title: cheddar potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine milk, butter, onion flakes, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes and cheese.
Mix well.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 1 hour or until bubbly and golden brown.

title: pecan squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth and light.
Beat in egg yolk, flavoring and flour until well mixed.
Pat evenly into a pan (8 x 8).
Beat the egg white slightly and brush over the dough. Sprinkle the pecans evenly on top and press them in the dough slightly.
Bake 16 to 18 minutes at 375° or until golden brown. Cool in pan and cut into squares.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in Crisco.
Mix with vegetable oil and ice water, adding a little at a time, until soft, smooth ball.
Roll out on floured surface.
Bake at 475° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: toll house marble squares
directions: Mix butter, sugars and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Blend in flour, soda and salt.
Mix in nuts if used.
Spread in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Place in a 375° oven for 1 minute.
Remove and run knife through to marbleize. Bake 12 to 14 minutes.

title: parmesan bread sticks
directions: Cut each biscuit in half.
Roll until pencil shaped, about 4-inches long.
Roll sticks in butter.
Place on cookie sheet. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes until golden brown.

title: potato hot dish
directions: Place hash browns in a bowl.
Mix together cream of potato soup, cream of celery soup and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes and let stand until potatoes thaw.
Add chopped onions and green peppers.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle parsley on top and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 300°.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Pour in 2 (8 or 9-inch) round cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: helen's lemon cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Mix powdered sugar, lemon juice and oil together.
While cake is still warm, punch holes with fork over entire cake.
Pour mixture over cake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and put into casserole dish. Sprinkle top and bottom with bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
Pour off grease; add tomato paste, tomatoes and salt.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Mix cottage cheese, parsley and oregano.
Let set for flavors to absorb.
Mix Cheddar and Mozzarella cheeses.
Cook noodles.
Place by layers in 2-inch deep large pan, half of tomato-beef sauce, layer noodles, half of cottage cheese mixture and half of grated cheeses; repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Cream butter and 3 tablespoons sugar; add crushed pretzels. Mix well.
Press into 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese and 1 cup sugar until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzel crust.
Chill. Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Stir in strawberries. Chill until partially congealed.
Spread over cream cheese layer. Chill until firm.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Melt the chocolate chips and butter in double boiler. Add condensed milk and vanilla.

Put flour in a large mixing bowl and gradually pour in hot chocolate mixture while beaters are running. Add pecans and stir well. Set aside for 10 minutes. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 9 minutes.

title: chocolate icebox dessert
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well.
Add egg yolks, chocolate syrup and marshmallows.
Fold in beaten egg whites; add nuts. Cover bottom of pan with half the graham cracker crumbs; spread mixture over crust. Cover with remaining crumbs. Refrigerate for 24 hours. Cut into squares.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: mexican pot roast
directions: Saute 1 bunch chopped green onions and green pepper in butter. Add 1 can tomato sauce.
Add shredded pot roast and all cans of beans and salsas.
Place catsup tamales and olives in last, lightly stirring.
(Do not drain beans except for pintos and garbanzos.)
Place cheese on top and cover.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° until warmed through and bubbly.
Can remove lid if getting too much moisture.
This is best made the day before to allow flavors to mingle.
Serve with tortilla chips and green chilies. Can be frozen.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Spread rice ina 9 x 13 baking dish. Add water. Sprinkle dry onion soup over rice and water mixture. Season chicken to taste and place chicken, skin side up on rice mixture.
Slightly dilute soup with milk and spread over top of chicken. Cover with foil and bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: chicken and broccoli saute
directions: Thaw broccoli and cut in half.
Cut chicken into pieces.
Chop red pepper.
Saute chicken, red pepper and mushrooms in 1/3 cup of olive oil and 1/4 cup of margarine.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and Italian seasoning.
Add soup; stir and heat through.
Boil 4 quarts of water; salt.
Add rigatoni; cook 15 minutes, then add thawed broccoli and cook for 3 to 5 minutes longer.
Drain in colander.
Pour chicken mixture over rigatoni and broccoli.
Add Romano and Parmesan cheese.
Toss and serve.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Simmer beans, water and consomme for 2 hours.
Saute onions in butter until tender.
Add to soup along with remaining ingredients.
Add more water if needed.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Ready to serve.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix all dry ingredients
and
sift.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into an 11	x
x
2-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: In large bowl, sift flour, soda and powder.
Cut in margarine as for pie crust.
Beat eggs; add sugar and beat again.
Blend egg mixture into flour mixture.
Roll out on floured board to 1/4-inch thickness; cut out cookies.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from cookie sheet at once.

title: snow tunnel cake
directions: Bake cake in accordance with box directions. Cool. Slice 1 inch layer off the top. Gently hollow out a trench in the cake 1-1/2 inches wide and 2 inches deep. Tear cake from trench into small pieces. Combine milk and pudding mix. Beat on low for 2 minutes. Fold cake pieces and 1-3/4 c. of topping into pudding. Fill trench with mixture. Replace top of cake. Spread remaining topping over sides and top of cake. Chill until set.

title: madrilane
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.
Strain through cheesecloth or a dish towel.
You will be straining out the tomato puree.
You will have about 6 cups of soup.
You may wish to add a topping of sour cream or yogurt.

title: broccoli casserole with chicken
directions: Combine soup and milk.
Pour over chicken in bottom of dish. Then layer cheese, followed by broccoli.
Top with onion rings from can.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until broccoli is tender.

title: chow chow
directions: You will need 13 half-pint jars with lids.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients; will be more like cookie dough than cake batter.
Pat into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: out of this world pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cool until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add jello (dry).
Cool.
Add bananas; place in two baked pie shells.
Chill.
Top with Cool Whip.
Enjoy.

title: three grain bread
directions: In a large bowl, put the first 3 ingredients and set aside. Heat together the skim milk, honey, Canola oil, sugar and salt in a large pan and warm to lukewarm.
Then break the yeast into the liquid and mix by hand until it becomes smooth.
Pour this mixture into the flour in the large bowl.
Gradually add the remaining 2 1/4 to 2 1/2 cups flour, just enough to make a moderately stiff dough.
Turn onto a floured surface and knead until smooth.
Place dough in greased bowl, turning once.
Cover; let rise once until doubled.
Form three loaves; put into greased bread pans.
Let rise to double in size.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Line pie pan with pastry; set aside.
Brown bacon slices; drain, dice and cool.
Combine eggs, cheese and onion salt in medium mixing bowl.
Stir in diced bacon.
Add cream or evaporated milk; blend well.
Pour egg mixture into pie shell; bake in a 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve hot in wedges.
Serves 6.

title: pork chop apple bake
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Peel apples.
Slice in bottom of dish.
Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon. Sprinkle over apples.
Place raw pork chops on top of apples.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: carrot-cheese log
directions: Finely shred the carrots.
In a small mixing bowl, stir together carrots, cream cheese, Parmesan cheese and fine herbs. Cover and chill cheese mixture for at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: white bean, tomato and basil salad *
directions: Soak the beans in water to cover overnight.
Drain and cover with fresh water.
Simmer until tender (about 1 hour or more), adding salt to taste after first 30 minutes.
Drain the beans and put them in a serving bowl.
Add the oil and onion and toss thoroughly while the beans are still hot.
Just before serving, add the tomatoes and basil leaves.
Toss and correct seasoning. Serves 6 to 8.

title: jello chiffon
directions: Make jello according to directions on package.
Refrigerate until firm, then whip jello 2 minutes and add dry milk.
Continue whipping with mixer another 5 minutes.
It will get light and fluffy.
Drained fruit may be added.
Refrigerate.

title: baby ruth candy cookies
directions: In saucepan, mix cocoa, butter, sugar and milk.
Bring to boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix well working fast.
Drop on waxed paper.
Cool for 1 hour.

title: banana pudding
directions: Follow box instructions for mixing pudding.
Add vanilla and about 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Layer the following in a bowl: cookies, banana slices, pudding.
Make several layers.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: In a large bowl mix together oil, egg and sugar.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add dry ingredients and fruit cocktail.
Add topping.

title: fruit cake
directions: Combine fruit and peel.
Add brandy.
Mix well.
Let stand 3 to 4 hours.
Cream butter and gradually beat in sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla and beat in eggs, one at a time, until well blended.
Resift flour.
Add to
milk.
Add to cream mixture alternately with milk.
Combine batter with fruit mixture and milk.
Grease 2 pans and line with heavy paper.
Fill 2/3 full. Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours or until done.
Cool and brush with brandy or sherry and store.
Makes approximately 3 pounds.
